AIApplication.description: Represents an instance of a machine learning (ML) application.
AIApplication.label: AI Application

AIApplicationConfig.description: Represents additional prediction information related to a machine learning (ML) application.
AIApplicationConfig.label: AI Application config

AIInsightAction.description: Represents an Einstein prediction insight action.
AIInsightAction.label: AI Insight Action

AIInsightFeedback.description: Represents an Einstein prediction insight feedback.
AIInsightFeedback.label: AI Insight Feedback

AIInsightReason.description: Represents an Einstein prediction insight reason.
AIInsightReason.label: AI Insight Reason

AIInsightValue.description: Represents an Einstein prediction insight value.
AIInsightValue.label: AI Insight Value

AIResearchPromptResult.description: Represents the research result generated by Einstein from a prompt template.

API Total Usage.description: API Total usage events contain details about Platform SOAP API, Platform REST API, and Bulk API requests.

AbnExperiment.description: Represents an A/B/n experiment that's used with Marketing Cloud Next content, Experience Cloud websites, and platform automations.
AbnExperiment.label: Experiment

AbnExperimentCohort.description: Represents the specified audience that's participating in an A/B/n experiment.
AbnExperimentCohort.label: Experiment Cohort

AcadTermEnrlPolicyRuleLog.description: Represents the log of the policy rule calculation runs for an academic term enrollment.

AcademicCredential.description: A credential which can be earned by learners.

AcademicSession.description: Records course offering period. Specifies time periods based on an institution’s calendar whether that is semesters, quarters, trimesters, or other terms.

AcademicTerm.description: Defines an academic period which may hold other more defined time periods within it to create a specific time for reporting and offerings.

AcademicTermEnrollment.description: Represents information about a student's enrollment in an Academic Term.

AcademicTermPolicyRule.description: Represents a junction between Academic Term and Expression Set objects where an expression set is used as a policy rule for the academic term.

AcademicTermRegstrnTimeline.description: Represents the registration time window for an academic term.

AcceptedEventRelation.description: Represents event participants (invitees or attendees) with the status Accepted for a given event.
AcceptedEventRelation.label: Accepted Event Relation

Account.description: Standard and custom fields extend the standard Account object for use in Consumer Goods Cloud to represent an individual account, which is an company or person involved with your business, such as customers, competitors, and partners.
Account.label: Account

AccountAccountRelation.description: Represents a relationship between accounts, such as a relationship between a business account and a household account.
AccountAccountRelation.label: Account Account Relationship

AccountBillingAccount.description: Represents a junction between Account objects and Billing Account objects.
AccountBillingAccount.label: Account Billing Account

AccountBrand.description: Represents the brand details of a Partner Account.
AccountBrand.label: Account Brand

AccountCleanInfo.description: Stores the metadata Data.com Clean uses to determine an account record’s clean status. AccountCleanInfo helps you automate the cleaning or related processing of account records.
AccountCleanInfo.label: Account Clean Info

AccountContactRelation.description: Standard and custom fields extend the standard Account object for use in Public Sector Solutions to represent information of members in a household
AccountContactRelation.label: Account Contact Relationship

AccountContactRole.description: Represents the role that a Contact plays on an Account.
AccountContactRole.label: Account Contact Role

AccountFinancialSummary.description: Represents the summary of financial details associated with an account.

AccountForecast.description: Represents the rolling forecast record of a particular account. The forecast is prepared using data directly from sales agreements, orders, and opportunities.
AccountForecast.label: Account Forecast

AccountForecastAdjustment.description: Represents the manual adjustments made to forecast values for a particular account.
AccountForecastAdjustment.label: Account Forecast Adjustment

AccountForecastPeriodMetric.description: Represents records of account metrics which vary by period but are not specific for a product.
AccountForecastPeriodMetric.label: Account Forecast Period Metric

AccountInsight.description: Represents an individual insight (a key business development) related to an account record.

AccountOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing an account with a User other than the owner.
AccountOwnerSharingRule.label: Account Owner Rule

AccountParticipant.description: Represents information about a participant in the context of an account record.

AccountPartner.description: This object represents a partner relationship between two Account records. An AccountPartner record is created automatically when a Partner record is created for a partner relationship between two accounts. An AccountPartner record is also created automatically between an account and an opportunity’s account when a Partner record is created between an account and an opportunity.
AccountPartner.label: Account Partner

AccountPlan.description: Represents customer information with measurable objectives and executable steps to proactively manage and grow customer relationships.
AccountPlan.label: Account Plan

AccountPlanObjMeasCalcCond.label: Account Plan Objective Measure Calculation Condition

AccountPlanObjMeasCalcDef.description: Represents the metadata associated with an account plan objective measure calculation definition. An account plan objective measure calculation definition contains a target object, rollup field, and logic for calculating the current value of a sales account plan objective measure.
AccountPlanObjMeasCalcDef.label: Account Plan Objective Measure Calculation Definition

AccountPlanObjMeasCalcDefLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of the definition of a target object, rollup field, and logic for calculating the current value of a sales account plan objective measure.
AccountPlanObjMeasCalcDefLocalization.label: Translation

AccountPlanObjMeasRela.description: Represents a junction between an account plan objective measure and the related objects.
AccountPlanObjMeasRela.label: Account Plan Objective Measure Relation

AccountPlanObjective.description: Represents strategic objectives or initiatives pursued by a relationship team with a customer to enhance customer engagement and satisfaction.
AccountPlanObjective.label: Account Plan Objective

AccountPlanObjectiveMeasure.description: Represents the performance of target metrics for an objective associated with the account plan.
AccountPlanObjectiveMeasure.label: Account Plan Objective Measure

AccountProductForecast.description: Represents the cumulative values for planned quantities, opportunities, and orders of a sales agreement for a given product across all periods in that rolling time period.
AccountProductForecast.label: Account Product Forecast

AccountProductPeriodForecast.description: Represents the quantity and revenue information of opportunities, sales agreements, orders, and resultant forecasted quantities for a product in a particular time period of the forecast rolling period. Other than the fields AdjustedForecastQuantity and AdjustedForecastRevenue, no other fields of this object can be updated.
AccountProductPeriodForecast.label: Account Product Period Forecast

AccountRelationship.description: Represents a relationship of a given type between two accounts.
AccountRelationship.label: Account Relationship

AccountRelationshipShareRule.description: Represents the rule that determines which object records are shared, how they are shared, the account relationship type that shares the records, and the level of access granted to the records. This object is available in API version 45.0 and later.
AccountRelationshipShareRule.label: Account Relationship Data Sharing Rule

AccountServicePreference.description: Represents the preferences an account has for the services they receive. In Home Health, this object represents the preferences that a patient has for the health workers assigned to their visits.

AccountShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on an account.
AccountShare.label: Account Share

AccountTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with an Account.

AccountTeamMember.description: Represents a User who is a member of an Account team.
AccountTeamMember.label: Account Team Member

AccountTerritoryAssignmentRule.description: An account assignment rule that assigns accounts to territories based on account fields. Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.

AccountTerritoryAssignmentRuleItem.description: A row of selection criteria for an AccountTerritoryAssignmentRule object. Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.

AccountTerritorySharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing an Account within a territory.

AccountUserTerritory2View.description: Represents the view of the Users in Assigned Territories related list in Lightning Experience for Sales Territories.
AccountUserTerritory2View.label: Account User Territory2 View

AccountingFieldMapping.description: Represents the custom field mappings used to populate transaction journal records with other Salesforce data.
AccountingFieldMapping.label: Accounting Field Mapping

AccountingModelConfig.description: Represents settings for the accounting models used with Accounting Subledger. Accounting models are based on accounting sets, which include details about what accounting data is used and how.
AccountingModelConfig.label: Accounting Model Config

AccountingPeriod.description: Represents information about a time period for which businesses prepare reports and analyze performance. Each billing transaction is associated with an accounting period.

Accreditation.description: Represents the professional accreditations of a facility. For example, a joint commission accredits a facility as a general acute care hospital.
Accreditation.label: Accreditation

ActionCadence.description: Represents the definition of a cadence.

ActionCadenceRule.description: Represents the logic that a branch step uses to determine which branch an action cadence tracker follows in an action cadence. Use ActionCadenceRule to learn about a branch step, including its logic and what the next step is.

ActionCadenceRuleCondition.description: Represents the logic for a branch step.

ActionCadenceStep.description: Represents a step in a cadence. Use ActionCadenceStep to learn which steps belong to a cadence, and how the steps are connected to each other.

ActionCadenceStepTracker.description: Represents a step in an active cadence for a specific cadence target.

ActionCadenceStepVariant.description: Represents an email template or call script variant associated with an action cadence step. Email and call steps can have up to 3 variants associated so sales teams can compare the engagement results.

ActionCdncStpMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for an action cadence step.

ActionLinkGroupTemplate.description: Action link templates let you reuse action link definitions and package and distribute action links. An action link is a button on a feed element. Clicking on an action link can take a user to another Web page, initiate a file download, or invoke an API call to an external server or Salesforce. Use action links to integrate Salesforce and third-party services into the feed. Every action link belongs to an action link group and action links within the group are mutually exclusive.
ActionLinkGroupTemplate.label: Action Link Group Template

ActionLinkTemplate.description: Action link templates let you reuse action link definitions and package and distribute action links. An action link is a button on a feed element. Clicking an action link can take a user to another Web page, initiate a file download, or invoke an API call to an external server or Salesforce. Use action links to integrate Salesforce and third-party services into the feed.
ActionLinkTemplate.label: Action Link Template

ActionPlan.description: Represents the instance of an action plan, a set of tasks created from an action plan template.
ActionPlan.label: Action Plan

ActionPlanBaseTemplateAsgn.description: Represents a junction between an action plan template and a related record. An action plan template can be assigned to a job position, position, or a recruitment requisition.

ActionPlanItem.description: Represents the instance of an action plan item.
ActionPlanItem.label: Action Plan Item

ActionPlanTemplate.description: Represents the instance of an action plan template.
ActionPlanTemplate.label: Action Plan Template

ActionPlanTemplateAssignment.description: Represents the association of an action plan template with its related care plan template, goal, or problem definition. When instantiated, the action plan generates the corresponding intervention tasks and links them to the appropriate record, such as a condition, goal, or care plan.

ActionPlanTemplateItem.description: Represents the instance of an item on an action plan template version.
ActionPlanTemplateItem.label: Action Plan Template Item

ActionPlanTemplateItemValue.description: Represents the value associated with an action plan template item.
ActionPlanTemplateItemValue.label: Action Plan Template Item Value

ActionPlanTemplateVersion.description: Represents the version of an action plan template.
ActionPlanTemplateVersion.label: Action Plan Template Version

ActionPlanTmplItmAssessmentInd.description: Represents the action plan template items and the assessment indicator definitions associated with them.
ActionPlanTmplItmAssessmentInd.label: Action Plan Template Item Assessment Indicator

ActionVisibility.description: This object serves as a junction to connect Account or Contact to other objects so that information in those other object can be used to define visibility rules for actions in the Dynamic Actions for Unified Health Scoring component.

ActionableEventSubtype.description: Represents the subtype of an external or internal event that's processed by the Actionable Event Orchestration framework to trigger different types of actions.

ActionableEventType.description: Represents the type of an external or internal event that's processed by the Actionable Event Orchestration framework to trigger different types of actions.

ActionableEventTypeDef.description: Represents the definition of an actionable event type so that the records can be migrated from one org to another.
ActionableEventTypeDef.label: Actionable Event Type Definition

ActionableListMbrInvitation.description: Represents a relationship between an Actionable List Member and an Appointment Invitation.

ActionableOrchResponseEvent.description: Represents information about an internal or external event after actions are taken by the orchestration process and the response is recorded.

ActionableOrchSourceEvent.description: Represents information about an event on which actions are taken by the orchestration process.

ActivationPlatform.description: Represents metadata about ActivationPlatform, such as platform name, delivery schedule, output format, and destination folder. This object is available in API version 54.0 and later.
ActivationPlatform.label: Activation Platform

ActiveFeatureLicenseMetric.description: Represents the number of active, assigned, and purchased feature licenses in the org.
ActiveFeatureLicenseMetric.label: Active Feature License Metric

ActivePermSetLicenseMetric.description: Represents the number of active, assigned, and purchased permission set licenses in the org.
ActivePermSetLicenseMetric.label: Active Permission Set License Metric

ActiveProfileMetric.description: Represents the profile associated with the active, assigned, and purchased user licenses.
ActiveProfileMetric.label: Active Profile Metric

ActivityFieldHistory.description: Represents a change in a field value for a tracked object or field.
ActivityFieldHistory.label: Activity Field History

ActivityHistory.description: This read-only object is displayed in a related list of closed activities—past events and closed tasks—related to an object. It includes activities for all contacts related to the object. ActivityHistory fields for phone calls are only available if your organization uses Salesforce CRM Call Center.
ActivityHistory.label: Activity History

ActivityMetric.description: Represents activities that were added to Salesforce automatically by Einstein Activity Capture and manually by users.

ActivityUsrConnectionStatus.description: Represents the status of the email connections for Einstein Activity Capture users. You can also see whether users accepted the required terms of service to capture emails.

ActnblListKeyPrfmIndDef.label: Actionable List Key Performance Indicator Definition

ActvPfrmDataConnectorS3.label: Activation Platform Data Connector for S3

AdditionalNumber.description: Represents an optional additional number for a call center. This additional number is visible in the call center's phone directory.
AdditionalNumber.label: Additional Directory Number

Address.description: Represents a mailing, billing, or home address.
Address.label: Address

AdvAccountForecastFact.description: Represents information about the generated advanced account forecast records.
AdvAccountForecastFact.label: Advanced Account Forecast Fact

AdvAccountForecastPeriod.description: Represents information about the periods for which advanced account forecasting is applied.
AdvAccountForecastPeriod.label: Advanced Account Forecast Period

AdvAccountForecastSet.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up an advanced account forecast set.
AdvAccountForecastSet.label: Advanced Account Forecast Set

AdvAcctForecastAdjPeriod.description: Represents details about the adjustment period of the advanced account forecast values.
AdvAcctForecastAdjPeriod.label: Advanced Account Forecast Adjustment Period

AdvAcctForecastDimSource.description: Represents information about the dimensions that can be used by advanced account forecast sets to generate advanced account forecast records.
AdvAcctForecastDimSource.label: Advanced Account Forecast Dimension Source

AdvAcctForecastDimension.description: Represents information about the dimensions selected for an advanced account forecast set.
AdvAcctForecastDimension.label: Advanced Account Forecast Dimension

AdvAcctForecastFactAdj.description: Represents information about adjustments made to advanced account forecast fact records.
AdvAcctForecastFactAdj.label: Advanced Account Forecast Fact Adjustment

AdvAcctForecastMeasureDef.description: Represents information about the measures to be displayed in the advanced account forecasts grid for the forecast set.
AdvAcctForecastMeasureDef.label: Advanced Account Forecast Measure Definition

AdvAcctForecastPeriodGroup.description: Represents information about advanced account forecast period records. This is the parent object of all the related advanced account forecast period records.
AdvAcctForecastPeriodGroup.label: Advanced Account Forecast Period Group

AdvAcctForecastSetPartner.description: Represents a junction between an advanced account forecast set and an account.
AdvAcctForecastSetPartner.label: Advanced Account Forecast Set Partner

AdvAcctForecastSetUse.description: Represents a junction between an advanced account forecast set and another object whose record serves as the context for generating forecasts. For example, a manufacturing program or a Sustainability Cloud object’s record can be the context for generating forecasts.
AdvAcctForecastSetUse.label: Advanced Account Forecast Set Use

AdvAcctFrcstDisplayGroup.description: Represents information about the groups for the advanced account forecast set measures or dimensions.
AdvAcctFrcstDisplayGroup.label: Advanced Account Forecast Display Group

AdvAcctFrcstDplyGroupItem.description: Represents information about the items associated with a display group for an advanced account forecast set.
AdvAcctFrcstDplyGroupItem.label: Advanced Account Forecast Display Group Item

AdvTherapyFieldOptOverride.description: Represents a list of fields with changed optionality, based on certain parameters.

AgeBandHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on the age band that they’re a part of and the status of their benefits eligibility.
AgeBandHlthRskAdjFctr.label: Age Band Health Risk Adjustment Factor

AgentWork.description: Represents a work assignment that’s been routed to an agent. If the work is transferred to another agent, a new AgentWork record is created. This object is available in API version 32.0 and later.
AgentWork.label: Agent Work

AgentWorkSkill.description: Represents a skill used to route a work assignment to an agent. AgentWorkSkill is used for reporting and represents the result of a routing decision.

AiGenActionItem.description: Represents business actions suggested by generative AI. AI-generated action items are sent to either agents for automatic execution or human users for review, depending on org preference and if there are any errors in the process.

AiJobRun.description: Represents an execution instance of an AI job. This object tracks the overall status and manages the lifecycle of the job from initiation to completion.
AiJobRun.label: AI Job Run

AiJobRunItem.description: Stores an individual item associated with a parent AiJobRun, including the inputs and resulting response.
AiJobRunItem.label: AI Job Run Item

AiModelLanguage.description: An object that stores language related information that is generated for each AI model.

AiVisitTaskRcmd.description: Represents the visit task recommendations. These recommendations can be accepted or rejected by a sales manager.

AiVisitTaskRcmdRequest.description: Represents the request parameters and responses of visit task recommendations.

AirTravelEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 commercial air travel.
AirTravelEmssnFctr.label: Air Travel Emissions Factor

AirTravelEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to air travel.
AirTravelEnrgyUse.label: Air Travel Energy Use

AllowedEmailDomain.description: Represents an allowed email domain for users in your organization. You can define an allowlist to restrict the email domains allowed in a user’s Email field.

AlternativePaymentMethod.description: Represents a payment method that isn’t cash, a debit card, or a credit card. This object defines methods that aren’t defined by the CardPaymentMethod or DigitalWallet objects. Examples of alternative payment methods include CashOnDeliver, Klarna, and Direct Debit. AlternativePaymentMethod functions the same as any other type of payment method for processing transactions through a payment gateway.
AlternativePaymentMethod.label: Alternative Payment Method

AnalyticsChangeEventLog.description: Analytics Change Event Logs represent route or page changes made in the CRM Analytics.

AnalyticsDownloadEventLog.description: AnalyticsDownloadEventLog represent downloads made from lens and dashboard in the CRM Analytics.

AnalyticsInteractEventLog.description: Analytics Interact Event Log represents route or page changes made in the CRM Analytic UI.

AnalyticsPerfEventLog.description: Analytics Perf Event Log helps track trends in your Analytics performance.

AnalyticsVizField.description: Represents a Tableau Next viusalization field.
AnalyticsVizField.label: Analytics Visualization Field

AnalyticsVizViewDef.description: Represents a Tableau Next viusalization view definition.
AnalyticsVizViewDef.label: Analytics Visualization View Definition

AnalyticsWorkspaceAsset.description: Represents a Tableau Next asset in a workspace.
AnalyticsWorkspaceAsset.label: Analytics Workspace Asset

AnnualEmssnInventory.description: Represents information about a company's total carbon emissions for a particular year in metric tonnes of CO2e (tCO2e). These emissions are the sum of all the emissions in scope 1, scope 2, and scope 3 greenhouse gas categories.
AnnualEmssnInventory.label: Annual Emissions Inventory

AnnualEmssnInventoryExtension.description: Represents additional information about a company's total carbon emissions for a particular year in metric tonnes of CO2e (tCO2e).
AnnualEmssnInventoryExtension.label: Annual Emissions Inventory Extension

AnnualEmssnRdctnTarget.description: Represents information about the emissions reduction target set by a company for a particular year.
AnnualEmssnRdctnTarget.label: Annual Emissions Reduction Target

AntiCorruptionInitSum.description: Represents information about the initiatives taken by an organization to communicate and train the employee on anti-corruption policies and procedures.
AntiCorruptionInitSum.label: Anti-Corruption Initiative Summary

Apex Callout Event Type.description: Apex Callout events contain details about callouts (external requests) during Apex code execution.

Apex Limit Event Object.description: ApexLimitEvent represents an Apex execution governor limit.

Apex REST API Event Type.description: Apex REST API events capture information about every Apex REST API request.

Apex SOAP Event Type.description: Apex SOAP events contain details about custom SOAP web service calls.

Apex Trigger Event Type.description: Apex Trigger events contain details about triggers that fire in an organization.

Apex Unexpected Exception Event Type.description: The Apex Unexpected Exception event type captures information about unexpected exceptions in Apex code execution.

ApexCalloutEventLog.description: Apex Callout event logs contain details about callouts (external requests) during Apex code execution.

ApexClass.description: Represents the saved copy of an Apex class. ApexClass uses the cached version of the class unless one is unavailable.
ApexClass.label: Apex Class

ApexClassMember.description: Represents the working copy of an Apex class for editing, saving, or compiling in a MetadataContainer.
ApexClassMember.label: Metadata Container Member

ApexCodeCoverage.description: Represents code coverage test results for an Apex class or trigger.
ApexCodeCoverage.label: Apex Code Coverage Data

ApexCodeCoverageAggregate.description: Represents aggregate code coverage test results for an Apex class or trigger. Available in Tooling API version 29.0 and later.
ApexCodeCoverageAggregate.label: Apex Code Coverage Aggregate Data

ApexComponent.description: Represents the saved copy of a Visualforce component. ApexComponent uses the cached version of the class unless one is unavailable.
ApexComponent.label: Visualforce Component

ApexComponentMember.description: Represents the working copy of a Visualforce component for editing, saving, or compiling in a MetadataContainer.
ApexComponentMember.label: Metadata Container Member

ApexEmailNotification.description: Stores a Salesforce user ID or external email address to be notified when unhandled Apex exceptions occur.
ApexEmailNotification.label: Apex Email Notification

ApexExecutionEventLog.description: Apex Execution event logs contain details about Apex classes that are used.

ApexExecutionOverlayAction.description: Specifies an Apex code snippet or SOQL query to execute at a specific line of code in an Apex class or trigger. Optionally, generates a heap dump.
ApexExecutionOverlayAction.label: Apex Execution Overlay Action

ApexExecutionOverlayResult.description: Represents the result from the Apex code snippet or SOQL query defined in the associated ApexExecutionOverlayAction, and the resulting heap dump if one was returned.
ApexExecutionOverlayResult.label: Apex Execution Overlay Result

ApexExtlCalloutEventLog.description: Apex Extl Callout EventLog represent external data callouts via custom adapters for Salesforce Connect.

ApexOrgWideCoverage.description: Represents code coverage test results for an entire organization.
ApexOrgWideCoverage.label: Apex Org-wide Code Coverage

ApexPage.description: Represents the saved copy of a Visualforce page. ApexPage uses the cached version of the page unless one is unavailable.
ApexPage.label: Visualforce Page

ApexPageInfo.description: Represents metadata about a Visualforce page.
ApexPageInfo.label: Apex Page Info

ApexPageMember.description: Represents the working copy of a Visualforce page for editing, saving, or compiling in a MetadataContainer.
ApexPageMember.label: Metadata Container Member

ApexRestApiEventLog.description: Apex REST API event logs capture information about every Apex REST API request.

ApexResult.description: A complex type that represents the result of Apex code executed as part of an ApexExecutionOverlayAction, returned in an ApexExecutionOverlayResult.

ApexSoapApiEventLog.description: Apex SOAP event logs contain details about custom SOAP web service calls.

ApexTestQueueItem.description: Represents a single Apex class in the Apex job queue.
ApexTestQueueItem.label: Apex Test Queue Item

ApexTestResult.description: Represents the result of an Apex test method execution.
ApexTestResult.label: Application Test Result

ApexTestResultLimits.description: Captures the Apex test limits used for a particular test method execution. An instance of this object is associated with each ApexTestResult object.
ApexTestResultLimits.label: Apex Test Result Limit

ApexTestRunResult.description: Contains summary information about all the test methods that were run in a particular Apex job.
ApexTestRunResult.label: Apex Test Run Result

ApexTestSuite.description: Represents a suite of Apex classes to include in a test run. A TestSuiteMembership object associates each class with the suite.
ApexTestSuite.label: Apex Test Suite

ApexTrigger.description: Represents the saved copy of an Apex trigger. ApexTrigger uses the cached version of the class unless one is unavailable.
ApexTrigger.label: Apex Trigger

ApexTriggerEventLog.description: Apex Trigger event logs contain details about triggers that fire in an organization.

ApexTriggerMember.description: Represents the working copy of an Apex trigger for editing, saving, or compiling in a MetadataContainer.
ApexTriggerMember.label: Metadata Container Member

ApexTypeImplementor.description: Represents Apex classes that directly or indirectly implement an interface. Using a SOQL query, this object gets information about public or global classes and only global classes for installed managed packages.
ApexTypeImplementor.label: Apex Type Implementor

ApexUnexpectedExcpEventLog.description: Apex Unexpected Excp Event Log captures information about unexpected exceptions in Apex code execution.

ApiTotalUsageEventLog.description: API Total Usage Event Log contains details about Platform SOAP API, Platform REST API, and Bulk API requests.

AppAnalyticsQueryRequest.description: Represents a request for AppExchange App Analytics data.
AppAnalyticsQueryRequest.label: App Analytics Query Request

AppDefinition.description: Represents the metadata of an app and its navigation items. Metadata is returned only for apps that the current user can access.
AppDefinition.label: App Definition

AppExtension.description: Represents a connection between the Field Service mobile app and another app, typically for passing record data to the Salesforce mobile app or other apps.
AppExtension.label: App Extension

AppFormProdtPrpsAttribute.description: Represents the attributes and values of an Application Form Product Proposal record.

AppFormProductCollateral.description: Represents a physical or financial asset that is pledged as collateral for an application form product.

AppFormProductParticipant.description: Represents information about the application form product participant.

AppMenuItem.description: Represents the organization’s default settings for items in the app menu or App Launcher.
AppMenuItem.label: AppMenuItem

AppTabMember.description: Represents the list of tabs for each of the available apps.
AppTabMember.label: App Tab Member

AppUsageAssignment.description: Provides application context for a record. A record can have different allowed actions or different related objects when it’s created for different applications. For example, a Revenue Lifecycle Management order has a related RevenueLifecycleManagement AppUsageAssignment, so Salesforce knows it can create assets for that order.
AppUsageAssignment.label: Application Usage Assignment

Applicant.description: Represents information about the individual or group that are applying.
Applicant.label: Applicant

ApplicantApplicantRelation.description: Represents the relationship between applicants, where an applicant can be either a business entity or an individual.
ApplicantApplicantRelation.label: Applicant-Applicant Relation

ApplicationActionItem.description: Stores the action items assigned to a user on an application.

ApplicationCase.description: This junction object stores a relationship between Case and IndividualApplication.
ApplicationCase.label: Application Case

ApplicationForm.description: Represents the high level information of an application that's submitted for the product.
ApplicationForm.label: Application Form

ApplicationFormEvalPtcp.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to an application form evaluation.

ApplicationFormEvaluation.description: Represents the details of the evaluation performed for an application form. For example, the details of the evaluation of a loan application form by an underwriter.

ApplicationFormParticipant.description: Represents information about the application form participant.

ApplicationFormProduct.description: Represents a junction between the application and the product requested by an applicant.
ApplicationFormProduct.label: Application Form Product

ApplicationFormProductDev.description: Represents a junction between an application form product and a deviation.

ApplicationFormProductFee.description: Represents the fees associated with an application form.

ApplicationFormProductProposal.description: Represents the proposal presented by the financial institution to the applicant with details of interest rate, monthly payment, validity dates, and total interest.

ApplicationFormRelation.description: Represents the relationship between an application and the context in which it’s held. For example, a application form related to recruitment requisition.

ApplicationFormSellerItem.description: Represents a junction between an application form and a seller product.

ApplicationFormTemplate.description: Represents the fields to capture application metadata as a template which is used in application tracking and processing.

ApplicationFormTerm.description: Represents the terms associated with an application form for a loan or a lease.

ApplicationRecommendation.description: Represents information about the recommendation for an individual application.

ApplicationRecommender.description: Represents a junction between an individual application and the recommender of the application.

ApplicationRenderMethod.description: Represents how a part of an application can be rendered.

ApplicationReview.description: Represents a review performed against a specified Individual Application.

ApplicationSectionDefinition.description: Represents the section of an application.

ApplicationStageDefinition.description: Represents a stage of an application.

ApplicationSubtypeDefinition.description: Represents a subtype of an application within an application domain.
ApplicationSubtypeDefinition.label: Application Subtype Definition

ApplnRenderMethodAssignment.description: Represents an assignment of the application render method to a component that's rendered in the application.

ApplnStageSectionDefinition.description: Represents a junction between an application stage definition and application section definition.

AppointmentAssignmentPolicy.description: Stores information about resource assignment rules.
AppointmentAssignmentPolicy.label: Appointment Assignment Policy

AppointmentCategory.description: Represents the category of work types and shifts.
AppointmentCategory.label: Appointment Category

AppointmentInvitation.description: Represents information about an appointment invitation that’s created for customers who can use it for booking appointments.
AppointmentInvitation.label: Appointment Invitation

AppointmentInvitee.description: Represents information about the participant and resources required for creating an appointment invitation URL.
AppointmentInvitee.label: Appointment Invitee

AppointmentScheduleAggr.description: Records the utilization of a service resource, by date, for the Load Balancing appointment assignment policy.
AppointmentScheduleAggr.label: Appointment Schedule Aggregate

AppointmentScheduleLog.description: Stores service appointments of each service Resource.
AppointmentScheduleLog.label: Appointment Schedule Log

AppointmentSchedulingPolicy.description: Represents a set of rules for scheduling appointments using Salesforce Scheduler.
AppointmentSchedulingPolicy.label: Appointment Scheduling Policy

AppointmentTopicTimeSlot.description: Represents a lookup to a work type or a work type group for a time slot
AppointmentTopicTimeSlot.label: Appointment Topic Time Slot

Approval.description: Represents an approval request for a Contract.

ApprovalSubmission.description: Represents the instance of an approval request that's submitted for a record of the related object.

ApprovalSubmissionDetail.description: ApprovalSubmissionDetail contains additional information about operations happening during the approval lifecycle. It will not hold any information that’s already captured in the existing ApprovalSubmission and ApprovalWorkItem entities.
ApprovalSubmissionDetail.label: Approval Submission Detail

ApprovalWorkItemCondition.description: Represents a condition for starting and concluding an approval step that's evaluated as part of the smart approval process.
ApprovalWorkItemCondition.label: Approval Work Item Condition

ApprovalWorkItemCriteria.description: Represents the logic by which a smart approval request is evaluated.
ApprovalWorkItemCriteria.label: Approval Work Item Criteria

ApptBookingConfig.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up appointment scheduling.

ApptBookingUrlConfig.description: Represents a collection of fields used to set up the URL paths for appointment scheduling endpoints.

ApptBundleAggrDurDnscale.description: Sums the duration of the bundle members, reduced by a predefined percentage.
ApptBundleAggrDurDnscale.label: Appointment Bundle Aggregation Duration Downscale

ApptBundleAggrPolicy.description: Policy that defines how the property values of the bundle members are aggregated and assigned to the bundle.
ApptBundleAggrPolicy.label: Appointment Bundle Aggregation Policy

ApptBundleConfig.description: Represents the general parameters that define the behavior of the bundle.
ApptBundleConfig.label: Appointment Bundle Config

ApptBundlePolicy.description: Policy that defines how the bundling of service appointments should be handled.
ApptBundlePolicy.label: Appointment Bundle Policy

ApptBundlePolicySvcTerr.description: Represents a link between the BundlePolicy and the ServiceTerritory.
ApptBundlePolicySvcTerr.label: Appointment Bundle Policy Service Territory

ApptBundlePropagatePolicy.description: Policy that defines which property values are inherited from the bundle to the bundle members or are assigned as constant values in the bundle members.
ApptBundlePropagatePolicy.label: Appointment Bundle Propagation Policy

ApptBundleRestrictPolicy.description: Policy that defines the restrictions that are considered while forming a bundle.
ApptBundleRestrictPolicy.label: Appointment Bundle Restriction Policy

ApptBundleSortPolicy.description: Policy that defines the properties by which the bundle members are sorted within the bundle. Can also be used in the automatic mode for determining the order of the automatic selection of bundle members.
ApptBundleSortPolicy.label: Appointment Bundle Sort Policy

ArchiveActivity.description: Represents metadata retrieved for a single Archive process initiated by an action. Retrieved metadata can include status tracking, start and end times, record counts, and monitoring and auditing outcomes.

ArchivePolicyDefinition.description: Represents a data lifecycle policy that, in each row, defines the scope, frequency, and rules for automated archiving or purging of records from a root entity, such as Contact or Lead.

Article Type__DataCategorySelection.description: A data category selection represents a data category that classifies an article.

AsgnRsrcApptSchdEvent.description: Represents the assigned resources that are part of various platform events. This object is included in a streamed notification received on the channels for the parent platform events. You can’t subscribe to the AsgnRsrcApptSchdEvent channel directly.
AsgnRsrcApptSchdEvent.label: Assigned Resource Appointment Scheduling Event

AsmtQstnMaterialityTpc.description: Represents a junction between a materiality topic and an assessment question.

AsmtQstnRespRecommendation.description: Maps an assessment question’s response to the recommendation it has to provide for a care plan. Recommendations can be problems, goals, interventions, or other assessments.
AsmtQstnRespRecommendation.label: Assessment Question Response Recommendation

Assessment.description: Stores the header data for an assessment.
Assessment.label: Assessment

AssessmentConfiguration.description: Represents a configuration for Assessment component. An AssessmentConfiguration entry indicates configuration for user flows such as sending out emails or reminder actions on assessments initiated by the patient.
AssessmentConfiguration.label: Assessment Configuration

AssessmentDefinition.description: Represents the definition of an assessment including details such as the last revised date and purpose.
AssessmentDefinition.label: Assessment Definition

AssessmentEnvelope.description: Represents information about an envelope that contains the assessments related to a user. For example, you can create an envelope that contains assessments for a patient or a caregiver related to depression or anxiety.
AssessmentEnvelope.label: Assessment Envelope

AssessmentEnvelopeItem.description: Represents information about an item in an envelope that contains the assessments related to a user. For example, you can create an item that contains an assessment for depression or anxiety.
AssessmentEnvelopeItem.label: Assessment Envelope Item

AssessmentIndDefinedValue.description: Stores the list of acceptable values which are defined as part of assessment indicator definition for a single and multi select question.
AssessmentIndDefinedValue.label: Assessment Indicator Defined Value

AssessmentIndValue.description: Stores the list of target or captured values which are defined as part of assessment indicator definition for a single and multi select question.

AssessmentIndicatorDefinition.description: Define parameters that act as markers of compliance for retail tasks to compare target and actual values.
AssessmentIndicatorDefinition.label: Assessment Indicator Definition

AssessmentQstnVerChoice2.description: Represents a choice a user can select for an assessment question version.

AssessmentQuestion.description: Represents the container object that stores the questions required for an assessment.
AssessmentQuestion.label: Assessment Question

AssessmentQuestionAssignment.description: Represents a junction between an assessment question set and an assessment question.
AssessmentQuestionAssignment.label: Assessment Question Assignment

AssessmentQuestionConfig.description: Represents the assessment question record metadata configuration.
AssessmentQuestionConfig.label: Assessment Question Config

AssessmentQuestionResponse.description: Stores the responses submitted to an assessment.
AssessmentQuestionResponse.label: Assessment Question Response

AssessmentQuestionSetConfig.description: Reqpresents the assessment question set record metadata configuration.
AssessmentQuestionSetConfig.label: Assessment Question Set Config

AssessmentQuestionVersion.description: Stores the question versions for the assessment questions.
AssessmentQuestionVersion.label: Assessment Question Version

AssessmentReason.description: Represents the reasons for an assessment such as the associated coverage information.

AssessmentSavedSession.description: Represents a session of an assessment that's saved to resume for later.
AssessmentSavedSession.label: Assessment Saved Session

AssessmentSignature.description: Stores the respondent’s signature during an assessment.
AssessmentSignature.label: Assessment Signature

AssessmentStagedData.description: Represents the responses to assessment questions when a user captures and submits information with the Discovery Framework Data Capture Flow on a mobile device. The information is used to create assessment and related records.

AssessmentTask.description: Perform activities such as planogram check, inventory check, promotion check, in-store survey, or custom task in stores to capture information.
AssessmentTask.label: Assessment Task

AssessmentTaskContentDocument.description: Associate content documents to visits, tasks, promotions, or planograms.
AssessmentTaskContentDocument.label: Assessment Task Content Document

AssessmentTaskDefinition.description: Associate an assessment task with an assessment indicator definition.
AssessmentTaskDefinition.label: Assessment Task Definition

AssessmentTaskIndDefinition.description: Associate an assessment indicator definition with an assessment task definition.
AssessmentTaskIndDefinition.label: Assessment Task Indicator Definition

AssessmentTaskOrder.description: Define an order activity that the sales rep can perform during a visit to the stores.
AssessmentTaskOrder.label: Assessment Task Order

Asset.description: Represents an item of commercial value, such as a product sold by your company or a competitor, that a customer has purchased.

AssetAccountParticipant.description: Represents a junction between the Asset and Account objects describing the association between a participating account and an asset.
AssetAccountParticipant.label: Asset Account Participant

AssetAction.description: Represents a change made to a lifecycle-managed asset. The fields can’t be edited.

AssetActionSource.description: Represents an optional way to record what transactions caused changes to lifecycle-managed assets. Use it to trace financial and other information about asset actions. This object supports Salesforce order products and work order line items, and transaction IDs from other systems. The fields can’t be edited.

AssetAttribute.description: Stores asset attributes to track and analyze asset conditions to improve their uptime.
AssetAttribute.label: Asset Attribute

AssetContactParticipant.description: Represents a junction between the Asset and Contact objects describing the association between a participating contact and an asset.
AssetContactParticipant.label: Asset Contact Participant

AssetContractRelationship.description: Represents a relationship between an asset and a contract.

AssetDowntimePeriod.description: Represents a period during which an asset is not able to perform as expected. Downtime periods include planned activities, such as maintenance, and unplanned events, such as mechanical breakdown.

AssetFulfillmentDecomp.description: Represents the relationship between an ordered asset and its corresponding fulfillment asset.

AssetMilestone.description: Represents the key events in the lifecycle of an asset, such as manufacturing, registration, or resale.

AssetOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing an Asset with users other than the owner.

AssetRateAdjustment.description: Stores the tier rate adjustments for the asset rate card entries.
AssetRateAdjustment.label: Asset Rate Adjustment

AssetRateCardEntry.description: Stores the negotiated rate card entries that are associated with an asset in Revenue Cloud.

AssetRelationship.description: Represents a non-hierarchical relationship between assets due to an asset modification; for example, a replacement, upgrade, or other circumstance. In Subscription Management and Revenue Lifecycle Management, this object represents an asset or assets grouped in a bundle or set.

AssetShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on an Asset.

AssetStatePeriod.description: Represents a time span when an asset has the same quantity, amount, and monthly recurring revenue (MRR). An asset has as many asset state periods as there are changes to it (asset actions) during its lifecycle. The dashboard and related pages show the current asset state period. The fields can’t be edited.

AssetStatePeriodAttribute.description: Represents a virtual object that holds the key-value pair of the asset attribute in a specified asset state period. This object is a child object of AssetStatePeriod.

AssetTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with an Asset.

AssetTitle.description: Represents information that establishes the legal ownership of an asset or a vehicle.

AssetTitleParty.description: Represents the relationship between an account, a contact, or a user and an asset title.

AssetTokenEvent.description: The documentation has moved to AssetTokenEvent in the Platform Events Developer Guide.

AssetType.description: Represents a type of asset, such as a type of item, physical space, or service offering.

AssetWarranty.description: Defines the warranty terms applicable to an asset along with any exclusions and extensions.

AssignedResource.description: Represents a service resource who is assigned to a service appointment in Field Service and Lightning Scheduler. Assigned resources appear in the Assigned Resources related list on service appointments.
AssignedResource.label: Assigned Resource

AssociatedLocation.description: Represents a link between an account and a location in Field Service. You can associate multiple accounts with one location. For example, a shopping center location may have multiple customer accounts.
AssociatedLocation.label: Associated Location

Assortment.description: Represents a list of products that are eligible for sale in a store.

AsyncApexJob.description: Represents an individual Apex sharing recalculation job, a batch Apex job, a method with the future annotation, or a job that implements Queueable or Schedulable. Use this object to query Apex batch jobs in your organization.
AsyncApexJob.label: Apex Job

AsyncOpSyndicationFeedFile.description: Represents the sync status of file-related information shared with external channels such as Facebook and Instagram.

AsyncOperationLog.description: Represents an async operations log containing progress and status information about external synchronizations to the Omnichannel Inventory service.
AsyncOperationLog.label: Async Operation Log

AsyncOperationTracker.description: Represents the status of an asynchronous request initiated from the Quote, Order, and CreditMemo entities.
AsyncOperationTracker.label: Async Operation Tracker

AsyncReportRunEventLog.description: Async Report Run Event Log is used for reporting scheduled requests. This category includes dashboard refreshes, asynchronous reports, schedule reports, and analytics snapshots.

Asynchronous Report Run Event Type.description: Asynchronous Report Run events are created for reporting requests that are scheduled. This category includes dashboard refreshes, asynchronous reports, schedule reports, and analytics snapshots.

AttachedContentDocument.description: This read-only object contains all ContentDocument objects associated with an object.
AttachedContentDocument.label: Attached Content Document

AttachedContentNote.description: This read-only object contains all ContentNote objects associated with an object.
AttachedContentNote.label: Note

Attachment.description: Represents a file that a User has uploaded and attached to a parent object.
Attachment.label: Attachment

AttachmentEventLog.description: Attachment event logs contain information about attachments.

AttrPicklistExcludedValue.description: Represents the excluded picklist values for a product classification attribute or a product attribute definition.

AttribModel.description: Represents an attribution model used with Personalization, Attribution, and Campaign Influence, including model weights and touch type.
AttribModel.label: Attribution

AttribModelRelatedTypeParmDef.label: Attribution Model Related Type Parameter Definition

AttributeAdjustmentCondition.description: Represents the condition applied to an attribute that determines the price of a product or service being sold.

AttributeBasedAdjRule.description: Represents the attribute conditions in a rule associated with the attribute based adjustment made for a product or service being sold.

AttributeBasedAdjustment.description: Represents the association between the product selling model and the price adjustment for product or service being sold based on its attributes. This object stores information about the attributes that define the price of the product or service, the discounts applied, along with its value for a given date range.

AttributeCategory.description: Represents a logical grouping of attributes that can be reused while defining products. Attribute Categories are used for searching and managing product attributes. For example, the "Mobile Handset Properties" category has color, storage and make model, and size attributes.

AttributeCategoryAttribute.description: Represents a relationship between an attribute category and the attribute definition.

AttributeDefinition.description: Represents a product, asset, or object attribute, for example, a hardware specification or software detail.

AttributePicklist.description: Represents a custom picklist for an asset attribute.
AttributePicklist.label: Attribute Picklist

AttributePicklistValue.description: Represents the values of an asset attribute picklist.
AttributePicklistValue.label: Attribute Picklist Value

Audience.description: Represents an audience that is defined by criteria and can be assigned and used for targeting in an Experience Cloud site.
Audience.label: Audience

Aura Request Event Type.description: Aura Request events contain details of requests to Apex methods from Aura and Lightning web components. For example, you can benchmark request time or identify the URI of an unsuccessful request.

AuraDefinitionBundle.description: Represents a Lightning Aura component definition bundle, such as a component or application bundle. A bundle contains a Lightning Aura component definition and all its related resources.
AuraDefinitionBundle.label: Aura Component Bundle

AuraRequestEventLog.description: Aura Request Event Log contains details of requests to Apex methods from Aura and Lightning web components.

AuthApplicationAsset.description: Information related to the association between an Asset and the Application for the license of an Asset.

AuthApplicationPlace.description: Information related to the association between a location and its application for the license of the location.

AuthConfig.description: Represents authentication options for My Domain and Experience Cloud site login pages.
AuthConfig.label: Authentication Configuration

AuthConfigProviders.description: Represents an authentication provider that’s configured in an organization. AuthConfigProviders is a child of the AuthConfig object.
AuthConfigProviders.label: Authentication Configuration Auth. Provider

AuthFormRequestRecord.description: Junction between an Authorization Request and the Salesforce record that is being authorized. For example. the actual financial Salesforce records shared with third parties or any Salesforce record being shared as a result of the consent request.
AuthFormRequestRecord.label: Authorizable Form Request Record

AuthLocationAccessSchedule.description: Represents the operating hours during a specified period in which authorization is valid for a place.

AuthProvParamFwdAllowlist.description: Represents an allowlisted URL parameter that can be forwarded from authentication provider client configuration URLs to the authorization URL. Use this type to add custom functionality to authentication providers. For example, allowlist a ui_locales parameter and use it to send a user's language preference from Salesforce to the third-party provider's login page.
AuthProvParamFwdAllowlist.label: Auth Provider Param Forwarding Allowlist

AuthProvider.description: Represents an authentication provider (auth provider). An auth provider lets users log in to your Salesforce org from an external service provider, such as Facebook, Google, or GitHub.
AuthProvider.label: Auth. Provider

AuthSession.description: The AuthSession object represents an individual user session in your organization.
AuthSession.label: Auth Session

AuthorizationForm.description: Represents the specific version and effective dates of a form that is associated with consent, such as a privacy policy or terms and conditions.
AuthorizationForm.label: Authorization Form

AuthorizationFormConsent.description: Represents the date and way in which a user consented to an authorization form.
AuthorizationFormConsent.label: Authorization Form Consent

AuthorizationFormDataUse.description: Represents the data use consented to in an authorization form.
AuthorizationFormDataUse.label: Authorization Form Data Use

AuthorizationFormText.description: Represents an authorization form’s text and language settings.
AuthorizationFormText.label: Authorization Form Text

AuthorizedEmailDomain.description: Represents an authorized domain for email verification.
AuthorizedEmailDomain.label: Authorized Email Domain

AuthorizedInsuranceLine.description: Represents the insurance lines that an insurance company is authorized to sell.
AuthorizedInsuranceLine.label: Authorized Insurance Line

AutomatedAction.description: Represents the configuration of an automated action, such as a workflow rule.

AutomatedActionCondition.description: Represents the logical operator details for evaluating conditions in an automated action.

AutomatedActionOverride.description: Represents a modified attribute of a shared automated action. For example, the modified attribute can contain customizations for your business.

AutomatedActionParameter.description: Represents the values or field references evaluated by the automated action.

AutomatedActionReminder.description: Represents a reminder to the end user to take an action in the future.

Automotive Cloud Fields on ApplicationFo.description: Standard fields extend the ApplicationForm object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent high-level information of an application that's submitted for an automotive financial product.
Standard fields extend the ApplicationFormProduct object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent the relationship between an application form product and a deviation.
Standard fields extend the ApplicationFormProductProposal object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent the terms attached to a scheme to sanction an automotive loan or lease.
Standard fields extend the ApplicationFormSellerItem object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent a junction between an application form and an automotive seller product.

Automotive Cloud Fields on Asset.description: Standard fields extend the Asset object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent information about each physical item that’s manufactured, installed, or sold, such as a vehicle, a part like a car engine, or an accessory like car seat covers. Use the VehicleId field on asset to represent an asset as a vehicle.

Automotive Cloud Fields on InternalOrgan.description: Standard fields extend the InternalOrganizationUnit object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent account structures or departments within a company.

Automotive Cloud Fields on Lead.description: Standard fields extend the Lead object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent information about the time frame during which a lead is interested in a transaction.

Automotive Cloud Fields on Product2.description: Standard fields extend the Product2 object for use in Automotive Cloud to represent information about vehicle models, parts, and accessories.

Award.description: Represents a person's or organization's professional awards.
Award.label: Award

BackgroundOperation.description: Represents a background operation in an asynchronous job queue.
BackgroundOperation.label: Background Operation

BackgroundOperationResult.description: Stores error messages generated when or importing data into big objects using Bulk API.

BalanceAdjustmentRequest.description: The request to create a financial adjustment in a backend billing system. Adjustments requests can be for either debit or credit amounts. Often used to give the customer a goodwill gesture.

Banker.description: Represents a business unit member who is assigned the banker role for a branch unit.
Banker.label: Banker

BatchApexErrorEvent.description: The documentation has moved to BatchApexErrorEvent in the Platform Events Developer Guide.
BatchApexErrorEvent.label: Batch Apex Error Platform Event

BatchCalcJobDefinition.description: Represents a Data Processing Engine (DPE) definition.
BatchCalcJobDefinition.label: Batch Calculation Job Definition

BatchCalcJobDefinitionView.description: Represents the details of a Data Processing Engine definition. The definition can also be a file-based definition that is available in your Salesforce org.
BatchCalcJobDefinitionView.label: Batch Calculation Job Definition View

BatchJob.description: Represents an instance of a batch job that is either running and has been run.
BatchJob.label: Batch Job

BatchJobDefinition.description: Represents the definition of a batch job.
BatchJobDefinition.label: Batch Job Definition

BatchJobPart.description: Represents one part of a batch job.
BatchJobPart.label: Batch Job Part

BatchJobPartFailedRecord.description: Represents records that a batch job part couldn't successfully process.
BatchJobPartFailedRecord.label: Batch Job Part Failed Record

BatchJobStatusChangedEvent.description: Notifies subscribers of when a batch job is completed in a flow.
BatchJobStatusChangedEvent.label: Batch Job Status Changed Event

BatchProcessJobDefView.description: Represents the details of a Batch Job definition. The definition can also be file-based definitions that are available in your Salesforce org.
BatchProcessJobDefView.label: Batch Process Job Definition View

BatchProcessJobDefinition.description: Represents the details of a Batch Management job.
BatchProcessJobDefinition.label: Batch Process Job Definition

Benefit.description: Represents information about benefits associated with a program.
Benefit.label: Benefit

BenefitAction.description: Represents details of an action that can be triggered for a benefit.
BenefitAction.label: Benefit Action

BenefitAssignment.description: Represents the enrollment information of an individual or business that is captured in an application. For example, an individual who is unemployed can raise an application requesting help from the government. If it is approved, the individual is enrolled into the unemployment insurance benefit.
BenefitAssignment.label: Benefit Assignment

BenefitAssignmentAdjustment.description: Represents a monetary or non-monetary benefit adjustment made to an enrollee that can be disbursed in various frequencies.

BenefitAssignmentAsset.description: Represents a junction between an asset and a benefit assignment.
BenefitAssignmentAsset.label: Benefit Assignment Asset

BenefitDisbursement.description: Represents the allocation of an enrollee's benefit that can be made as monetary or non-monetary with different frequencies.
BenefitDisbursement.label: Benefit Disbursement

BenefitDisbursementAdj.description: Represents the changes of an enrollee's benefit that can be made as monetary or non-monetary with similar units of measure.

BenefitItemCode.description: Represents information about a code set or a code set bundle that identifies an item that is associated with a benefit.

BenefitParameterValue.description: Represents the runtime value of a parameter that's used when executing a flow for benefit action.
BenefitParameterValue.label: Benefit Parameter Value

BenefitPrvdSearchableFld.description: Represents a collection of denormalized data from certain fields in the Provider Management data model. Provider search queries this object instead of multiple objects, which improves search performance.

BenefitSchedule.description: Represents information about the plan for delivering the benefit.

BenefitSession.description: Represents information about an instance of a planned benefit delivery

BenefitSpecialty.description: Represents a junction between a benefit and a care specialty. The object maps the benefits provided to constituents with the specialties offered by the network of service providers.

BenefitType.description: Represents information about the type of benefits that can be applied to an individual or a group.
BenefitType.label: Benefit Type

BillingAccount.description: Represents the customer's billing controls in the backend system. Used to set up and maintain details such as bill frequency, bill format, and autopay details.
BillingAccount.label: Billing Account

BillingAccountContact.description: Represents a junction between Billing Account objects and Contact objects.

BillingBatchFilterCriteria.description: Represents the filter that all eligible billing schedules must satisfy in order to be picked up by an invoice run.

BillingBatchScheduler.description: Represents a scheduled processing job that triggers recurring invoice batch runs.

BillingMilestonePlan.description: Represents a structured approach to invoicing where invoices are scheduled based on predefined milestones.

BillingMilestonePlanItem.description: Represents a specific billing milestone within the billing milestone plan that’s used to manage and track billing based on the completion of certain deliverables or stages.

BillingPeriodItem.description: Represents a payment period for an invoice. The billing period item is used to pass billing information to an invoice line.

BillingPolicy.description: Represents information about a set of billing treatments that define the rules to invoice a customer for an order item.

BillingScheduleGroup.description: Represents a consolidated view of all the billing schedules related to the order items generated from one asset, including new orders and amendment orders.

BillingTreatment.description: Represents information about the billing of an order item.

BillingTreatmentItem.description: Represents information about allocation of the total amount of an order item to billing schedules throughout the order item's lifecycle.

BindingObjUsageRsrcPlcy.description: Represents the policies that are used for the usage resource that's associated with an asset or a binding object.

BindingObjectCustomExt.description: Represents the external or custom target object that's bound to the entitlements granted with the sellable product.

BindingObjectRateAdjustment.description: Represents the rate adjustments of the usage resource associated with the binding object that's used to charge over consumption.

BindingObjectRateCardEntry.description: Represents the rate card entry details of the usage resource associated with the binding object that's used to charge over consumption.

BiodiversitySummary.description: Represents the biodiversity information that a company discloses as part of ESRS E4 - Biodiversity and ecosystems.
BiodiversitySummary.label: Biodiversity Summary

BldgEnrgyIntensity.description: Represents the average energy intensity by fuel type across a set of buildings. You can derive this data from published sources. Alternatively, you can do so by using energy use records as the data source and then setting up a window of time with some characteristics of the building size and type.
BldgEnrgyIntensity.label: Building Energy Intensity

BldgEnrgyIntensityCnfg.description: Represents the setup object that contains the mapping between the Building Energy Intensity Record record type and internal enums. You can primarily use this object for calculations across different record types.
BldgEnrgyIntensityCnfg.label: Building Energy Intensity Record Type Config

BldgEnrgyIntensityVal.description: Represents the calculated average energy intensity for an individual fuel type across a set of buildings. Each record stores the fuel use intensity as a function of the floor area of the occupied space of that building.
BldgEnrgyIntensityVal.label: Building Energy Intensity Value

BldgSizeCategory.description: Represents the building size filter criteria for the building energy intensity records. The building size filter criteria are stored as a range of floor area sizes from a minimum size to a maximum size, in units of sqft or m². The records can have overlapping minimum-maximum ranges.
BldgSizeCategory.label: Building Size Category

Blocked Redirect Event Type.description: Blocked redirect events capture information about blocked redirections from Salesforce to untrusted and malformed URLs.

BlockedRedirectEventLog.description: Blocked Redirect events capture information about blocked redirections from Salesforce to untrusted and malformed URLs.

BoardCertification.description: Represents the practitioner's board certifications such as being board-certified in cardiology and cardiovascular disease.
BoardCertification.label: Board Certification

Bookmark.description: Represents a link between opportunities that share common information.
Bookmark.label: Bookmark

BotDefinition.description: Represents a top level object for Einstein Bots or Agentforce Agents.
BotDefinition.label: Bot

BotVersion.description: Represents a version of a bot or agent defined by a BotDefinition record.
BotVersion.label: Bot Version

BranchUnit.description: Represents details about a branch of an organization.
BranchUnit.label: Branch Unit

BranchUnitBusinessMember.description: Represents a user or contact who can perform a specific role for a branch.
BranchUnitBusinessMember.label: Branch Unit Business Member

BranchUnitCustomer.description: Represents a customer account that is assigned to or attributed to a branch unit.
BranchUnitCustomer.label: Branch Unit Customer

BranchUnitRelatedRecord.description: Represents a record such as a case or account that is associated with or attributed to a branch unit.
BranchUnitRelatedRecord.label: Branch Unit Related Record

BrandingSet.description: Represents a set of branding properties for an Experience Builder site, as defined in the Theme panel in Experience Builder.
BrandingSet.label: Branding Set

BrandingSetProperty.description: Represents a branding set property in the Theme panel in Experience Builder.
BrandingSetProperty.label: Branding Set Property

Brief.description: Represents a marketing brief. A brief contains information that’s used for positioning and grounding a marketing campaign.

BriefcaseAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a briefcase definition to selected users and user groups.
BriefcaseAssignment.label: Briefcase Assignment

BriefcaseDefinition.description: Represents a briefcase definition. A briefcase makes selected records available for users and groups to view when they’re offline in the Salesforce Field Service mobile app for iOS and Android.
BriefcaseDefinition.label: Briefcase Definition

BriefcaseRule.description: Represents a rule that specifies records for a briefcase definition.
BriefcaseRule.label: Briefcase Rule

BriefcaseRuleFilter.description: Represents a filter criteria for a briefcase rule.
BriefcaseRuleFilter.label: Briefcase Rule Filter

BroadcastCommAudience.description: Represents the audience that the broadcast communication is sent to.
BroadcastCommAudience.label: Broadcast Communication Audience

BroadcastCommunication.description: Represents a broadcast communication related to an incident.
BroadcastCommunication.label: Broadcast Communication

BroadcastTopic.description: Represents a definition of a broadcast topic. A broadcast topic is associated with a list of Experience Cloud network sites for Service Cloud and collaboration rooms for Sales Cloud.
BroadcastTopic.label: Broadcast Topic

BroadcastTopicGroup.description: Represents a junction object that relates a group to an alert type broadcast topic. The broadcast sends the alert to this group.
BroadcastTopicGroup.label: Broadcast Topic Group

BroadcastTopicNetwork.description: Represents a link between a broadcast topic and the Experience Cloud network site for Service Cloud.

BrowserPolicyViolation.description: Represents a violation that occurred within the last seven days related to the Trusted URLs and Trusted URLs for External Redirects allowlists. These violations include blocked resource requests based on your content security policy (CSP) and blocked redirections.
BrowserPolicyViolation.label: Browser Policy Violation

BsgRelationship.description: Represents a relationship between billing schedule groups to support bundles where one parent billing schedule group has multiple child billing schedule groups.

Budget.description: Tracks an estimate of future revenue or expenses during a specific time period.

BudgetAllocation.description: Represents a subsection of a Budget that shows where allocated resources are being applied.

BudgetCategory.description: Represents the purpose of the budget line item.

BudgetCategoryValue.description: Captures budget values for category and time period.

BudgetParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a budget.

BudgetPeriod.description: Defines a distinct time interval in which the estimate applies.

Bulk API Event Type.description: Bulk API events contain details about Bulk API requests.

Bulk API Request Event Type.description: The Bulk API request event captures when Bulk API requests are received to create a job, update a job, create a batch, update a batch, and when a job completes.

BulkApi2EventLog.description: Bulk API 2 event logs contain details about Bulk API 2.0 requests.

BulkApiEventLog.description: Bulk API event logs contain details about Bulk API requests.

BulkApiRequestEventLog.description: The Bulk API request event captures when Bulk API requests are received to create a job, update a job, create a batch, update a batch, and when a job completes.

BundleBasedAdjustment.description: Represents the association between the product selling model and the price adjustment for a product or service being sold as a bundle. This object stores information of the product or service's price, the discounts applied, along with its value for a given date range.

BundledCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Bundled Care Fee Agreement.
BundledCareFeeAgreement.label: Bundled Care Fee Agreement

BusProcessFeedbackConfig.description: Represents information about the configuration for feedback collection. The feedback collection method triggers against pre-determined conditions on object to gather feedback.
BusProcessFeedbackConfig.label: Business Process Feedback Configuration

BusRegAuthTypeDependency.description: Information related to the association of permit to permit dependency in a given business context.

BusRegAuthorizationType.description: Represents the association between authorization activity and license or permit type.

Business Process.description: Represents a business process. Business Processes track separate sales, lead, support, and solution lifecycles by displaying different picklist values according to each user’s profile.

BusinessAlertStatus.description: Represents information about the read status of an insight alert.

BusinessBrand.description: Represents a unique brand for a business that belongs to a parent entity.
BusinessBrand.label: Business Brand

BusinessHours.description: Specifies the business hours of your support organization. Escalation rules are run only during these hours.
BusinessHours.label: Business Hours

BusinessLicense.description: Represents the licenses of a party role like healthcare provider or producer.
BusinessLicense.label: Business License

BusinessLicenseApplication.description: Represents an application form submitted by a business owner. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.

BusinessMilestone.description: Represents the milestones of a business, such as acquisition, market listing, and expansion.
BusinessMilestone.label: Business Milestone

BusinessProcessDefinition.description: Represents information about stages in a customer lifecycle map.
BusinessProcessDefinition.label: Business Process Definition

BusinessProcessFeedback.description: Represents information about the survey and the question associated with each stage in a customer lifecycle map.
BusinessProcessFeedback.label: Business Process Feedback

BusinessProcessGroup.description: Represents information about the customer lifecycle maps. Customer lifecycle maps are used to track the scores provided by customers across their lifecycle using Salesforce Surveys. For example, the lifecycle stages for an Insurance business process group can include acquisition, onboarding, claims, routine services, and renewal.
BusinessProcessGroup.label: Business Process Group

BusinessProcessTypeDef.description: Represents a type of business process within an application domain.
BusinessProcessTypeDef.label: Business Process Type Definition

BusinessProfile.description: Represents the insurance-related attributes for the insured business.
BusinessProfile.label: Business Profile

BusinessType.description: Represents a category of any activity (business or individual), such as healthcare, restaurant, or retail. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.

BuyerAccount.description: Represents an account that is enabled as a buyer for Lightning B2B Commerce.
BuyerAccount.label: Buyer Account

BuyerCriteria.description: Represents the buyer context qualifier of locale for any buyer groups of type Market
BuyerCriteria.label: Buyer Criteria

BuyerGroup.description: Associates group qualifiers (entitlements, price books, promotions, and shipping methods) with buyer members based on buyer account ID or on the localized language and currency of the market browsed in a webstore.
BuyerGroup.label: Buyer Group

BuyerGroupBuyerCriteria.description: Associates a buyer group that is enabled for webstores supporting multiple languages and currencies with BuyerCriteria that define those languages and currencies.
BuyerGroupBuyerCriteria.label: Buyer Group Buyer Criteria

BuyerGroupMember.description: Represents a member of a buyer group.
BuyerGroupMember.label: Buyer Group Member

BuyerGroupPricebook.description: Represents a buyer group price book used in Lightning B2B Commerce.
BuyerGroupPricebook.label: Buyer Group Price Book
