BuyerGroupRelatedObject.description: Used to associate currencies and supported ship-to countries with a buyer group and its price books, promotions, and entitlements. Supports buyer experience when buyer group members shop in stores enabled for multiple locales.
BuyerGroupRelatedObject.label: Buyer Group Related Object

CSP Violation Event Type.description: CSP violation events capture details about blocked resource requests from Lightning Experience pages based on your content security policy (CSP).

CalcMatrixColumnRange.description: Represents information about a value in a decision matrix column when the column is of the type number range or text range.
CalcMatrixColumnRange.label: Decision Matrix Column Range

CalcProcStepRelationship.description: Defines a parent-child relationship between two Expression Set Steps in an Expression Set Version. The label for this object is Expression Set Step Relationship.
CalcProcStepRelationship.label: Expression Set Step Relationship

CalculatedInsightRangeBound.description: Stores the information required to calculate a range-bound data insight.
CalculatedInsightRangeBound.label: Calculated Insight Range Bound

CalculationMatrix.description: Matches input values to a table row and returns the row's output values. The label for this object is Decision Matrix.
CalculationMatrix.label: Decision Matrix

CalculationMatrixColumn.description: Defines a column in a Decision Matrix. The label for this object is Decision Matrix Column.
CalculationMatrixColumn.label: Decision Matrix Column

CalculationMatrixRow.description: Defines a row in a Decision Matrix. The label for this object is Decision Matrix Row.
CalculationMatrixRow.label: Decision Matrix Row

CalculationMatrixVersion.description: Defines a version of a Decision Matrix. The label for this object is Decision Matrix Version.
CalculationMatrixVersion.label: Decision Matrix Version

CalculationProcedure.description: Performs a series of calculations using matrix lookups and user-defined variables and constants. The label for this object is Expression Set.
CalculationProcedure.label: Calculation Procedure

CalculationProcedureStep.description: Defines a step in an Expression Set. The label for this object is Expression Set Step.
CalculationProcedureStep.label: Calculation Procedure Step

CalculationProcedureVariable.description: Defines a variable in an Expression Set. The label for this object is Expression Set Variable.
CalculationProcedureVariable.label: Calculation Procedure Variable

CalculationProcedureVersion.description: Defines a version of an Expression Set. The label for this object is Expression Set Version.
CalculationProcedureVersion.label: Calculation Procedure Version

Calendar.description: Represents a calendar. This can be a default user calendar, public calendar, resource calendar, or holiday calendar.
Calendar.label: Calendar

CalendarView.description: These calendars can be created and assigned to users other than the creator. Available calendars include object, shared, public, resource, and user list calendars. Object calendars represent a calendar based on a Salesforce object, either standard or custom.
CalendarView.label: Calendar

CallCenter.description: Represents a call center, which is a logical representation of a single computer-telephony integration (CTI) system instance in an organization.
CallCenter.label: Call Center

CallCenterRoutingMap.description: Stores a mapping between a user or queue in a Salesforce org to a user or queue in an external system’s call center.
CallCenterRoutingMap.label: Call Center Routing Map

CallCoachingMediaProvider.description: Represents the media provider for call recordings.
CallCoachingMediaProvider.label: CallCoachingMediaProvider

CallCtrAgentFavTrfrDest.description: Represents a transfer destination that has been marked (starred) as a favorite in the Omni-Channel softphone by a contact center agent for voice call transfers.
CallCtrAgentFavTrfrDest.label: Call Center Agent Favorite Transfer Destination

CallCtrAgentFavTrfrDestShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a favorite transfer destination in the Omni-Channel softphone for voice call transfers. This object is available in API version 55.0 and later.
CallCtrAgentFavTrfrDestShare.label: Call Center Agent Favorite Transfer Destination Share

CallDisposition.description: Represents a call result value that sales reps select when logging a call.

CallDispositionCategory.description: Represents the call outcome of a phone call that is used in reports and branching criteria for cadences.

CallTemplate.description: Represents a call script for users to read when making calls.

Campaign.description: Represents and tracks a marketing campaign, such as a direct mail promotion, webinar, or trade show.
Campaign.label: Campaign

CampaignInfluence.description: Represents the association between a campaign and an opportunity in Customizable Campaign Influence.
CampaignInfluence.label: Campaign Influence

CampaignInfluenceModel.description: This read-only object represents a campaign influence model in Customizable Campaign Influence. Use campaign influence models to group CampaignInfluence records created by a specific set of triggers and workflows that you define. The Primary Campaign Source influence model is the default model.
CampaignInfluenceModel.label: Campaign Influence Model

CampaignMember.description: The CampaignMember object represents the relationship between a campaign and either a lead or a contact. If the Accounts as Campaign Members setting is enabled in an org, CampaignMember can also represent the relationship between a campaign and an account.
CampaignMember.label: Campaign Member

CampaignMemberStatus.description: One or more member status values defined for a campaign.
CampaignMemberStatus.label: Campaign Member Status

CampaignOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a campaign with User records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
CampaignOwnerSharingRule.label: Campaign Owner Rule

CampaignShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a Campaign.
CampaignShare.label: Campaign Share

CampaignTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Campaign.

CapitationCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Capitation Care Fee Agreement type.
CapitationCareFeeAgreement.label: Capitation Care Fee Agreement

CardPaymentMethod.description: Represents a credit card or debit card payment method, which implements the PaymentMethod object.
CardPaymentMethod.label: Card Payment Method

CareBarrier.description: Represents the circumstances or obstacles affecting a patient or member.
CareBarrier.label: Care Barrier

CareBarrierDeterminant.description: Represents the relationship of a barrier to a determinant for a patient or member.
CareBarrierDeterminant.label: Care Barrier Determinant

CareBarrierType.description: Represents the standard, defined list of barriers maintained by an organization.
CareBarrierType.label: Care Barrier Type

CareBenefitVerifySettings.description: Configuration settings for benefit verification requests.
CareBenefitVerifySettings.label: Care Benefit Verification Settings

CareDeterminant.description: Represents the determinants of health for a patient such as availability of safe housing, adequate employment, or local food markets.
CareDeterminant.label: Care Determinant

CareDeterminantType.description: Represents the standard, defined list of determinants of health maintained by an organization, including the domain and type.
CareDeterminantType.label: Care Determinant Type

CareDiagnosis.description: Represents the details of a diagnosis including code type, name, and description. One or more care diagnoses can be associated with a care request.
CareDiagnosis.label: Care Diagnosis

CareEpisode.description: Records details of the interaction between a patient and a healthcare provider for the period during which the patient receives healthcare services from the provide. This object is based on the EpisodeOfCare FHIR resource.

CareEpisodeDetail.description: Represents additional information associated with a CareEpisode record.

CareFacilityBed.description: Represents information related to different bed types at a facility with associated care programs and products. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.

CareFeeScheduleItem.description: Stores procedure level fees for a fee schedule definition.
CareFeeScheduleItem.label: Care Fee Schedule Item

CareGap.description: Represents gaps in patient care through a specified period. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

CareGapCriteriaResult.description: Represents the result of an evaluated clinical measure criteria. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

CareInterventionType.description: Represents the standard, defined list of interventions maintained by an organization.
CareInterventionType.label: Care Intervention Type

CareLimitType.description: Defines the characteristics of limits on benefit provision.
CareLimitType.label: Care Limit Type

CareMetricTarget.description: Represents the expected care metrics at an org level and patient level.
CareMetricTarget.label: Care Metric Target

CareObservation.description: Represents the observed values for care metrics originating from external systems that contain biometric data
CareObservation.label: Care Observation

CarePgmEnrolleeWkOrdStep.description: Represents information about the step in a work order that's executed for the care program enrollee.

CarePgmEnrolleeWorkOrder.description: Represents information about the work order that's executed for the care program enrollee.

CarePgmProvHealthcareProvider.description: Represents a junction object identifying the primary healthcare professional associated with a care program provider and to look up all healthcare professionals for care program providers.
CarePgmProvHealthcareProvider.label: Care Program Healthcare Provider

CarePlan.description: Represents an instantiation of a care plan template for a particular individual in order to reach specific goals.

CarePlanActivity.description: Represents a planned action that’s part of a care plan. For example, knowledge campaigns, physiotherapy appointments, medication regimens, etc.
CarePlanActivity.label: Care Plan Activity

CarePlanActivityDetail.description: Represents additional information associated with a CarePlanActivity record.
CarePlanActivityDetail.label: Care Plan Activity Detail

CarePlanDetail.description: Represents additional information associated with a care plan record.
CarePlanDetail.label: Care Plan Detail

CarePlanTemplate.description: Represents the template for a type of care plan that can be offered for a household scenario.

CarePlanTemplateBenefit.description: Represents a junction between a care plan template and a benefit. This object stores the benefit details of a care plan.

CarePlanTemplateGoal.description: Represents a junction between a care plan template and a goal definition. This object stores the goal details of a care plan template.

CarePlanTemplateProblem.description: Represents problems in Care Plan Templates. These problems may or may not have goals as their direct children.

CarePreauth.description: Represents the details of preauthorizations for care under a member’s plan.
CarePreauth.label: Care Preauth

CarePreauthItem.description: Represents the details of items included in a preauthorization for care under a member’s plan.
CarePreauthItem.label: Care Preauth Item

CareProcessingError.description: Stores information on processing errors sent from payer to provider on a member’s authorization request.
CareProcessingError.label: Care Processing Error

CareProgram.description: Represents a set of activities, such as a patient therapy, financial assistance, education, wellness, or fitness plan, offered to participants by an employer or insurer.
CareProgram.label: Care Program

CareProgramAssistance.description: Represents a junction between Care Program and Program objects.

CareProgramCampaign.description: Represents a relationship between the Care Program object and the Campaign object.
CareProgramCampaign.label: Care Program Campaign

CareProgramEligibilityRule.description: Represents a rule defining the criteria for patient care program enrollment eligibility. This entity creates an association between Care Program and an Enrollment Eligibility Criteria.
CareProgramEligibilityRule.label: Care Program Eligibility Rule

CareProgramEnrollee.description: Represents a participant enrolled in a care program.
CareProgramEnrollee.label: Care Program Enrollee

CareProgramEnrolleeProduct.description: Represents the affiliation between a care program enrollee and a care program product, a care program provider, or both.
CareProgramEnrolleeProduct.label: Care Program Enrollee Product

CareProgramEnrollmentCard.description: Represents a care program membership card that includes a membership number or enrollment code.
CareProgramEnrollmentCard.label: Care Program Enrollment Card

CareProgramGoal.description: Represents a business or clinical goal related to a care program.
CareProgramGoal.label: Care Program Goal

CareProgramProduct.description: Represents the affiliation between a care program and a care program product, care program provider, or both.
CareProgramProduct.label: Care Program Product

CareProgramProvider.description: Represents a business account that is the service provider for a care program product.
CareProgramProvider.label: Care Program Provider

CareProgramTeamMember.description: Represents a person who delivers services under a program, such as a program manager or care coordinator.
CareProgramTeamMember.label: Care Program Team Member

CareProviderAdverseAction.description: Captures adverse actions against the provider, such as malpractice lawsuits or revoked licences.
CareProviderAdverseAction.label: Care Provider Adverse Action

CareProviderAfflRoleConfig.description: Represents information about the affiliations of the healthcare provider.
CareProviderAfflRoleConfig.label: Care Provider Affiliation Role Config

CareProviderFacilitySpecialty.description: Represents all the specialties that the practitioner provides at a given location. For example, a physician who is board-certified in both spine and neuro may provide spine services at one location and neuro services at another.
CareProviderFacilitySpecialty.label: Care Provider Facility Specialty

CareProviderSearchConfig.description: Represents fields that can appear in provider search results. Use this object to specify fields in arbitrary objects (source) that are made available in the search object (target).
CareProviderSearchConfig.label: Care Provider Search Config

CareProviderSearchableField.description: This object holds denormalized data from certain fields in the Provider Relationship Management data model.
CareProviderSearchableField.label: Care Provider Searchable Field

CareRegisteredDevice.description: Represents a device or device registration information for a patient or a care program enrollee.
CareRegisteredDevice.label: Care Registered Device

CareRequest.description: Represents the general details of a care-related request including member information, admission date, decision reason, and so on. A single request can contain multiple diagnoses, services, or drugs. Care requests include preauthorizations for drugs and services, admission notifications, concurrent review of admissions, appeals, complaints, and grievances.
CareRequest.label: Care Request

CareRequestConfiguration.description: Represents the details for a record type such as service request, drug request, or admission request. One or more record types can be associated with a care request.
CareRequestConfiguration.label: Care Request Configuration

CareRequestDrug.description: Represents the details of a requested drug including name, strength, frequency, and instructions for administration. One or more drug requests can be associated with a care request.
CareRequestDrug.label: Care Request Drug

CareRequestExchangeInfo.description: Represents information about a care request exchange.
CareRequestExchangeInfo.label: Care Request Exchange Information

CareRequestExtension.description: Represents extra details for a care request such as the subscriber details for the member's health plan, home healthcare status, and ambulance transportation details.
CareRequestExtension.label: Care Request Extension

CareRequestItem.description: Represents the details of a care service request, including name, modifiers, and the effective date. One or more care service requests can be associated with a care request.
CareRequestItem.label: Care Request Item

CareRequestReviewer.description: Represents the details of a care request reviewer including name, reviewer type, status of the care request at the end of the review, the reviewer’s notes, and date of review. A care request, care request item, care request drug, or care diagnosis can be associated with a care request reviewer.
CareRequestReviewer.label: Care Request Reviewer

CareRequestSupportingCntnt.description: Represents details about supporting content of a care request such as assessments or content documents.
CareRequestSupportingCntnt.label: Care Request Supporting Content

CareService.description: Represents a healthcare treatment, service, or procedure offered by a provider, practitioner, or facility.
CareService.label: Care Service

CareServiceVisit.description: Associates a service request or a referral request (ClinicalServiceRequest) with a visit (ServiceAppointment) that’s part of that service or referral.

CareServiceVisitPlan.description: Associates a service request with the series of visits that are planned as part of that visit. The series of visits is represented using MaintenancePlan.

CareSpecialty.description: Represents a listing of provider specialty codes and descriptions. For example, 02 - Physician/General Surgery.
CareSpecialty.label: Care Specialty

CareSpecialtyTaxonomy.description: The junction object between CareSpecialty and CareTaxonomy.
CareSpecialtyTaxonomy.label: Care Specialty Taxonomy

CareSystemFieldMapping.description: Represents a mapping from fields in external source systems to Salesforce target entities and attributes

CareTask.description: Represents additional information about a healthcare-related task such as process status, beneficiary, and related tasks.
CareTask.label: Care Task

CareTaskDetail.description: Represents extra details about a healthcare-related task such as the detail type, detail record, detail code, and detail value.
CareTaskDetail.label: Care Task Detail

CareTaxonomy.description: Represents a static list of taxonomy codes.
CareTaxonomy.label: Care Taxonomy

CartCheckoutSession.description: Represents a checkout session used in Lightning B2B Commerce checkout.
CartCheckoutSession.label: Cart Checkout Session

CartDeliveryGroup.description: Represents shipping information for the delivery of items in an order against a store built with B2B Commerce or D2C Commerce.
CartDeliveryGroup.label: Cart Delivery Group

CartDeliveryGroupMethod.description: Represents the selected delivery method for a cart delivery group used in Lightning B2B Commerce checkout.
CartDeliveryGroupMethod.label: Cart Delivery Group Method

CartDeliveryGroupMethodAdj.description: Represents the shipping promotion discount for a shipping method.
CartDeliveryGroupMethodAdj.label: Cart Delivery Group Method Adjustment

CartItem.description: Represents an item in a WebCart that’s active in a store built with B2B or D2C Commerce. Cart item can be of type Product or Charge.
CartItem.label: Cart Item

CartItemPriceAdjustment.description: Price adjustment for a cart item.
CartItemPriceAdjustment.label: Cart Item Price Adjustment

CartTax.description: Represents taxes for a line item in a WebCart that’s active in a store built with B2B Commerce or D2C Commerce.
CartTax.label: Cart Tax

CartValidationOutput.description: Associate errors to cart entities, such as cart line items, delivery groups, and the like, in a store built with B2B Commerce or D2C Commerce. An example error is “Out of stock.”
CartValidationOutput.label: Cart Validation Output

Case.description: Represents a case, which is a customer issue or problem.
Case.label: Case

CaseArticle.description: Represents the association between a Case and a KnowledgeArticle.
CaseArticle.label: Case Article

CaseComment.description: Represents a comment that provides additional information about the associated Case.
CaseComment.label: Case Comment

CaseContactRole.description: Represents the role that a given Contact plays on a Case.
CaseContactRole.label: Case Contact Role

CaseEpisode.description: Represents the episode linked to a case or a case proceeding result, where a business or person or license is the subject.

CaseGatewayRequest.description: Holds the JSON output from the Financial Services Cloud flows and serves as an endpoint for integration with backend systems. It records the data interchange between the integrated systems.
CaseGatewayRequest.label: Case Gateway Request

CaseHistory.description: Represents historical information about changes that have been made to the associated Case.
CaseHistory.label: Case History

CaseHistory2.description: Represents historical information about owner and status changes that have been made to the associated Case.
CaseHistory2.label: Case History

CaseMilestone.description: Represents a milestone (required step in a customer support process) on a Case.
CaseMilestone.label: Case Milestone

CaseOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a case with users other than the owner.
CaseOwnerSharingRule.label: Case Owner Rule

CaseParticipant.description: Represents a junction between a case, and an account or a contact. This object stores the details of the participant associated with a case. This participant could be the applicant, co-applicant, a household, or even a business account.
CaseParticipant.label: Case Participant

CaseProceeding.description: Represents a legal and formal demand for the enforcement of an individual’s rights against another party in a court of justice.

CaseProceedingComplaint.description: Represents the association between a complaint and its corresponding case proceeding.

CaseProceedingInfraction.description: Represents the association between an infraction and its corresponding case proceeding.

CaseProceedingParticipant.description: Represents a junction between the case proceeding and a participant, such as an account or a contact. This object stores the details of a participant who is involved in a case proceeding.

CaseProceedingResult.description: Represents the outcome of a legal case for a participant.

CaseProgram.description: Represents the junction between Case and Program objects.

CaseRelatedFile.description: Represents the details of a file attached to a case, such as file properties, file processing details, and other additional relevant information.

CaseRelatedIssue.description: This object acts as a junction between a customer issue (Case) and the Incident or Problem that represents an associated service failure.
CaseRelatedIssue.label: Case Related Issue

CaseRelatedSubject.description: Represents a junction between a case and an object impacted by the case.

CaseShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a Case.
CaseShare.label: Case Share

CaseSolution.description: Represents the association between a Case and a Solution.
CaseSolution.label: Case Solution

CaseStatus.description: Represents the status of a Case, such as New, On Hold, or In Process.
CaseStatus.label: Case Status Value

CaseSubjectParticle.description: Represents the Social Business Rules custom format for the Case Subject field on cases created from inbound social posts.
CaseSubjectParticle.label: Case Subject Particle

CaseTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Case

CaseTeamMember.description: Represents a case team member, who works with a team of other users to help resolve a case.
CaseTeamMember.label: Case Team Member

CaseTeamMemberProgram.description: Represents mapping information between Case Team Member and Program.

CaseTeamRole.description: Represents a case team role. Every case team member has a role on a case, such as “Customer Contact” or “Case Manager.”
CaseTeamRole.label: Case Team Member Role

CaseTeamTemplate.description: Represents a predefined case team, which is a group of users that helps resolve a case.
CaseTeamTemplate.label: Predefined Case Team

CaseTeamTemplateMember.description: Represents a member on a predefined case team, which is a group of users that helps resolve cases.
CaseTeamTemplateMember.label: Predefined Case Team Member

CaseTeamTemplateRecord.description: The CaseTeamTemplateRecord object is a linking object between the Case and CaseTeamTemplate objects. To assign a predefined case team to a case (customer inquiry), create a CaseTeamTemplateRecord record and point the ParentId to the case and the TeamTemplateId to the predefined case team.
CaseTeamTemplateRecord.label: Predefined Case Team Record

CategorizedCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Categorized Care Fee Agreement.
CategorizedCareFeeAgreement.label: Categorized Care Fee Agreement

CategoryData.description: Represents a logical grouping of Solution records.
CategoryData.label: Category Data

CategoryNode.description: Represents a tree of Solution categories.
CategoryNode.label: Category Node

CategoryNodeLocalization.description: When the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization, the CategoryNodeLocalization object provides the translation of the label of a solution category.
CategoryNodeLocalization.label: Category Node Localization

Change Set Operation Event Type.description: Change Set Operation events contain information from change set migrations.

ChangeRequest.description: Represents a decision to implement a formal request for a change (RFC).
ChangeRequest.label: Change Request

ChangeRequestRelatedIssue.description: Represents a junction object that relates a ChangeRequest to an Incident or Problem due to a service failure.
ChangeRequestRelatedIssue.label: Change Request Related Issue

ChangeRequestRelatedItem.description: Represents a junction object that relates a ChangeRequest to an Asset.
ChangeRequestRelatedItem.label: Change Request Related Item

ChangeSetOperationEventLog.description: Change Set Operation events contain information from change set migrations.

ChannelObjectLinkingRule.description: Represents a rule for linking a channel interaction with an object (such as Lead or Contact).

ChannelProgram.description: Represents a channel program that vendors use to market and sell their products through channel partners.
ChannelProgram.label: Channel Program

ChannelProgramLevel.description: Represents a level, based on member experience, in a channel program.
ChannelProgramLevel.label: Channel Program Level

ChannelProgramMember.description: Represents a partner who is a member of a channel program.
ChannelProgramMember.label: Channel Program Member

ChatterActivity.description: ChatterActivity represents the number of posts and comments made by a user and the number of comments and likes on posts and comments received by the same user.
ChatterActivity.label: Chatter Activity

ChatterAnswersActivity.description: Represents the reputation of a User in Chatter Answers zones.

ChatterAnswersReputationLevel.description: Represents a reputation level within a Chatter Answers zone.

ChatterConversation.description: Represents a private conversation in Chatter, consisting of messages that conversation members have sent or received.

ChatterConversationMember.description: Represents a member of a private conversation in Chatter. A member has either sent messages to or received messages from other conversation participants.

ChatterExtension.description: Represents a Rich Publisher App that’s integrated with the Chatter publisher.
ChatterExtension.label: Extension

ChatterExtensionConfig.description: Configuration for the Chatter extension for Experience Cloud sites.
ChatterExtensionConfig.label: Chatter Extension Configuration

ChatterMessage.description: Represents a message sent as part of a private conversation in Chatter.

Claim.description: Represents a warranty Claim submitted by a partner to a manufacturer, or a supplier recovery claim submitted by the manufacturer to a supplier.
Claim.label: Claim

Claim Case.description: A junction object that associates the Claim object with the Case object. You see this object only if you have enabled the Use Many-to-Many Relationships org pref.

ClaimCovPaymentAdjustment.description: Represents the amount increased or decreased on a claim coverage payment as adjustments such as deductibles, copays, or coinsurance when applied on a claimed amount.

ClaimCovReserveAdjustment.description: Represents the amount adjusted on a claim coverage reserve as the reserve is changed and payments are made.

ClaimCoverage.description: Represents a causal part in a defective asset that requires repair or replacement.
ClaimCoverage.label: Claim Coverage

ClaimCoveragePaymentDetail.description: Represents the claim coverage amount that must be paid to a claimant for a part replaced or replaced or a labor service performed to rectify a causal part in a defective asset.
ClaimCoveragePaymentDetail.label: Claim Coverage Payment Detail

ClaimCoverageProdtProcDef.description: Represents the definition for custom configurations that's used for processing claim coverage payment details.

ClaimFinancialSettings.description: Represents the configuration settings for Insurance Claim Financial Services.
ClaimFinancialSettings.label: Claim Financial Settings

ClaimItem.description: Represents a defective asset that requires repair or replacement.
ClaimItem.label: Claim Item

ClaimItemAttribute.description: Represents attributes for a claim item.
ClaimItemAttribute.label: Claim Item Attribute

ClaimItemRelatedObject.description: Represents the relationship between a claim item and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on the claim item.
ClaimItemRelatedObject.label: Claim Item Related Object

ClaimParticipant.description: A junction object that associates the Claim object with the Account object. This object represents the participants of a claim.
ClaimParticipant.label: Claim Participant

ClaimPaymentSummary.description: Represents the amount of money that's paid to a claimant or claim participant to cover a claim.
ClaimPaymentSummary.label: Claim Payment Summary

ClaimPayoutPlan.description: Represents the payout plan details for a claim, such as payment frequency, duration, and payouts.

ClaimRecovery.description: Represents a recovery of funds on an insurance claim through subrogation and salvage activities. Recovered amounts can come from a salvage company or through legal litigation or arbitration. Master-detail child object of Claim.

ClaimTeamMember.description: Represents a user who is a part of the claim team.
ClaimTeamMember.label: Claim Team Member

ClauseCatgConfiguration.description: Represents the configuration about the clause category that can be used in a response document by the user.
ClauseCatgConfiguration.label: Clause Category Configuration

CleanDataService.description: Represents a data service that adds and updates data in existing records in an org.
CleanDataService.label: Data Service

CleanEnergyProject.description: Represents information about a project that provides credits a company can purchase to claim clean energy usage.
CleanEnergyProject.label: Clean Energy Project

CleanRule.description: Represents a data integration rule that controls how a data service adds and updates data for existing records in an org.
CleanRule.label: Data Integration Rule

ClientBrowser.description: Represents a cookie added to the browser upon login, and also includes information about the browser application where the cookie was inserted.
ClientBrowser.label: Client Browser

ClimateChgEmssnFincSummary.description: Represents the emissions and financial information that a company discloses as part of ESRS E1 - Climate change.
ClimateChgEmssnFincSummary.label: Climate Change Emissions and Financial Summary

ClimateChgRiskOppSummary.description: Represents the climate-related risks and opportunities that a company discloses as part of ESRS E1 - Climate change.
ClimateChgRiskOppSummary.label: Climate Change Risk Opportunity Summary

ClinicalMeasure.description: Represents a structured and computable definition of a health-related measure for identifying care gaps. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

ClinicalMeasureCriteria.description: Represents a computable criteria of a health-related measure. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

ClinicalMeasureCriteriaGrp.description: Represents a group of computable criteria for a health-related measure. This object is available in API version 59.0 and later.

CmsnStmtLineItemTypConfig.label: Commission Statement Line Item Type Configuration

CodeSet.description: Represents various industry defined codes in the context of their systems and versions of those systems.
CodeSet.label: Code Set

Codeset.description: Represents various industry defined codes in the context of their systems and versions of those systems.

CodesetRelationship.description: Represents a relationship between a codeset and its related codeset. For example, a labor code associated with a fault code.

CollabDocumentMetric.description: Represents the engagement metrics for a Quip thread (document or spreadsheet) that’s linked to a Salesforce record.

CollabDocumentMetricRecord.description: Represents an association between a CollabDocumentMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollabTemplateMetric.description: Represents the engagement metrics for a Quip template.

CollabTemplateMetricRecord.description: Represents an association between a CollabTemplateMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollabUserEngagementMetric.description: Represents the user engagement metrics for a Quip thread in a Quip template or document.

CollabUserEngmtRecordLink.description: Represents an association between a CollabUserEngagementMetric and a Salesforce record.

CollaborationGroupMember.description: Represents a member of a Chatter group.
CollaborationGroupMember.label: Group Member

CollaborationGroupMemberRequest.description: Represents a request to join a private Chatter group.
CollaborationGroupMemberRequest.label: Group Member Request

CollaborationGroupRecord.description: Represents the records associated with Chatter groups.
CollaborationGroupRecord.label: Group Record

CollaborationInvitation.description: Represents an invitation to join Chatter, either directly or through a group.
CollaborationInvitation.label: Chatter Invitation

CollaborationRoom.description: Represents a collaboration room, which links Salesforce to a Slack channel used by applications with specific use cases, such as swarming or reporting.
CollaborationRoom.label: Collaboration Room

ColorDefinition.description: Represents color metadata for a tab.
ColorDefinition.label: Color Definition

CombinedAttachment.description: This read-only object contains all notes, attachments, Google Docs, documents uploaded to libraries in Salesforce CRM Content, and files added to Chatter that are associated with a record.
CombinedAttachment.label: Note, Attachment, Google Doc And File

CommSubscription.description: Represents the subscription options for a specific communication.
CommSubscription.label: Communication Subscription

CommSubscriptionChannelType.description: Represents the engagement channel through which you can reach a customer for a communication subscription.
CommSubscriptionChannelType.label: Communication Subscription Channel Type

CommSubscriptionConsent.description: Represents a customer’s consent to a communication subscription.
CommSubscriptionConsent.label: Communication Subscription Consent

CommSubscriptionTiming.description: Represents a customer's timing preferences for receiving a communication subscription.
CommSubscriptionTiming.label: Communication Subscription Timing

CommerceEntitlementBuyerGroup.description: Represents the entitlement policy for a buyer group.
CommerceEntitlementBuyerGroup.label: Entitlement Buyer Group

CommerceEntitlementPolicy.description: Represents an entitlement policy, which determines what products and prices a user can see.
CommerceEntitlementPolicy.label: Entitlement Policy

CommerceEntitlementPolicyShare.description: Represents the entitlement rule for sharing products and prices with users other than the owner.
CommerceEntitlementPolicyShare.label: Entitlement Policy Share

CommerceEntitlementProduct.description: Represents the entitlement policy for a product.
CommerceEntitlementProduct.label: Entitlement Product

CommissionSchedule.description: Represents a commission calculation and rate definition. Calculates commission values for a commissionable event.
CommissionSchedule.label: Commission Schedule

CommissionScheduleAssignment.description: Represents the commission calculation applicable to a specific product or producer for one or multiple commissionable events.
CommissionScheduleAssignment.label: Commission Schedule Assignment

Community (Zone).description: Represents a zone that contains Idea or Question objects.

CompactLayout.description: Represents the values that define a compact page layout.
CompactLayout.label: Compact Layout

CompactLayoutInfo.description: Represents the metadata for a custom or standard compact layout.
CompactLayoutInfo.label: Compact Layout

CompactLayoutItemInfo.description: Represents a field selected for a compact layout, and the order of that field in the compact layout.
CompactLayoutItemInfo.label: Compact Layout Item

Competency.description: Represents a skill, subject matter expertise, or behavior required for a job or role.

CompetencyRelatedObject.description: Represents a junction between competency and another object.

ComplaintCase.description: Represents the association between a public complaint and its corresponding case.

ComplaintParticipant.description: Represents a junction between a public complaint, and an account or a contact. This object stores the details of the participant who registers a complaint with the authorities. This participant could be the applicant, co-applicant, a household, or even a business account.

Composite API Event Type.description: Composite API events contain details about composite API requests.

Composite API Subrequest Event Type.description: Composite API subrequest events contain details about composite API subrequests.

ConcurApexLimitEventLog.description: Concurrent Apex Limit event logs contain information about long-running concurrent Apex requests in your org that Salesforce terminated after reaching your org’s concurrency limit. Requests with an established Apex context that execute for 5 seconds are counted towards your org’s limit of concurrent long-running requests. (Asynchronous requests don’t count towards the limit.) When the long-running requests exceed the org default limit, additional long-running requests are denied.

Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event.file: objects/C/Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event Type.json
Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit Event.description: Concurrent Long-Running Apex Limit events contain information about long-running concurrent Apex requests in your org that Salesforce terminated after reaching your org’s concurrency limit. Requests with an established Apex context that execute for 5 seconds are counted towards your org’s limit of concurrent long-running requests. (Asynchronous requests don’t count towards the limit.) When the long-running requests exceed the org default limit, all new Apex invocation requests are denied.

CondIntrctnHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on the set of interacting conditions they are diagnosed with and the status of their benefits eligibility.
CondIntrctnHlthRskAdjFctr.label: Condition Interaction Health Risk Adjustment Factor

ConferenceNumber.description: Holds the telephone number for an external event shown in the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.
ConferenceNumber.label: Conference Number

Console Event Type.description: Console events contain information about the performance and use of Salesforce Consoles. The Console events are logged whenever a Console tab is opened with a sidebar component. Outside of that, when Console tabs are opened, a regular view record detail event is served just like in Salesforce Classic.

ConstituentRole.description: Contains information about roles associated with the individual.

Consumption Rate.description: Consumption rates describe the billing rate for a range of usage within a consumption schedule. All consumption schedules require at least one consumption rate in order to rate usage on a usage product.

Consumption Schedule.description: A consumption schedule organizes a set of consumption rates by which usage-based products are quoted and billed.

ContCalloutSummaryEventLog.description: Continuation Callout Summary events contain information about all of the asynchronous callouts performed during a transaction, their response status codes, execution times, and URL endpoint destinations.

Contact.description: Represents a contact, which is a person associated with an account.
Contact.label: Contact

ContactCenterChannel.description: Represents a junction object that relates a Bring Your Own Channel for Contact Center as a Service (CCaaS) messaging channel to a CallCenter object for Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS. This object also represents the routing details for a voicemail configuration.
ContactCenterChannel.label: Contact Center Channel

ContactCleanInfo.description: Stores the metadata Data.com Clean uses to determine a contact record’s clean status. Helps you automate the cleaning or related processing of contact records. ContactCleanInfo includes a number of bit vector fields.
ContactCleanInfo.label: Contact Clean Info

ContactDailyMetric.description: Represents the daily engagement metrics for a contact.

ContactMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for a contact.

ContactOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a contact with a User other than the owner.
ContactOwnerSharingRule.label: Contact Owner Rule

ContactPointAddress.description: Represents a contact’s billing or shipping address, which is associated with an individual or person account.
ContactPointAddress.label: Contact Point Address

ContactPointConsent.description: Represents a customer's consent to be contacted via a specific contact point, such as an email address or phone number.
ContactPointConsent.label: Contact Point Consent

ContactPointEmail.description: Represents a contact’s email, which is associated with an individual or person account.
ContactPointEmail.label: Contact Point Email

ContactPointPhone.description: Represents a contact’s phone number, which is associated with an individual or person account.
ContactPointPhone.label: Contact Point Phone

ContactPointTypeConsent.description: Represents consent for a contact point type, such as email or phone.
ContactPointTypeConsent.label: Contact Point Type Consent

ContactProfile.description: Represents information about an individual, such as their ethnicity, citizenship, birth place, race, and so on.

ContactRequest.description: Represents a customer’s request for support to get back to them about an issue.
ContactRequest.label: Contact Request

ContactRequestShare.description: Represents a list of access levels to a ContactRequest with an explanation of the access level.
ContactRequestShare.label: Contact Request Share

ContactShare.description: Represents a list of access levels to a Contact along with an explanation of the access level. For example, if you have access to a record because you own it, the ContactAccessLevel is All and RowCause is Owner.
ContactShare.label: Contact Share

ContactSuggestionInsight.description: Represents a suggestion for a new contact record.

ContactTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Contact.

ContainerAsyncRequest.description: Allows you to compile and asynchronously deploy a MetadataContainer object to your organization.
ContainerAsyncRequest.label: Container Async Request

Content Distribution Event Type.description: Content Distribution events contain information about content distributions and deliveries to users.

Content Document Link Event Type.description: Content Document Link events contain sharing information for content documents.

Content Transfer Event Type.description: Content Transfer events contain information about content transfer events, such as downloads, uploads, and previews. This information includes events performed on files and attachments to records.

ContentAsset.description: Represents a Salesforce file that has been converted to an asset file in a custom app in Lightning Experience. Use asset files for org setup and configuration. Asset files can be packaged and referenced by other components.
ContentAsset.label: Asset File

ContentBody.description: Represents the body of a file in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files
ContentBody.label: Content Body

ContentDistribution.description: Represents information about sharing a document externally.
ContentDistribution.label: Content Delivery

ContentDistributionEventLog.description: Content Distribution events contain information about content distributions and deliveries to users.

ContentDistributionView.description: Represents information about views of a shared document.
ContentDistributionView.label: Content Delivery View

ContentDocLinkEventLog.description: Content Document Link events contain sharing information for content documents.

ContentDocument.description: Represents a document that has been uploaded to a library in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files. This object is available in versions 17.0 and later for Salesforce CRM Content.
ContentDocument.label: Content Document

ContentDocumentHistory.description: Represents the history of a document.
ContentDocumentHistory.label: Content Document History

ContentDocumentLink.description: Represents the link between a Salesforce CRM Content document, Salesforce file, or ContentNote and where it's shared. A file can be shared with other users, groups, records, and Salesforce CRM Content libraries.
ContentDocumentLink.label: Content Document Link

ContentDocumentListViewMapping.description: Represents an association between a ListView and a Quip ContentDocument. Applies to Quip file types only. Maintains the mapping between a list view and Quip document when the list view is exported to a newly created Quip document.
ContentDocumentListViewMapping.label: Quip Document from List View

ContentDocumentSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following or commenting on a file in a library.
ContentDocumentSubscription.label: Content Document Subscription

ContentFolder.description: Represents a folder in a content library for adding files.
ContentFolder.label: Content Folder

ContentFolderItem.description: Represents a file (ContentDocument) or folder (ContentFolder) that resides in a ContentFolder in a ContentWorkspace.
ContentFolderItem.label: Content Folder Item

ContentFolderLink.description: Defines the association between a library and its root folder.
ContentFolderLink.label: Content Folder Link

ContentFolderMember.description: Defines the association between a file and a folder.
ContentFolderMember.label: Content Folder Member

ContentHubItem.description: Represents a file or folder in a Files Connect external data source, such as Microsoft SharePoint or OneDrive for Business.
ContentHubItem.label: Files Connect item

ContentHubRepository.description: Represents a Files Connect external data source such as Microsoft SharePoint or OneDrive for Business.
ContentHubRepository.label: Files Connect repository

ContentLink.description: Represents a reference object with information about its content source.
ContentLink.label: Content Link

ContentNote.description: Represents a note created with the enhanced note taking tool, released in Winter ‘16.
ContentNote.label: Note

ContentNotification.description: Represents a notification for a file.
ContentNotification.label: Content Notification

ContentSource.description: Represents the data source that's referenced by an object.
ContentSource.label: Content Source

ContentTagSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a tag on a file.
ContentTagSubscription.label: Content Tag Subscription

ContentTaxonomy.description: Represents a content taxonomy, which is used to classify and organize Salesforce CMS content. To create a hierarchy of terms in a content taxonomy, use this object in addition to the ContentTaxonomyTerm, ContentTaxonomyRelatedTerm, and ContentTaxonomyTermRelatedTerm objects.
ContentTaxonomy.label: Content Taxonomy

ContentTaxonomyRelatedTerm.description: Represents the relationship between a term and the content taxonomy to which the term belongs.
ContentTaxonomyRelatedTerm.label: Content Taxonomy Related Term

ContentTaxonomyTerm.description: Represents a term in a content taxonomy. Terms describe what content is or how it's used, and they’re organized in parent-child relationships in the taxonomy hierarchy.
ContentTaxonomyTerm.label: Content Taxonomy Term

ContentTaxonomyTermRelatedTerm.description: Represents the relationship between two terms in a content taxonomy.
ContentTaxonomyTermRelatedTerm.label: Content Taxonomy Term Related Term

ContentTaxonomyTermRelationshipType.description: Represents the type of relationship between two terms in a content taxonomy.
ContentTaxonomyTermRelationshipType.label: Content Taxonomy Term Relationship Type

ContentTransferEventLog.description: ContentTransferEventLog stores information about content transfer events, such as downloads, uploads, and previews. This information includes events performed on files and attachments to records.

ContentUserSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following another user.
ContentUserSubscription.label: Content User Subscription

ContentVersion.description: Represents a specific version of a document in Salesforce CRM Content or Salesforce Files.
ContentVersion.label: Content Version

ContentVersionComment.description: Represents a comment on a version of a file.
ContentVersionComment.label: Content Version Comment

ContentVersionHistory.description: Represents the history of a specific version of a document.
ContentVersionHistory.label: Content Version History

ContentVersionRating.description: Represents a rating on a version of a file.
ContentVersionRating.label: Content Version Rating

ContentWorkspaceDoc.description: Represents a link between a document and a public library in Salesforce CRM Content.
ContentWorkspaceDoc.label: Library Document

ContentWorkspaceMember.description: Represents a member of a content library.
ContentWorkspaceMember.label: Library Member

ContentWorkspaceSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a library.
ContentWorkspaceSubscription.label: Content Workspace Subscription

ContextMappingConfig.description: Represents the context mapping configurations for business process types.

ContextParamMap.description: Represents optional context data for a Conversation or a ConversationParticipant.
ContextParamMap.label: Context Param Map

Continuation Callout Summary Event Type.description: Continuation Callout Summary events contain information about all of the asynchronous callouts performed during a transaction, their response status codes, execution times, and URL endpoint destinations.

Contract.description: Represents a contract (a business agreement) associated with an Account.
Contract.label: Contract

ContractContactRole.description: Represents the role that a Contact plays on a Contract.
ContractContactRole.label: Contract Contact Role

ContractGroupPlan.description: Represents a set of plans as part of the contract between the insurance carrier and the group. This set of plans corresponds to the plans included in the quote (as Quote Line Items). Child object of Contract.
ContractGroupPlan.label: Contract Group Plan

ContractGroupPlanGroupClass.description: Represents the association of a Contract Group Plan to a Group Class. Use this entity to define group classes and group class contributions at the contract group plan level.
ContractGroupPlanGroupClass.label: Contract Group Plan Group Class

ContractGrpPlanGrpClsAttr.description: Represents a view of the attributes selected for each contract group plan group class.
ContractGrpPlanGrpClsAttr.label: Contract Group Plan Group Class Attribute

ContractItemPrice.description: Represents an object that’s used to capture a price for a product on a contract.

ContractItemPriceAdjTier.description: Represents the tiers of a price adjustment to a product on a contract.

ContractItemPriceHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields of a ContractItemPrice object.

ContractLineItem.description: Represents a product covered by a service contract (customer support agreement).
ContractLineItem.label: Contract Line Item

ContractLineOutcome.description: Represents information on a contract line outcome’s captured data and other related parameters that are used when capturing data.
ContractLineOutcome.label: Contract Line Outcome

ContractLineOutcomeData.description: Represents the contract line outcome’s captured data. It stores the data that was captured between the contract line outcome’s start date and end date. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.
ContractLineOutcomeData.label: Contract Line Outcome Data

ContractPaymentAgreement.description: Stores information about the contract payment agreement associated with a contract.
ContractPaymentAgreement.label: Contract Payment Agreement

ContractStatus.description: Represents the status of a Contract, such as Draft, InApproval, Activated, Terminated, or Expired.
ContractStatus.label: Contract Status Value

ContractTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Contract.

ConvAnalysisSummary.description: Represents the information stored for each run or refresh of Sales Signals.

ConvAnalysisTopic.description: Represents a topic generated from the Sales Signals refresh or run. For example, a product experiencing issues due to high pricing could be a topic identified through the analysis of multiple calls.

ConvAnalysisTopicEntry.description: Represents a single entry under the ConvAnalysisTopic object. An entry represents a segment of a video or voice call that is associated with a conversation analysis topic.

ConvIntelligenceSignalRule.description: Represents a conversation intelligence signal rule.
ConvIntelligenceSignalRule.label: Conversation Intelligence Signal Rule

ConvIntelligenceSignalSubRule.description: Represents a condition (subrule) within a conversation intelligence signal rule.
ConvIntelligenceSignalSubRule.label: Conversation Intelligence Signal Sub-Rule

ConvMessageSendRequest.description: Represents a request to send a template-based messaging component to a series of messaging users in an enhanced messaging channel or Messaging for In-App.
ConvMessageSendRequest.label: Conversation Message Send Request

Conversation.description: Represents a conversation between an end user and an agent.
Conversation.label: Conversation

ConversationApiLog.description: Logs of an API operation on a specific conversation object done using the Conversation Service API.
ConversationApiLog.label: Conversation Api Log

ConversationChannelDefinition.description: Represents a configurable definition of a conversation channel that’s implemented for Interaction Service for Bring Your Own Channel for Messaging and Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS messaging channels.
ConversationChannelDefinition.label: Conversation Channel Definition

ConversationContextEntry.description: Represents the context of a message or an event in the chat history between an agent and a messaging user.
ConversationContextEntry.label: Conversation Context Entry

ConversationEntry.description: Represents a message or event in a voice call or a standard or enhanced messaging session.
ConversationEntry.label: Conversation Entry

ConversationParticipant.description: Represents an active participant in a conversation. A new ConversationParticipant record is created each time a participant joins a conversation.
ConversationParticipant.label: Conversation Participant

ConversationVendorInfo.description: This setup object connects the partner vendor system to the Service Cloud feature.
ConversationVendorInfo.label: Conversation Vendor Information

CorsWhitelistEntry.description: Represents an entry in the cross-origin resource sharing (CORS) allowlist. Origins included in the allowlist can request REST resources from that Salesforce org.
CorsWhitelistEntry.label: CORS Allowed Origin List

CostBook.description: Represents the cost book that contains multiple cost book entries.

CostBookEntry.description: Represents the total cost of a product or service that’s determined based on various factors that affect a product's price. For example, when a product is manufactured, the weight of the raw material can be a cost factor based on the amount of material required and its shipping cost.

CostCenter.description: Represents the actual expenses that are compared to the budget.

Coupon.description: A coupon associated with a promotion.
Coupon.label: Coupon

CourseCreditTransferAppln.description: Represents the details of a course credit transfer application.

CourseOffering.description: Represents an instance of a training course with location and date details of training courses.

CourseOfferingParticipant.description: Represents information about a student's enrollment in a Course Offering.

CourseOfferingPtcpResult.description: Represents the outcome of a student's participation in a course.

CourseOfferingRelationship.description: Represents a junction between a course offering and a related course offering.

CourseOfferingSchedule.description: Represents information about the schedule defined for a Course Offering.

CourseOfferingScheduleTmpl.description: Represents a template that can be used to define a course schedule.

CourseOfrgRubricCriterion.description: Represents an activity rubric criterion for a course offering.

CoverageBenefit.description: Represents the benefits provided to a covered member by a purchaser’s plan.
CoverageBenefit.label: Coverage Benefit

CoverageBenefitItem.description: Specific service covered by the insurance plan.
CoverageBenefitItem.label: Coverage Benefit Item

CoverageBenefitItemLimit.description: Allows you to track details associated with a specific benefit as it relates to expenditures, limits, coverage levels, eligibility, and exclusion.
CoverageBenefitItemLimit.label: Coverage Benefit Item Limit

CoverageType.description: Represents the type of coverage, such as liability, earthquake, or collision damage. You see this object only if you have enabled the Access Master List of Coverage Types org pref.

CrMemoProcessErrDtlEvent.description: Represents the information about errors that occurred while creating or applying a credit memo as part of a request. This object is included in a CreditInvoiceProcessedEvent, CreditMemoProcessedEvent, NegInvcLineProcessedEvent, or VoidInvoiceProcessedEvent platform event message. You can't subscribe to CrMemoProcessErrDtlEvent platform event directly.

CrbnCreditAlloc.description: Represents information about how the carbon credits are allocated by an organization to offset their emissions.
CrbnCreditAlloc.label: Carbon Credit Allocation

CrbnCreditAllocItem.description: Represents information about carbon credit allocation and emissions related to each emission activity.
CrbnCreditAllocItem.label: Carbon Credit Allocation Item

CrbnCreditDistribution.description: Represents a junction between the sustainability credit and carbon credit allocation objects. To offset emissions for carbon credit allocation items, specify the emissions activity on this junction object.
CrbnCreditDistribution.label: Carbon Credit Distribution

CrbnCreditProject.description: Represents information about the environmental project that generates carbon credits by removing greenhouse gasses or preventing a certain quantity of greenhouse gasses from being released.
CrbnCreditProject.label: Carbon Credit Project

CrbnEmssnScopeAlloc.description: Represents the allocation of fuel consumption for different scope emissions. For an energy use record, tCO₂e is calculated and the results are classified as either Scope 1, Scope 2, or Scope 3 emission values. Each individual fuel type has its own scope allocation record. To put the tCO2e result in the correct scope, the energy use record points to the scope allocation record.
CrbnEmssnScopeAlloc.label: Carbon Emissions Scope Allocation

CrbnEmssnScopeAllocVal.description: Represents the scope allocation by fuel type.
CrbnEmssnScopeAllocVal.label: Carbon Emissions Scope Allocation Value

CreateAssetOrderDtlEvent.description: Contains information about an attempt to create or update an asset as a result of /actions/standard/createOrUpdateAssetFromOrder. If the request was successful, the event shows information about the asset. If the request failed, the event shows error information.

CreditMemo.description: Represents a document that’s used to reduce the amount that a buyer owes a seller under the terms of an earlier invoice.

CreditMemoAddressGroup.description: Represents the storage of the buyer's address information, which is used to determine the tax credit amount for a buyer when a credit memo is issued.

CreditMemoInvApplication.description: Represents information about the application of a credit memo to an invoice.

CreditMemoLine.description: Represents the product, service, adjustment, or tax line items included in a credit memo.

CreditMemoLineInvoiceLine.description: Represents a junction between a credit memo line and an invoice line.

CreditMemoLineTax.description: Represents tax information of a credit memo line of type Tax.

CreditMemoProcessedEvent.description: Represents the notification to the customers after the process initiated by the /commerce/invoicing/credit-memos request is complete.

Crisis.description: Represents a major crisis event that affects an Employee in an InternalOrganizationUnit.

CronJobDetail.description: Contains details about the associated scheduled job, such as the job’s name and type.
CronJobDetail.label: Cron Job

CronTrigger.description: Contains schedule information for a scheduled job. CronTrigger is similar to a cron job on UNIX systems. This object is available in API version 17.0 and later.
CronTrigger.label: Scheduled Jobs

CryptoProdCatgWalletGroup.description: Specifies if CryptoWalletGroup is in the allowlist or airdrop for the ProductCategory. A custom object between ProductCategory and CryptoWalletGroup adding the CryptoWalletGroup to allowlist or airdrop.

CspViolationEventLog.description: CSP violation events capture details about blocked resource requests from Lightning Experience pages based on your content security policy (CSP).

CurrencyType.description: Represents the currencies used by an organization for which the multicurrency feature is enabled.
CurrencyType.label: Currency Type

CustExpIntlTransfSetup.description: Stores information for different data sources that are processed for customer insights. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.

CustodyChainEntry.description: Represents information about an entry or event in the chain of custody.

CustodyItem.description: Represents information about an item in the custody chain.

CustodyItemRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a custody item and the context in which it’s held. For example, a custody item related to a case or case proceeding.

CustodyItemRgltyCodeVio.description: Represents a junction between a custody item and the related regulatory code violation. The violation can be related to laws, regulations, or code that is associated with the custody item.

CustodyVerfcTypeOverride.description: Represents information about the verification of an entry in the chain of custody.

Custom Object__Feed.description: Represents the feed, specifically posts and feed-tracked changes, on a custom object.

Custom Objects.description: In the user interface, you can extend your org’s data by defining custom objects. Custom objects are custom database tables that allow you to store information unique to your organization. For custom objects, the custom flag—a Boolean field in the describe results—is true.

CustomApplication.description: Represents a custom or standard application.
CustomApplication.label: Custom App

CustomBrand.description: Represents a custom branding and color scheme.
CustomBrand.label: Custom Brand

CustomBrandAsset.description: Represents a branding element in a custom branding scheme. For example, a color, logo image, header image, or footer text.
CustomBrandAsset.label: Custom Brand Asset

CustomField.description: Represents a custom field on a custom object that stores data unique to your organization.
CustomField.label: Custom Field Definition

CustomFieldDisplay.description: Represents the view type assigned to product attribute custom fields.
CustomFieldDisplay.label: Custom Field Display

CustomFieldDisplayValue.description: Stores variation details for the product attribute item view.
CustomFieldDisplayValue.label: Custom Field Display Value

CustomFieldMember.description: Represents the working copy of a field for editing or saving in a MetadataContainer.
CustomFieldMember.label: Metadata Container Member

CustomFulfillmentScopeCnfg.description: Represents a user-defined scope to define and customize scope-specific validation and orchestration for flexible fulfillment.

CustomHelpMenuItem.description: Represents the items within a section of the Lightning Experience help menu that the admin added to display custom, org-specific help resources.
CustomHelpMenuItem.label: Custom Help Menu Item

CustomHttpHeader.description: Represents a custom HTTP header used with OData 2.0 or OData 4.0 external data sources. Custom HTTP headers provide context information from Salesforce such as region, org details, or the role of the person viewing the external object.
CustomHttpHeader.label: Custom HTTP Header

CustomMsgChannel.description: Represents a custom conversation channel and stores event-driven Messaging settings. Custom conversation channels are implemented for Bring Your Own Channel for Messaging and Bring Your Own Channel for CCaaS Messaging channels.

CustomNotificationType.description: Stores information about custom notification types.
CustomNotificationType.label: Custom Notification Type

CustomObject.description: Represents a custom object that stores data unique to your organization. Includes access to the associated CustomObject object and related fields in Salesforce Metadata API.
CustomObject.label: Custom Object Definition

CustomObjectParticipant.description: Represents information about a participant in the context of a custom object record.

CustomPermission.description: Represents a permission created to control access to a custom process or app, such as sending email.
CustomPermission.label: Custom Permission

CustomPermissionDependency.description: Represents the dependency between two custom permissions when one custom permission requires that you enable another custom permission.
CustomPermissionDependency.label: Custom Permission Dependency

Customer.description: Represents the customer role of an individual with respect to a particular company or organization.
Customer.label: Customer

CustomerProperty.description: Represents the insurable and insured properties of a customer.
CustomerProperty.label: Customer Property

DandBCompany.description: Represents a Dun & Bradstreet® company record, which is associated with an account added from Data.com.

Dashboard.description: Represents a dashboard, which shows data from custom reports as visual components. Access is read-only.
Dashboard.label: Dashboard

Dashboard Event Type.description: Dashboard events contain details about report requests from dashboards. These requests are triggered by dashboard refreshes, subscriptions, and filter changes.

DashboardComponent.description: Represents a dashboard component, which can be a chart, metric, table, or gauge on a dashboard. Access is read-only.
DashboardComponent.label: Dashboard Component

DataAssessmentConfigItem.description: Represents a saved configuration for a specific vendor’s package for data assessment.
DataAssessmentConfigItem.label: Data Assessment Configuration Item

DataAssessmentFieldMetric.description: Represents summary statistics for matched, blank, and differing fields in account records of an org compared to records in Data.com.
DataAssessmentFieldMetric.label: Data Assessment Field Metric

DataAssessmentMetric.description: Represents a summary of statistics for fields matched and unmatched in your account records with Data.com account records.
DataAssessmentMetric.label: Data Assessment Metric

DataAssessmentValueMetric.description: Summarizes the number of fields matched for your account records with Data.com account records.
DataAssessmentValueMetric.label: Data Assessment Field Value Metric

DataDetPlcyDataSrchExps.description: Represents data search expressions for scanning DataDetect scan policies based on Java regex.

DataDetPlcyMdatScanCrit.description: Represents inclusion and exclusion criteria that filter what DataDetect scan policy object fields are to be scanned based on metadata tags.

DataDetPlcySstvDataCatg.description: Represents the sensitive data categories that the DataDetect scan policy is required to scan.

DataDetectJobObjectSession.description: Represents an object-specific job session that's created whenever a DataDetect scan policy job session runs on a scan policy object.

DataDetectJobSession.description: Represents a run of a DataDetect scan policy that's triggered manually.

DataDetectPolicy.description: Represents a set of parameters that specifies the types of sensitive data to be searched for in a data scan. DataDetect scan policies can also apply filters to a data scan, and select what specific objects and fields are to be scanned.

DataDetectPolicyObjField.description: Represents an object field of the DataDetect scan policy object to be scanned. This object is available in API version 64.0 and later.

DataDetectPolicyObject.description: Represents an object of the DataDetect scan policy to be scanned. This object is available in API version 62.0 and later.

DataDetectPolicySnapshot.description: Represents the snapshot of a DataDetect scan policy and its components retrieved during a job session.

DataDetectScanResult.description: Represents the results of a DataDetect scan policy data scan.

DataEncryptionKey.description: The DataEncryptionKey object is part of the Bring Your Own Key (BYOK) feature, which allows users to upload a data encryption key (DEK) using a public key generated by the Salesforce Shield Key Management Service (KMS). Customers create their own DEKs and upload them to Salesforce. Users access this entity via the API to list DEK keys for auditing purposes. They can also programmatically use this object to create the certificate and to upload key material.
DataEncryptionKey.label: Data Encryption Key

DataIntegrationRecordPurchasePermission.description: Represents Lightning Data purchase credits that a Salesforce admin has granted to users.
DataIntegrationRecordPurchasePermission.label: DataIntegrationRecordPurchasePermission

DataKitDeployEvent.description: Represents a data kit deployment event that notifies subscribers of the status of the data kit component deployment. This object is available in API version 61.0 or later.
DataKitDeployEvent.label: Data Kit Deployment Event

DataKitDeploymentLog.description: Represents the log details of a data kit component deployment. This object is available in API version 61.0 or later.
DataKitDeploymentLog.label: Data Kit Deployment Log

DataMaskCustomValueLibrary.description: Represents a set of user-inputted values in a custom library in Data Mask.
DataMaskCustomValueLibrary.label: Custom Library

DataMltOrgMdatChgLineage.label: Data Multi Org Metadata Change Lineage

DataSourceBundleDefinition.description: Represents the bundle of streams that a user adds to a data kit.
DataSourceBundleDefinition.label: Data Source Bundle Definition

DataSrcDataModelFieldMap.label: Data Source Data Model Field Mapping

DataStreamTemplate.description: Represents metadata about the data stream that a user adds to a data kit. This object is available in API version 52.0 and later.
DataStreamTemplate.label: Data Stream Template

DataUseLegalBasis.description: Represents the legal basis for contacting a customer, such as billing or contract.
DataUseLegalBasis.label: Data Use Legal Basis

DataUsePurpose.description: Represents the reason for contacting a prospect or customer, such as for billing, marketing, or surveys
DataUsePurpose.label: Data Use Purpose

DataWeaveResource.description: Represents the DataWeaveScriptResource class that is generated for all DataWeave scripts.
DataWeaveResource.label: DataWeave Resource

DatabaseSaveEventLog.description: Database Save events track when records are created,updated, or deleted

DatacloudCompany.description: Represents the fields for Data.com company records.

DatacloudContact.description: The fields and properties for Data.com contact records.

DatacloudDandBCompany.description: Represents a set of read-only fields that are used to return D&B company data from Data.com API calls.

DatacloudOwnedEntity.description: Represents fields in the DatacloudOwnedEntity object. The DatacloudOwnedEntity object tracks user-purchased records.

DatacloudPurchaseUsage.description: Represents an object used to identify and track Data.com record purchases. This object is available in API version 30.0 or later.

DatasetExport.description: Represents a dataset exported from CRM Analytics. When a dataset is exported, the data is converted into a .csv file and the schema is stored in a separate JSON file. These files are stored in two objects: DatasetExport and DatasetExportPart. DatasetExport acts as the header and includes the JSON schema.
DatasetExport.label: Dataset Export

DatasetExportPart.description: Represents a dataset exported from CRM Analytics. When a dataset is exported, the data is converted into a .csv file and the schema is stored in a separate JSON file. These files are stored in two objects: DatasetExport and DatasetExportPart. DatasetExportPart contains parts of the .csv file.
DatasetExportPart.label: Dataset Export Part

DatedConversionRate.description: Represents the dated exchange rates used by an organization for which the multicurrency and the effective dated currency features are enabled.
DatedConversionRate.label: Dated Conversion Rate

DealIndirectPartner.description: Represents an indirect partner’s involvement in a deal.

DebitMemo.description: Represents the document used to charge an additional amount to a buyer by a seller. An invoice is generated for the debit memo in the next invoice run.

DebitMemoAddress.description: Represents the buyer's address information, which is used to determine the tax amount for a buyer when a debit memo is issued.

DebitMemoLine.description: Represents the additional charge amount that the buyer must pay for the product, service, or debit memo line tax that’s related to the debit memo.

DebugLevel.description: Represents a set of log category levels to assign to a TraceFlag object. Multiple trace flags can use a debug level.
DebugLevel.label: Debug Level

DecisionMatrixDefinition.description: Represents information about a decision matrix definition.
DecisionMatrixDefinition.label: Decision Matrix Definition

DecisionMatrixDefinitionVersion.description: Represents information about a decision matrix definition version.
DecisionMatrixDefinitionVersion.label: Decision Matrix Definition Version

DecisionTable.description: Represents the information about a decision table.
DecisionTable.label: Decision Table

DecisionTableDatasetLink.description: Represents a dataset link associated with a decision table. Use dataset links in a decision table to select an object whose records the decision table must evaluate and provide outcomes for.
DecisionTableDatasetLink.label: Decision Table Dataset Link

DecisionTableParameter.description: Represents an input or output field in a decision table. An input field is a field in the business rule object or custom metadata type that contains values used by the decision table to evaluate records and values. An output field is a field in the business rule object or custom metadata type that contains the values provided as outcomes for a rule.
DecisionTableParameter.label: Decision Table Parameter

DecisionTableSourceCriteria.description: Represents the fields and values from a data source that are used to define the condition logic of the data that's used in a decision table.
DecisionTableSourceCriteria.label: Decision Table Source Criteria

DecisionTblDatasetParameter.description: Represents the mapping between a decision table parameter and a field of the object selected in the dataset link. This mapping allows the decision table to know which object fields from the dataset link must be evaluated by the input fields of the decision table.
DecisionTblDatasetParameter.label: Decision Table Dataset Parameter

DeclinedEventRelation.description: Represents event participants (invitees or attendees) with the status Declined for a given event.
DeclinedEventRelation.label: Declined Event Relation

DelegateGroup.description: Represents a Delegate Group for queries.
DelegateGroup.label: Delegated Group

DelegateGroupGrant.description: Represents a Delegate Group Grant, indicating permissions granted to a delegate group.
DelegateGroupGrant.label: Delegated Group Grant

DelegateGroupMember.description: Represents users assigned to the delegate group
DelegateGroupMember.label: Delegated Administrators

DeleteEvent.description: Represents a record that has been soft deleted.
DeleteEvent.label: Recycle Bin Item

DeliveryEstimationSetup.description: Shows the configuration options for the commerce delivery service offered through a web store or sales channel. Includes settings such as delivery location group, channel, fulfillment types, and default fulfillment time.
DeliveryEstimationSetup.label: Delivery Estimation Setup

DeliveryTask.description: Represents information about shipments and orders to be delivered to a store in a visit.

DeployDetails.description: A complex type that contains detailed XML for any compile errors reported in the asynchronous request defined by a ContainerAsyncRequest object.

DeployRequest.description: Uses file representations of metadata components to create, update, or delete those components in a Salesforce org. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.
