DeployRequest.label: Deploy Request

Deviation.description: Represents the information about the deviation from set rules.

DigitalSignature.description: Represents a signature captured on a service report in field service.
DigitalSignature.label: Digital Signature

DigitalVerification.description: Stores information about the verification of a related record
DigitalVerification.label: Digital Verification

DigitalWallet.description: Represents a customer’s digital wallet service. Salesforce Payments can use a digital wallet as a payment source when processing payments through a payment gateway.
DigitalWallet.label: Digital Wallet

DirectMessage.description: Represents a direct message conversation between multiple users in Chatter.

Disclosure.description: Represents the disclosure details that a company shares, which can be included by a user in their response document.
Disclosure.label: Disclosure

DisclosureDefinition.description: Represents information that defines a disclosure type, such as details of the publisher or vendor who created or implemented the report.
DisclosureDefinition.label: Disclosure Definition

DisclosureDefinitionVersion.description: Represents the version information about the disclosure definition.
DisclosureDefinitionVersion.label: Disclosure Definition Version

DisclosureType.description: Represents the types of disclosures that are done by an individual or an organization and the associated metadata.
DisclosureType.label: Disclosure Type

DisclsReportingPeriod.description: Represents a corporate reporting period that is used for stakeholder disclosure reports.
DisclsReportingPeriod.label: Disclosure Reporting Period

Dispute.description: Represents the details of a dispute that involves one or multiple disputed transactions.
Dispute.label: Dispute

DisputeItem.description: Represents a transaction that’s being disputed.
DisputeItem.label: Dispute Item

DisputeItemArbitration.description: Represents the details of the arbitration or compliance case filed for a transaction that's being disputed.
DisputeItemArbitration.label: Dispute Item Arbitration

DisputeItemChargeback.description: Represents the claim and chargeback created by the card issuer for a transaction that's being disputed.
DisputeItemChargeback.label: Dispute Item Chargeback

DisputeItemMerchantAlert.description: Represents the alert sent by the card issuer to the merchant. The alert occurs through a chargeback prevention vendor like Ethoca Merchant Alerts™ for a transaction that’s being disputed.
DisputeItemMerchantAlert.label: Dispute Item Merchant Alert

DisputeItemQueueResponse.description: Represents the response received from the job that’s run to fetch the claim details.
DisputeItemQueueResponse.label: Dispute Item Queue Response

DisputeQueueJobRun.description: Represents a job that’s run to fetch the details of the claims.
DisputeQueueJobRun.label: Dispute Queue Job Run

DisputeReason.description: Represents the reason for the transaction dispute.
DisputeReason.label: Dispute Reason

DistributorAuthorization.description: Represents the official authorization from an insurance company granting a distributor the permission to act as its agent.
DistributorAuthorization.label: Distributor Authorization

Division.description: A logical segment of your organization's data. For example, if your company is organized into different business units, you could create a division for each business unit, such as “North America,” “Healthcare,” or “Consulting.” Available only if the organization has the Division permission enabled.

DivisionLocalization.description: When the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization, the DivisionLocalization object provides the translation of the label for a division.

DivrsEquityInclSum.description: Represents information that indicates the quantitative view of the organization based on the employee gender, age group, and other fairness indicators.
DivrsEquityInclSum.label: Diversity Equity Inclusion Summary

DocAtchDownloadEventLog.description: Document Attachment Downloads events contain details of document and attachment downloads.

DocChkItemValidatedTarget.description: Represents the details of the document checklist item and the target object against which the document checklist item was validated.

DocClauseSetAsmtQstn.description: Represents a junction between a document clause set and an assessment question.

Document.description: Represents a file that a user has uploaded. Unlike Attachment records, documents are not attached to a parent object.
Document.label: Document

Document Attachment Downloads Event Type.description: Document Attachment Downloads events contain details of document and attachment downloads.

DocumentAttachmentMap.description: Maps the relationship between an EmailTemplate and its attachment, which is stored as a Document.
DocumentAttachmentMap.label: Document Entity Map

DocumentCategory.description: Represents a document category that's used to group the document checklist items.
DocumentCategory.label: Document Category

DocumentCategoryDocumentType.description: Represents a junction between Document Category and Document Type.
DocumentCategoryDocumentType.label: Document Category Document Type

DocumentChecklistItem.description: Represents a checklist item for a file documentation upload.
DocumentChecklistItem.label: Document Checklist Item

DocumentDecisionRequirement.description: Represents the decision criteria that will be used to determine applicable documents.
DocumentDecisionRequirement.label: Document Decision Requirement

DocumentRecipient.description: Connects a Service Report to a Digital Signature.
DocumentRecipient.label: Document Recipient

DocumentType.description: Represents the type of file being uploaded or attached.
DocumentType.label: Document Type

Domain.description: Read-only object that represents a custom Web address assigned to a site in your organization.
Domain.label: Domain

DomainProvision.description: Represents provisioned changes to custom domains.
DomainProvision.label: Domain Provision

DomainSite.description: Read-only junction object that joins the Site and Domain objects.
DomainSite.label: Custom URL

DsarPolicy.description: Represents a Data Subject Access Request (DSAR) policy created in the Privacy Center managed package. DSAR policies anonymize or transfer personal data from your org at your customer’s request. This object is available in API version 50.0 and later.
DsarPolicy.label: Data Subject Access Request Policy

DsarPolicyLog.description: Represents the history of Data Subject Access Request (DSAR) policy execution requests. This log records the status and results of executed DSAR policies for a customer. This object is available in API version 50.0 and later.
DsarPolicyLog.label: Data Subject Access Request Policy Log

DuplicateJob.description: Represents an instance of a job that identifies duplicates among existing records in the system.

DuplicateJobDefinition.description: Setup object defining a job that identifies duplicate record items globally.

DuplicateJobMatchingRule.description: Represents a MatchingRule to be used with a DuplicateJob sharing the corresponding DuplicateJobMatchingRuleDefinition.

DuplicateJobMatchingRuleDefinition.description: Setup object specifying a MatchingRule to use with DuplicateJob instances that share a DuplicateJobDefinition.

DuplicateRecordItem.description: Represents a record that’s been identified as a duplicate. DuplicateRecordItems are included in a DuplicateRecordSet, which are processed in duplicate jobs. Use this object to create custom report types for duplicates.
DuplicateRecordItem.label: Duplicate Record Item

DuplicateRecordSet.description: Represents a group of records that have been identified as duplicates. Each duplicate record set contains one or more duplicate record items. Use this object to create custom report types and view the results of duplicate jobs.
DuplicateRecordSet.label: Duplicate Record Set

DuplicateRule.description: Represents a duplicate rule for detecting duplicate records.
DuplicateRule.label: Duplicate Rule

DynamicDataCapture.description: DynamicDataCapture is a junction object that adds a Form tab to Work Order Overview, and to the related list of a work order, work order line item, or service appointment in the Field Service mobile app.
DynamicDataCapture.label: Form

EconomicPerformanceSum.description: Represents statistics about the direct economic value generated and distributed by an organization or the related income and expenses.
EconomicPerformanceSum.label: Economic Performance Summary

EducInstSearchableProfile.description: Represents information about an educational institution aggregated from other objects for Criteria-Based Search and Filter.

EducInstitutionOffering.description: Represents a junction between an institution's account and other objects, such as program, learning program, and academic term.

EducationalInfoRequest.description: Represents details about a request for information (RFI) raised by prospective students, parents, or counselors.

ElectricityEmssnFctrSet.description: Represents the factors that are used to convert electricity usage into CO₂e, CO₂, CH₄, and N₂O values. This record holds data on the breakdown of sources of electricity by fuel type (grid mixes).
ElectricityEmssnFctrSet.label: Electricity Emissions Factor Set

ElectronicMediaGroup.description: Represents the type of media that you can associate with a product or category.
ElectronicMediaGroup.label: Electronic Media Group

EmailContent.description: Represents a marketing email asset for use with Account Engagement.
EmailContent.label: Email Content

EmailDomainFilter.description: Represents a filter that determines whether an email relay is restricted to a specific list of domains.
EmailDomainFilter.label: Email Domain Filter

EmailDomainKey.description: Represents a domain key for an organization’s domain, used to authenticate outbound email that Salesforce sends on the organization’s behalf.
EmailDomainKey.label: Email Domain Key

EmailInsight.description: Represents an insight generated from an email interaction. EmailInsights acts as a central place to store various types of insights related to email messages. The insights stored include status, type, and time of generation. Only certain types of insights can be created based on a pre-configured list of insight types.

EmailInsightAction.description: Represents the actions that have been taken, or could be taken, in relation to email insights. It logs different types of actions and associated metadata, helping to track and manage the activities and decisions made based on email insights.

EmailMessageRelation.description: Represents the relationship between an email and contacts, leads, and users.
EmailMessageRelation.label: Email Message Relation

EmailRelay.description: Represents the configuration for sending an email relay. An email relay routes email sent from Salesforce through your company’s email servers.
EmailRelay.label: Email Relay

EmailRoutingAddress.description: An email address used for Email-to-Case. Email routing addresses store a unique email services address provided by Salesforce and configuration options for emails received by this address.
EmailRoutingAddress.label: Email-to-Case Routing Address

EmailStatus.description: Represents the status of email sent.
EmailStatus.label: Email Status

EmailTemplate.description: Represents a template for an email, mass email, list email, or Sales Engagement email. Supported in first-generation managed packages only.
EmailTemplate.label: Email Template

EmailTemplateMonthlyMetric.description: Represents the monthly engagement metrics for an email template.

EmbeddedServiceAppointmentSettings.label: Embedded Service Deployment for Appointment Management

EmbeddedServiceConfig.description: Represents a setup node for creating an Embedded Service deployment.
EmbeddedServiceConfig.label: Embedded Service Deployment

EmbeddedServiceCustomComponent.description: Represents a custom component created for an Embedded Service feature.
EmbeddedServiceCustomComponent.label: Custom Component for Embedded Service

EmbeddedServiceCustomLabel.description: Represents a customized label that appears in the embedded component for a particular Embedded Service deployment. Labels can be customized for both Embedded Chat and embedded Appointment Management (beta).
EmbeddedServiceCustomLabel.label: Custom Label for Embedded Service

EmbeddedServiceCustomization.description: Represents a mapping between the EmbeddedServiceCustomization record parent and the EmbeddedServiceConfiguration or EmbeddedServiceMenuSettings, for a set of Embedded Service resources. Each resource is set of customizations applied via an uploaded static resource for your Embedded Chat.
EmbeddedServiceCustomization.label: Deployment Custom Setting

EmbeddedServiceDetail.description: Represents a metadata catalog object that exposes fields from the underlying Embedded Service setup objects defined in each EmbeddedServiceConfig deployment for guest users. Guest users don’t have direct access to the Embedded Service setup objects.
EmbeddedServiceDetail.label: Embedded Service

EmbeddedServiceFieldService.description: Represents a setup node for creating an embedded Appointment Management (beta) deployment.

EmbeddedServiceFlow.description: Represents a Flow Definition used by an Embedded Service deployment.
EmbeddedServiceFlow.label: Embedded Service Flow

EmbeddedServiceFlowConfig.description: Represents whether an Embedded Service Flow feature is enabled or not.
EmbeddedServiceFlowConfig.label: Embedded Service Flow Configuration

EmbeddedServiceLabel.description: Represents a customized label in Embedded Chat or embedded Appointment Management.
EmbeddedServiceLabel.label: Embedded Service Label

EmbeddedServiceLiveAgent.description: Represents a setup node for creating an Embedded Chat deployment.
EmbeddedServiceLiveAgent.label: Embedded Service Deployment for Chat

EmbeddedServiceMenuItem.description: Represents the information needed to configure a Channel Menu item.
EmbeddedServiceMenuItem.label: Channel Menu Item

EmbeddedServiceMenuSettings.description: Represents a setup node for creating a channel menu deployment. Channel menus list the ways in which customers can contact your business.
EmbeddedServiceMenuSettings.label: Channel Menu Deployment

EmbeddedServiceResource.description: Represents a mapping from an EmbeddedServiceCustomization record parent to a set of resources. Each resource is a set of customizations applied via an uploaded static resource for your Embedded Chat.
EmbeddedServiceResource.label: Embedded Service Resource

EmissionsActivity.description: Represents a company’s emission generating activities and the greenhouse gas categories that are used to aggregate emissions for these activities.
EmissionsActivity.label: Emissions Activity

EmissionsAllocation.description: Represents information about the emissions from a child or partner account that are allocated to an account.
EmissionsAllocation.label: Emissions Allocation

EmissionsForecastFact.description: Represents information about the time periods, measures, and dimensions used to forecast the emissions of a company. The emissions forecast of the company is generated based on its business measures such as revenue or employee count, and the actual emissions data from previous years.
EmissionsForecastFact.label: Emissions Forecast Fact

EmpBenefitSummary.description: Represents statistics about benefits provided to employees and the usage of benefits.
EmpBenefitSummary.label: Employment Benefit Summary

EmpUserProvisionProcessErr.description: Represents an employee-user provisioning process error.
EmpUserProvisionProcessErr.label: Employee User Provisioning Process Error

Employee.description: Represents an employee within a company or organization.

Employee2.description: Represents an employee within a company or an organization.

EmployeeCrisisAssessment.description: Represents a crisis assessment of an Employee.

EmployeeDemographicSum.description: Represents statistics about employees based on their demographic information, such as employee count by age group, by gender, and by region.
EmployeeDemographicSum.label: Employee Demographic Summary

EmployeeDevelopmentSum.description: Represents statistics about training and development provided to upskill the employees.
EmployeeDevelopmentSum.label: Employee Development Summary

Employment.description: Represents the details of an individual's employment with an organization.

EmploymentCompensationSummary.description: Represents information about stakeholder engagement to assess the importance of environmental, social, and governance (ESG) issues for them.
EmploymentCompensationSummary.label: Employment Compensation Summary

EmploymentOffer.description: Represents an employment offer for a selected candidate.

EmploymentOfferVettingEval.description: Represents a junction between an employment offer and a vetting evaluation of the offer recipient.

EmssnRdctnCommitment.description: Represents information about a company's commitment to reducing its carbon emissions. This commitment is in line with the Paris Agreement’s goal to achieve a low-carbon future. For example, companies sign the Business Ambition for 1.5°C commitment letter and commit to set emission reduction targets to limit temperature rise to 1.5°C above pre-industrial levels.
EmssnRdctnCommitment.label: Emissions Reduction Commitment

EmssnReductionTarget.description: Represents information about the science-based or non-science-based target set by a company to fulfill its emissions reduction commitment. This target indicates the company’s emissions reduction goal. A company’s emissions reduction goal could be to reduce carbon emissions or increase renewable energy for reaching a target metric tonnes of CO2e (tCO2e) within a specific timeframe.
EmssnReductionTarget.label: Emissions Reduction Target

EnablementMeasureDefinition.description: Represents an Enablement measure, which specifies the job-related activity that a user performs to complete a milestone or outcome in an Enablement program. A measure identifies a source object and optional related objects, with optional field filters and filter logic, for tracking the activity. This object also represents Enablement measure information in Metadata API.
EnablementMeasureDefinition.label: Enablement Measure

EnablementProgram.description: Represents an Enablement program, which includes exercises and measurable milestones to help users such as sales reps achieve specific outcomes related to your company’s revenue goals.
EnablementProgram.label: Enablement Program

EnablementProgramDefinition.description: Represents Enablement program information in Metadata API.

EnblMeasureObjectDefinition.description: Represents the criteria for an object that tracks the job-related activity for an Enablement measure in an Enablement program. A separate EnblMeasureObjectDefinition is used for a measure's source object and each optional related object.

EnblPgmTaskMeasureProgress.description: Represents a user’s progress through the object and field requirements that an Enablement measure defines for an outcome or milestone in an Enablement program.
EnblPgmTaskMeasureProgress.label: Enablement Program Task Measure Progress

EnblProgramSection.description: Represents an optional section in an Enablement program. A section can include other program items, such as milestones and exercises.
EnblProgramSection.label: Enablement Program Section

EnblProgramTaskDefinition.description: Represents an outcome, a milestone, or an exercise in an Enablement program. A program task is also known as a program item.
EnblProgramTaskDefinition.label: Enablement Program Task Definition

EnblProgramTaskMeasure.description: Represents the connection between an Enablement measure and a specific milestone or outcome in an Enablement program.
EnblProgramTaskMeasure.label: Enablement Program Task Measure

EnblProgramTaskProgress.description: Represents a user’s progress towards completing an outcome, a milestone, or an exercise in an Enablement program.
EnblProgramTaskProgress.label: Enablement Program Task Progress

EnblProgramTaskSubCategory.description: Represents a custom exercise type that an Enablement admin adds to an Enablement program in Program Builder. A custom exercise type also requires a corresponding EnblProgramTaskDefinition record for Program Builder and corresponding LearningItem and LearningItemType records for when users take the exercise in the Guidance Center.
EnblProgramTaskSubCategory.label: Enablement Program Task Sub Category

EnergyAttrCertCredit.description: Represents information about the energy attribute certificate credits related to energy attribute certificate purchase.
EnergyAttrCertCredit.label: Energy Attribute Certificate Credit

EnergyAttrCertPurchase.description: Represents information about the purchase of energy attribute certificates from the clean energy project supplier. The information includes terms of engagement and the delivery type of energy attribute certificate.
EnergyAttrCertPurchase.label: Energy Attribute Certificate Purchase

EnergyAttrCreditDstr.description: Represents a junction between energy attribute credits and stationary asset energy use indicating the quantity of credits distributed for a specific energy use.
EnergyAttrCreditDstr.label: Energy Attribute Credit Distribution

EnergyServiceAgreement.description: The services or commodities purchased by a customer, for a specified product and optionally linked to a Contract. Contracted Services can be physical goods (eg. appliances), commodity services (eg. electricity, gas or water) or other miscellaneous services (eg. homeowner insurance, boiler maintenance contract).

EnergyServiceAgreementItem.description: Represents the details of the Energy Service Agreement object such as the time, location, and pricing information.

EngagementChannelType.description: Represents a channel through which a customer can be reached for communication. The Engagement Channel Type object supports only the English language.
EngagementChannelType.label: Engagement Channel Type

EngagementChannelWorkType.description: Represents the relationship between an Engagement Channel Type object and a Work Type object for Salesforce Scheduler.
EngagementChannelWorkType.label: Engagement Channel Work Type

EnhancedLetterhead.description: Represents an enhanced letterhead that can be associated with a Lightning email template that doesn’t use the Salesforce Merge Language (SML).
EnhancedLetterhead.label: Enhanced Letterhead

EnrichedField.description: Represents a field selected for Change Data Capture Enrichment for a channel and channel member. A non-empty enriched field is added to an update or delete change event even when not changed. Available in API version 51.0 and later.
EnrichedField.label: Platform Event Enrichment Field

EnrollmentEligibilityCriteria.description: Represents criteria that define patient enrollment eligibility for one or more care programs.
EnrollmentEligibilityCriteria.label: Enrollment Eligibility Criteria

Entitlement.description: Represents the customer support an account or contact is eligible to receive.
Entitlement.label: Entitlement

EntitlementContact.description: Represents a Contact eligible to receive customer support via an Entitlement.
EntitlementContact.label: Entitlement Contact

EntitlementTemplate.description: Represents predefined terms of customer support for a product (Product2).
EntitlementTemplate.label: Entitlement Template

EntityDefinition.description: Provides row-based access to metadata about standard and custom objects.
EntityDefinition.label: Entity Definition

EntityHistory.description: Represents historical information about an object’s changed field values.

EntityLimit.description: Represents the limits for an object as displayed in the Setup UI.
EntityLimit.label: Entity Limit

EntityMilestone.description: Represents a required step in a customer support process on a work order. The Salesforce user interface uses the term “object milestone.
EntityMilestone.label: Object Milestone

EntityParticle.description: Represents each element of a field that can be presented in a user interface. Contrast EntityParticle with FieldDefinition, which represents each element of a field defined in the Metadata API
EntityParticle.label: Entity Particle

EntitySubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a record or another user.
EntitySubscription.label: Entity Subscription

EnvironmentHubMember.description: Represents a member organization in the Environment Hub.

EnvironmentalRisk.description: Represents information about the risk that the environmental resources create for an organization.
EnvironmentalRisk.label: Environmental Risk

Event.description: Represents an event in the calendar. In the user interface, event and task records are collectively referred to as activities.

EventBusSubscriber.description: Represents a trigger, process, or flow that’s subscribed to a platform event or a change data capture event. Doesn’t include CometD or Pub/Sub API subscribers.
EventBusSubscriber.label: Platform Event Subscription

EventRelation.description: Represents a person (a user, lead, or contact) or a resource (such as a conference room) invited to an event. This object lets you add or remove invitees from an event and use the API to manage invitees’ responses to invitations. If Shared Activities is enabled, EventRelation can also represent other objects that are related to an event. EventRelation does not support triggers, workflow, or data validation rules.
EventRelation.label: Event Relation

EventRelayConfig.description: Represents the configuration of an event relay, which relays platform events and change data capture events from Salesforce to Amazon EventBridge.
EventRelayConfig.label: Event Relay Config

EventRelayFeedback.description: Represents execution state information about an event relay from Salesforce to Amazon EventBridge for platform events and change data capture events. Query this object to get information such as the event relay status and any error message.
EventRelayFeedback.label: Event Relay Feedback

EventTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with an Event.

EventWhoRelation.description: Represents the relationship between an event and a lead or contacts. This derived object is a filtered version of the EventRelation object; that is, IsParent is true and IsWhat is false. It doesn’t represent relationships to invitees or to accounts, opportunities, or other objects.

Examination.description: Represents information about the authorized examinations that qualify a license or permit.

Expense.description: Represents an expense linked to a work order. Service resource technicians can log expenses, such as tools or travel costs.
Expense.label: Expense

ExpenseReport.description: Represents a report that summarizes expenses.
ExpenseReport.label: Expense Report

ExpenseReportEntry.description: Represents an entry in an expense report.
ExpenseReportEntry.label: Expense Report Entry

ExplainabilityActionDef.description: Represents the explainability definition of the explainability action log that's generated by the associated application's action.
ExplainabilityActionDef.label: Explainability Action Definition

ExplainabilityActionVersion.description: Represents the explainability action version of the explainability action log that's generated by the associated application's action.
ExplainabilityActionVersion.label: Explainability Action Version

ExplainabilityMsgTemplate.description: Represents the template that contains the decision explanation message for a specified element type.
ExplainabilityMsgTemplate.label: Explainability Message Template

ExplainabilityMsgTemplateLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of the message in an explainability message template for an expression set step element.
ExplainabilityMsgTemplateLocalization.label: Translation

ExpressionFilter.description: Represents a logical expression that’s used to control the execution of macro instructions.
ExpressionFilter.label: Expression Filter

ExpressionFilterCriteria.description: Represents a condition in an expression that’s used to control the execution of macro instructions.
ExpressionFilterCriteria.label: Expression Filter Criteria

ExpressionSet.description: Represents information about an expression set. An expression set performs a series of calculations using lookups and user-defined variables and constants.
ExpressionSet.label: Expression Set

ExpressionSetConstraintObj.description: Represents the association between a Product object and the constraint model tags defined in a given constraint model.

ExpressionSetDefinition.description: Represents information about an expression set definition.
ExpressionSetDefinition.label: Expression Set Definition

ExpressionSetDefinitionContextDefinition.description: Represents a relationship between an expression set definition and a context definition. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.
ExpressionSetDefinitionContextDefinition.label: Expression Set Context Definition

ExpressionSetDefinitionVersion.description: Represents information about an expression set definition version.
ExpressionSetDefinitionVersion.label: Expression Set Definition Version

ExpressionSetMessageToken.description: Represents a token that's used in an explainability message template. The token can be replaced with an expression set version resource that the template is used in.
ExpressionSetMessageToken.label: Expression Set Message Token

ExpressionSetObjectAlias.description: Represents the alias of the source object that's used in an expression set.
ExpressionSetObjectAlias.label: Expression Set Object Alias

ExpressionSetVersion.description: Represents information about a specific version of an expression set. This object is also accessible through the UI API, which enables its use in components like Lightning Web Components (LWC).
ExpressionSetVersion.label: Expression Set Version

ExpressionSetView.description: Represents a virtual object that provides a consolidated view of file-based expression set. File-based expression sets are read-only templates. To be able to modify file-based expression sets, you must clone them first.
ExpressionSetView.label: Expression Set Template

ExpsSetObjectAliasFieldVw.description: Represents the virtual object that provides a consolidated view of source object and its alias, and the source object fields and their aliases that are used in an expression set. This object is used to check the permission level required to access the underlying object fields associated with their field aliases.
ExpsSetObjectAliasFieldVw.label: Expression Set Object Alias Field View

ExtDataShare.description: Represents a data share, which is a collection of Data Cloud objects that can be shared with other Data Cloud orgs or third-party partners.
ExtDataShare.label: Data Share

ExtKnowledgeConnector.description: Represents a connector to a third-party knowledge source for Unified Knowledge.

External Cross-Org Callout Event Type.description: External Cross-Org Callout events represent external data callouts via the cross-org adapter for Salesforce Connect.

External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.file: objects/E/External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.json
External Custom Apex Callout Event Type.description: External Custom Apex Callout events represent external data callouts via custom adapters for Salesforce Connect.

External Data Source Callout Event Type.file: objects/E/External Data Source Callout Event Type.json
External Data Source Callout Event Type.description: External Data Source Callout events represent external data callouts via the Salesforce Connect adapters for Amazon DynamoDB and Amazon Athena.

External OData Callout Event Type.description: External OData Callout events represent external data callouts via the OData 2.0 and OData 4.0 adapters for Salesforce Connect.

ExternalAccountHierarchy.description: Represents the external account hierarchy, which works like a role-based hierarchy. Use ExternalAccountHierarchy to allow partner and customer users to share data with other external accounts in their hierarchy.
ExternalAccountHierarchy.label: External Account Hierarchy

ExternalAccountHierarchyHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to values in the fields of an external account hierarchy.
ExternalAccountHierarchyHistory.label: External Account Hierarchy History

ExternalAuthIdentityProvider.description: Represents an external authentication (auth) identity provider. An external auth identity provider links to an external credential and obtains OAuth tokens for outbound callouts to external systems.
ExternalAuthIdentityProvider.label: External Auth Identity Provider

ExternalCredential.description: Represents the details of how Salesforce authenticates to the external system.
ExternalCredential.label: External Credential

ExternalDataSource.description: Represents the metadata associated with an external data source. Create external data sources to manage connection details for integration with data and content that are stored outside your Salesforce org.
ExternalDataSource.label: External Data Source

ExternalDataSrcDescriptor.description: Contains the metadata information for the external schema of an external data source. Use the metadata to map attributes from an AWS data source, such as Amazon DynamoDB and Amazon Athena, to Salesforce external object fields. Also, use the metadata to customize the data retrieval queries to an AWS data source.
ExternalDataSrcDescriptor.label: External Data Source Descriptor

ExternalDataUserAuth.description: Stores authentication settings for a Salesforce user to access an external system. The external system must be defined in an external data source or a named credential that’s configured to use per-user authentication.
ExternalDataUserAuth.label: External Data User Authentication

ExternalDocStorageConfig.description: Represents configuration, which admin makes in setup to specify the drive, path, and named credential to be used for storing documents on external drives.
ExternalDocStorageConfig.label: External Document Storage Config

ExternalEncryptionRootKey.description: Represents metadata about root keys stored in third-party key stores that are used to generate and secure keys that encrypt Salesforce data.

ExternalEvent.description: Holds native iOS or Android calendar event details for the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.
ExternalEvent.label: External Event

ExternalEventMapping.description: Holds native iOS or Android calendar event details for the Salesforce Today feature in the Salesforce mobile app.
ExternalEventMapping.label: External Event Mapping

ExternalLearning.description: Represents information that defines a training that is made available by an external provider as a course, program, or on-site experience, for a contact.

ExternalLearningPtcpResult.description: Represents the outcome of a student's participation in an external learning.

ExternalServiceRegistration.description: Represents the External Service configuration for an org.
ExternalServiceRegistration.label: External Service Registration

ExternalSocialAccount.description: Represents a managed social media account on a social network such as Facebook or Twitter.
ExternalSocialAccount.label: Managed Social Account

ExternalStringLocalization.description: Represents the translation of custom labels for a UI component represented by the ExternalString object. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.
ExternalStringLocalization.label: Custom Label Translation

ExtlClntAppOauthPlcyCnfg.label: External Client App OAuth Policy Config

ExtlClntAppSamlPlcyCnfg.label: External Client App SAML Policy Configuration

ExtlPtcpRsltLrnrPgmRqmt.description: Represents a junction between the External Learning Participant Result and Learner Program Requirement objects.

ExtlRecShrCnct.description: Represents authentication data to make outbound calls to and inbound calls from an external system to publish events for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrCnctAccnt.description: Represents an association between an account and an external record share connection for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrField.description: Represents an imported, exported, or updated external record share field for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrFieldMap.description: Represents the external record share field mapping between the sender and receiver for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrLead.description: Represents the Lead record of a vendor org if you’re a partner. If you’re a vendor for Partner Connect, this object represents a partner org.

ExtlRecShrObject.description: Represents a shared object for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrOpportunity.description: Represents the opportunity for Partner Connect in the vendor org if you’re a partner and the partner org if you’re the vendor.

ExtlRecShrPcklstOptn.description: Represents a picklist option of an external record share picklist field shared between a partner and vendor for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrPicklistMap.description: Represents the external record share picklist field mapping between the partner and vendor system for Partner Connect.

ExtlRecShrRecordMap.description: Represents the lead or opportunity being mapped between a partner and vendor for Partner Connect.

FSL__Time_Dependency__c.description: Represents a dependency between two service appointments. This object is used to define scheduling relationships between two appointments. It allows you to determine the order and timing in which dependent appointments should be scheduled.

FeeScheduleDefinition.description: Stores fee schedule information for contracts of Standard Care Fee Agreement types.
FeeScheduleDefinition.label: Fee Schedule Definition

FeedAttachment.description: Represents an attachment to a feed item, such as a file attachment or a link. Use FeedAttachment to add various attachments to one feed item.
FeedAttachment.label: Feed Attachment

FeedComment.description: Represents a comment added to a feed by a user.
FeedComment.label: Feed Comment

FeedItem.description: FeedItem represents an entry in the feed, such as changes in a record feed, including text posts, link posts, and content posts.
FeedItem.label: Feed Item

FeedLike.description: Indicates that a user has liked a feed item.
FeedLike.label: Feed Like

FeedPollChoice.description: Shows the choices for a poll posted in the feed.
FeedPollChoice.label: Feed Poll Choice

FeedPollVote.description: Shows how users voted on a poll posted in the feed.
FeedPollVote.label: Feed Poll Vote

FeedPost.description: FeedPost represents the following types of changes in a record feed, such as AccountFeed: text posts, link posts, and content posts.

FeedRevision.description: Holds the revision history of a specific feed item or comment, including a list of attributes that changed for each revision.
FeedRevision.label: Feed Revision

FeedTrackedChange.description: Represents an individual field change or set of field changes. A FeedTrackedChange is a child object of a record feed, such as AccountFeed.
FeedTrackedChange.label: Feed Tracked Change

FieldChangeSnapshot.description: Use this virtual object to learn which opportunities' close dates changed during the specified time period.
FieldChangeSnapshot.label: Field Change Snapshot

FieldDefinition.description: Represents a standard or custom field, providing row-based access to field metadata. Contrast FieldDefinition with EntityParticle, which represents each element of a field that can be presented in a user interface. FieldDefinition has parity with metadata type Field.
FieldDefinition.label: Field Definition

FieldHistoryArchive.description: Represents field history values for all objects that retain field history. FieldHistoryArchive is a big object, available only to users with the “Retain Field History” permission.
FieldHistoryArchive.label: Field History Archive

FieldMapping.description: Represents a mapping between fields in an object in the org and fields in a data service. A data service uses two separate field maps: one controls how the data service matches records in an object, and the other controls how the data service adds or updates data for an existing record.
FieldMapping.label: Field Mapping

FieldMappingField.description: Represents a field in an object in the org that maps to a field in a data service.
FieldMappingField.label: Field Mapping Field

FieldMappingRow.description: Represents a field in a data service record that maps to a field in an object record in the org.
FieldMappingRow.label: Field Mapping Row

FieldPermissions.description: Represents the enabled field permissions for the parent PermissionSet.
FieldPermissions.label: Field Permissions

FieldRestrictionRule.description: Represents a field visibility rule that controls whether a field is visible to a user, based on the field’s inclusion in the PersonalInfo_EPIM field set. If Enhanced Personal Information Management setting was enabled before Spring ’22, field visibility is based on the field’s compliance categorization.
FieldRestrictionRule.label: Field Restriction Rule

FieldSecurityClassification.description: Represents a field’s data sensitivity value selected from the SecurityClassification picklist.
FieldSecurityClassification.label: Field Security Classification

FieldServiceMobileSettings.description: Represents a configuration of settings that control the Field Service iOS and Android mobile app experience.
FieldServiceMobileSettings.label: Field Service Mobile Settings

FieldServiceOrgSettings.description: Represents the org settings for Field Service, such as Appointment Assistant settings.
FieldServiceOrgSettings.label: Field Service Org Settings

FileSearchActivity.description: Represents search activity on a file.
FileSearchActivity.label: FileSearchActivity

FinAssetPortfolioTgtAlloc.description: Stores target asset allocation for a financial account, person account, or household.
FinAssetPortfolioTgtAlloc.label: Financial Asset Portfolio Target Allocation

FinServ AccountContactRelation Custom Fi.description: Represents the relationship between an individual (specifically the contact part of the individual) and the household (account) that the individual is a member of. AccountContactRelation is a standard object that is available through the Shared Contacts feature. Custom fields extend the AccountContactRelation standard object for use in Financial Services Cloud.

FinServ AuthorizationForm Custom Fields.description: Represents the specific version and effective dates of a form that is associated with consent, such as a privacy policy or terms and conditions.

FinServ AuthorizationFormConsent Custom.description: Represents the date and way in which a user consented to an authorization form.

FinServ AuthorizationFormText Custom Fie.description: Represents an authorization form’s text and language settings.

FinServ_AccountAccountRelation__c.description: Represents a relationship between two accounts, such as between a household and a business account.

FinServ_Alert__c.description: Represents notifications to alert advisors about their client accounts.

FinServ_AssetsAndLiabilities__c.description: Represents assets or liabilities that are not represented in a client's financial accounts, such as real estate or collectibles.

FinServ_BillingStatement__c.description: Represents a billing statement for an individual’s financial account.

FinServ_Card__c.description: Represents credit or debit card associated with this financial account.

FinServ_ChargesAndFees__c.description: Represents agreed-to fees and charges for servicing an individual’s financial account.

FinServ_ContactContactRelation__c.description: Represents the relationship between any two individuals.

FinServ_Employment__c.description: Represents information about an individual’s employment history.

FinServ_FinancialAccountRole__c.description: Represents the role occupied by a person or organizational entity that is involved with a financial account, such as a beneficiary or trustee.

FinServ_FinancialAccountTransaction__c.description: Represents information about a single financial account transaction.

FinServ_FinancialAccount__c.description: Represents a financial account such as an investment account, bank account, or insurance policy.

FinServ_FinancialGoal__c.description: This Financial Goal object is installed in your Financial Services Cloud Salesforce org when you install the Financial Services Cloud Managed Package. It represents a client’s financial goal, such as college funds or a major purchase.

FinServ_FinancialHolding__c.description: Represents a financial holding in an investment account, such as shares of stock.

FinServ_IdentificationDocument__c.description: Represents information about documents used to verify an individual’s identity.

FinServ_LifeEvent__c.description: Represents a client’s life event, such as a birth or marriage.

FinServ_PolicyPaymentMethod__c.description: Represents the premium payment method for a policy, such as credit card, debit card, or internet banking.

FinServ_ReciprocalRole__c.description: Represents the other entity’s corresponding role in a one-to-one relationship between entities.

FinServ_Revenue__c.description: Represents data from Financial Services Cloud and external systems to aggregate revenue streams for an advisor’s book of business.

FinServ_Securities__c.description: Represents a security, such as a stock or bond.

FinancialAccount.description: Represents a financing option, such as an automotive loan or lease related to a customer.
FinancialAccount.label: Financial Account

FinancialAccountAddress.description: Represents an address related to a financial account.
FinancialAccountAddress.label: Financial Account Address

FinancialAccountBalance.description: Represents the details about a financial account balance.
FinancialAccountBalance.label: Financial Account Balance

FinancialAccountFee.description: Represents the charges levied on a financial account
FinancialAccountFee.label: Financial Account Fee

FinancialAccountMilestone.description: Represents the events in the lifecycle of a financial account.
FinancialAccountMilestone.label: Financial Account Milestone

FinancialAccountParty.description: Represents the relationship between an account or a contact and a financial account.
FinancialAccountParty.label: Financial Account Party

FinancialAccountStatement.description: Represents a periodic statement summary for a financial account.
FinancialAccountStatement.label: Financial Account Statement

FinancialAccountTransaction.description: Represents a single transaction related to a loan or a lease.
FinancialAccountTransaction.label: Financial Account Transaction

FinancialDeal.description: Represents the deal that the financial institution is working on.

FinancialDealAsset.description: Represents the assets included in the financial deal.

FinancialDealBid.description: Represents the bids placed by financial deal parties in the financial deal.

FinancialDealInteraction.description: Represents a junction between an interaction and a financial deal.

FinancialDealParticipant.description: Represents the user or the group with whom the deal is shared.

FinancialDealParty.description: Represents the parties, such as partners and competitors, that are involved in the deal.

FinancialDealProduct.description: Represents the products (services) offered by the bank in the deal.

FinancialGoal.description: This Financial Goal object is a standard Salesforce object. It represents a financial goal for a person account.
FinancialGoal.label: Financial Goal

FinancialGoalFunding.description: The financial goal of an individual or person account that requires funding.
FinancialGoalFunding.label: Financial Goal Funding

FinancialGoalParty.description: Represents a junction between the financial goal and the person account.
FinancialGoalParty.label: Financial Goal Party

FinancialPlan.description: Represents a financial plan for a person account.
FinancialPlan.label: Financial Plan

FinclAcctPtyFinclAsset.description: Represents the financial account associated with the financial asset for a specific account or contact.
FinclAcctPtyFinclAsset.label: Financial Account Party Financial Asset

FinclDealInteractionSummary.description: Represents a junction between an interaction summary and a financial deal.

FiscalYearSettings.description: Settings to define a custom or standard fiscal year for your organization. This object has a parent-child relationship with the Period object.
FiscalYearSettings.label: Fiscal Year Settings

FldSvcObjChg.description: Represents a change made to one of a service appointment’s tracked fields.
FldSvcObjChg.label: Field Service Object Change

FldSvcObjChgDtl.description: Represents the details of a change made to one of a service appointment’s tracked fields.
FldSvcObjChgDtl.label: Field Service Object Change Detail

Fleet.description: Represents a group of assets used in commercial, service, or transport operations in the manufacturing industry.

FleetAsset.description: Represents the relationship between an asset and the fleet to which it belongs.

FleetParticipant.description: Represents the relationship between a fleet and a participant, such as an account, a contact, or a user.

FlexQueueItem.description: Represents an asynchronous Apex job in the Apex flex queue. Provides information about the job type and flex queue position of the AsyncApexJob.
FlexQueueItem.label: Flex Queue Item

FlowDefinitionView.description: Represents the description of a flow definition.
FlowDefinitionView.label: Flow Definition

FlowElementTestCoverage.label: Flow Element Test Coverage Record (Relates a Flow Element's developer name to a Flow Coverage Record, eg: myAssignment)

FlowInterview.description: Represents a flow interview. A flow interview is a running instance of a flow. This object is available in API version 32.0 and later.
FlowInterview.label: Flow Interview

FlowInterviewLog.description: Represents the logs of a screen flow interview. An interview is an instance of a running or previously run flow.
FlowInterviewLog.label: Flow Interview Log

FlowInterviewLogEntry.description: Represents the log of a specific element that’s executed by a screen flow interview. An interview is an instance of a running or previously run flow.
FlowInterviewLogEntry.label: Flow Interview Log Entry

FlowInterviewLogOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a FlowInterviewLog with users other than the owner.
FlowInterviewLogOwnerSharingRule.label: Flow Interview Log Owner Rule

FlowInterviewOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a FlowInterview with users other than the owner.
FlowInterviewOwnerSharingRule.label: Flow Interview Owner Rule

FlowInterviewShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a FlowInterview.
FlowInterviewShare.label: Flow Interview Share

FlowNavMetricEventLog.description: Flow Navigation Metric event logs contain metric data for flow interviews such as total execution time, number of interviews, and number of errors.

FlowOrchestration.description: Represents the details of an orchestration definition.
FlowOrchestration.label: Orchestration

FlowOrchestrationInstRelaObj.description: Represents a junction between a flow orchestration instance and a related object.

FlowOrchestrationInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of an orchestration.
FlowOrchestrationInstance.label: Orchestration Run

FlowOrchestrationLog.description: Represents logging data for a FlowOrchestrationInstance.
FlowOrchestrationLog.label: Orchestration Run Log

FlowOrchestrationStageInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of a stage in a run-time instance of an orchestration.
FlowOrchestrationStageInstance.label: Orchestration Stage Run

FlowOrchestrationStepInstance.description: Represents a run-time instance of a step in a run-time instance of a stage of a run-time instance of an orchestration.
FlowOrchestrationStepInstance.label: Orchestration Step Run

FlowOrchestrationVersion.description: Represents the version of an orchestration.
FlowOrchestrationVersion.label: Orchestration Version

FlowOrchestrationWorkItem.description: Represents a work item associated with a run-time instance of an interactive step in a run-time instance of an orchestration.
FlowOrchestrationWorkItem.label: Orchestration Work Item

FlowRecord.description: Represents the details of a flow. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.
FlowRecord.label: Flow

FlowRecordElement.description: Represents a single element within a flow version. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.
FlowRecordElement.label: Flow Element

FlowRecordElementOccurrence.description: Represents the execution metrics for a single element within a flow version.
FlowRecordElementOccurrence.label: Flow Record Element Occurrence

FlowRecordRelation.description: Represents a relationship between a record and a flow interview. When a flow interview is paused, Salesforce uses the $Flow.CurrentRecord global variable in the flow to associate the interview with a record.
FlowRecordRelation.label: Flow Record Relation

FlowRecordVersion.description: Represents the version of a flow. This object is available in API version 58.0 and later.
FlowRecordVersion.label: Flow Version

FlowRecordVersionOccurrence.description: Represents an instance of a recurring flow that runs on a schedule.
FlowRecordVersionOccurrence.label: Flow Version Occurrence

FlowStageRelation.description: Represents a relationship between a paused flow interview and its stages. When a flow interview is paused, Salesforce creates a FlowStageRelation record for each stage that’s set to the $Flow.CurrentStage or $Flow.ActiveStages global variable.
FlowStageRelation.label: Flow Interview Stage Relation

FlowTest.description: Represents the description of a flow test associated with a flow definition.
FlowTest.label: Flow Test

FlowTestCoverage.label: Flow Test Coverage Record (Relates a test method to flow version eg: MyTestClass.myTestMethod called MyFlow version 2)

FlowTestResult.description: This object is reserved for internal use.
FlowTestResult.label: Flow Test Result

FlowTestView.description: Represents the description of a flow test associated with a flow definition.
FlowTestView.label: Flow Test View

FlowVariableView.description: Represents a variable within the flow version.
FlowVariableView.label: Flow Variable

FlowVersionView.description: Represents the version of a flow definition.
FlowVersionView.label: Flow Version

Folder.description: Represents a repository for a Dashboard, Document, EmailTemplate, Macro, QuickText, or Report. Only one type of item can be contained in a folder.
Folder.label: Folder

FolderedContentDocument.description: Represents the relationship between a parent and child ContentFolderItem in a ContentWorkspace.
FolderedContentDocument.label: Foldered Content Document

ForecastingAdjustment.description: This object represents an individual forecast manager’s adjustment for a subordinate’s or child territory’s forecast via a ForecastingItem.
ForecastingAdjustment.label: Forecasting Adjustment

ForecastingColumnDefinitionLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a custom calculated column or custom reference data column label when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.
ForecastingColumnDefinitionLocalization.label: Translation

ForecastingCustomCategory.description: Represents a custom forecasting category used for forecast rollups.

ForecastingCustomData.description: Represents forecast data from external sources to display in the forecasts page. For example, risk or last year’s revenue.
ForecastingCustomData.label: Forecasting Custom Data

ForecastingFact.description: This object is read-only and links a ForecastingItem with its opportunities, such as opportunities that share the same owner or forecast category and have a closing date within the period of the forecasting item.
ForecastingFact.label: Forecasting Fact

ForecastingFilter.description: Represents the custom filter for including or excluding data from opportunity forecasts.
ForecastingFilter.label: Forecasting Filter

ForecastingFilterCondition.description: Represents the custom filter condition logic for including or excluding data from opportunity forecasts.
ForecastingFilterCondition.label: Forecasting Filter Condition

ForecastingGroup.description: Represents groups used to roll up forecast totals on the forecasts page.
ForecastingGroup.label: Forecasting Group

ForecastingGroupItem.description: Represents the value within the picklist that is specified as the forecasting group for a forecast type. For example, if you have a forecasting group that identifies the industry an opportunity is part of, this object represents the value in the the industry picklist that’s chosen to be part of the group.
ForecastingGroupItem.label: Forecasting Group Item

ForecastingItem.description: This object is read-only used for individual forecast amounts. Users see amounts based on their perspectives and forecast roles.
ForecastingItem.label: Forecasting Item

ForecastingOwnerAdjustment.description: This object represents an individual forecast user’s adjustment of their own forecast, including territory forecasts they own, via a ForecastingItem.
ForecastingOwnerAdjustment.label: Forecasting Owner Adjustment

ForecastingQuota.description: This object represents an individual user’s or territory’s quota for a specified time period.
ForecastingQuota.label: Forecasting Quota

ForecastingShare.description: Represents forecasts shared between a forecast manager and a user.
ForecastingShare.label: Forecasting Share

ForecastingSourceDefinition.description: Represents the object, measure, date type, and hierarchy that a forecast uses to project sales.
ForecastingSourceDefinition.label: Forecasting Source Definition

ForecastingSrcRecJudgment.description: Represents forecast managers’ judgment of whether they consider an opportunity-related deal to be certain to close.

ForecastingSubmissionItem.description: Represents the values for each forecast category in a submitted forecast.

ForecastingTypeSource.description: Represents the mapping of a forecasting source definition to a forecast type.
ForecastingTypeSource.label: Forecasting Type Source

ForecastingUserPreference.description: Represents the forecasting selections that a user has made, such as display options, date range, forecasting type, and currency.
ForecastingUserPreference.label: Forecasting User Preference

FormulaFunctionCategory.description: Represents the category to which a formula belongs when building a formula.
FormulaFunctionCategory.label: Formula Function Category

FrcstCustmCatgRampRateSrc.description: Represents the total contract value used for custom bulk adjustments.

FrcstCustmzAdjustment.description: Represents an individual forecast manager’s adjustment of a subordinate’s consumption forecast.

FrcstCustmzOwnerAdjustment.description: Represents an individual forecast user’s adjustment of their own consumption forecast.

Frequently Occurring Fields.description: In addition to system fields, these fields are found on many objects.

FrgtHaulingEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 freight hauling.
FrgtHaulingEmssnFctr.label: Freight Hauling Emissions Factor

FrgtHaulingEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to freight hauling.
FrgtHaulingEnrgyUse.label: Freight Hauling Energy Use

FuelType.description: Represents information about the additional fuel types defined by a customer.
FuelType.label: Fuel Type

FuelTypeSustnUom.description: Represents a mapping between the additional fuel types and their corresponding unit of measure values defined by a customer.
FuelTypeSustnUom.label: Fuel Type Sustainability Unit of Measure

FulfillmentAsset.description: Represents an instance of a technical product used to provide a customer asset.

FulfillmentAssetAttribute.description: Represents an attribute of a fulfillment asset.

FulfillmentAssetRelationship.description: Represents a relationship between two fulfillment assets.

FulfillmentFalloutRule.description: Represents the fulfillment fallout handling rule.

FulfillmentLineAttribute.description: Represents an attribute of a fulfillment order line.

FulfillmentLineRel.description: Represents a relationship between two fulfillment order lines.

FulfillmentLineSourceRel.description: Represents the relationship between a fulfillment order line and its decomposition source.

FulfillmentOrder.description: Represents a group of products, fees, and delivery charges on a single order that share the same fulfillment location, delivery method, and recipient. The FulfillmentOrderLineItems belonging to a FulfillmentOrder are associated with OrderItemSummary objects belonging to a single OrderSummary.
FulfillmentOrder.label: Fulfillment Order

FulfillmentOrderItemAdjustment.description: Represents a price adjustment on a FulfillmentOrderLineItem. Corresponds to an OrderItemAdjustmentLineSummary associated with the corresponding OrderItemSummary.
FulfillmentOrderItemAdjustment.label: Fulfillment Order Item Adjustment

FulfillmentOrderItemTax.description: Represents the tax on a FulfillmentOrderLineItem or FulfillmentOrderItemAdjustment. Corresponds to an OrderItemTaxLineItemSummary.
FulfillmentOrderItemTax.label: Fulfillment Order Item Tax

FulfillmentOrderLineItem.description: Represents a product or delivery charge belonging to a FulfillmentOrder. Corresponds to an OrderItemSummary.
FulfillmentOrderLineItem.label: Fulfillment Order Product

FulfillmentPlan.description: Represents a set of steps to be created to fulfill the order.

FulfillmentStep.description: Represents a task that's required to perform a certain action as part of order fulfillment. This task can be manual or automated.

FulfillmentStepDefinition.description: Represents a definition of a step that must be executed during fulfillment orchestration.

FulfillmentStepDefinitionGroup.description: Represents a set of fulfillment step definitions.

FulfillmentStepDependency.description: Represents a dependency between tasks by defining the order between a task and one that depends on it.

FulfillmentStepDependencyDef.description: Represents a dependency that must be created between two fulfillment step records.

FulfillmentStepJeopardyRule.description: Represents the duration and tolerance for the step in the fulfillment process to allow the overall tracking of rules and risks.

FulfillmentStepSource.description: Represents a link between a fulfillment step and the corresponding order lines.

FulfillmentTaskAssignmentRule.description: Represents a set of actions that assign a task to a user or queue.

FulfillmentWorkspace.description: Represents a visual designer for fulfillment plans that can have multiple step groups and their dependencies.

FulfillmentWorkspaceItem.description: Represents information about the attributes that are used in the definition for a fulfillment step group.

FunctionConnection.description: Represents a connection between an org and Salesforce Functions.

FunctionInvocationRequest.description: Represents invocation information for a Salesforce Function.

FunctionReference.description: Represents a deployed Salesforce Function associated with an org.

FundingAward.description: Represents an award given to an individual or organization to facilitate a goal related to the funder’s mission. This object is available in API version 57.0 and later.

FundingAwardAmendment.description: Represents a modification to the scope or finances of a previously approved award. This object is available in API version 57.0 and later.

FundingAwardParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a funding award.

FundingAwardRequirement.description: Represents a deliverable or milestone for a funding award or funding disbursement. This object is available in API version 57.0 and later.

FundingAwardRqmtSection.description: Represents a part of a funding award requirement to be completed or reviewed.

FundingOppParticipant.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a funding opportunity.

FundingOpportunity.description: The pool of money available for distribution for a specific purpose. This object is available in API version 57.0 and later.

GameDefinition.description: Represents information about a game that the loyalty program offers to its members.
GameDefinition.label: Game Definition

GameParticipant.description: Represents a junction between a game definition and a participant who is either an account, a contact, or a loyalty program member.
GameParticipant.label: Game Participant

GameParticipantReward.description: Represents the reward that’s provided to a participant after they’ve played a game.
GameParticipantReward.label: Game Participant Reward

GameReward.description: The reward that’s offered to participants of a game.
GameReward.label: Game Reward

GenAIConversationSummary.description: Represents a generated summary of a voice or video call.

GenAiPlannerDefinition.description: Represents an agent planner service that uses a large language model (LLM) and a reasoning strategy to decompose a given task into smaller subtasks, identify the most suitable actions for each subtask, and invoke them.
GenAiPlannerDefinition.label: Generative AI Planner Definition

GenAiPlannerFunctionDef.description: Represents a relationship between the agent planner service and agent actions.
GenAiPlannerFunctionDef.label: Generative AI Planner Function Definition

GenAiPlannerRuleExprObject.label: Generative AI Planner Rule Expression Object

GenAiPluginDefinition.description: Represents an agent topic, which is a category of actions related to a particular job to be done by AI agents.
GenAiPluginDefinition.label: Generative AI Plugin Definition

GeneralLdgrAcctPrdSummary.description: Represents a junction between a general ledger account and a legal entity accounting period. Stores information about the total credit amount, total debit amount, opening balance, and closing balance of a general ledger account for a specific legal entity accounting period.

GeneralLedgerJrnlEntryRule.description: Represents information about the transaction journal entry rule, based on which transaction journals are created for the selected credit and debit general ledger accounts, transaction amount field, and percentage.

GeneratedWaste.description: Represents the information on the waste generated in operations, the waste generated while treating end-of-life products that were sold, and so on.
GeneratedWaste.label: Generated Waste

GenericVisitTask.description: Represents information about a task that can be performed during a visit.
GenericVisitTask.label: Generic Visit Task

GenericVisitTaskContext.description: Represents the context or purpose for a generic visit task.
GenericVisitTaskContext.label: Generic Visit Task Context

GeolocationBasedAction.description: Represents a geolocation-based action, which is an action that’s triggered when a user enters, exits, or is within the area of the associated object.
GeolocationBasedAction.label: Geolocation Based Action

GiftCommitmentSchedule.description: Represents the schedule for fulfilling the commitment.

GnrcVstKeyPerformanceInd.description: Represents the key performance indicators that can be recorded while performing a task during a visit. You can compare the expected and actual metric values with the key performance indicator records.
GnrcVstKeyPerformanceInd.label: Generic Visit Key Performance Indicator

GnrcVstTaskContextRelation.description: Represents common attributes used for a visit task and a visit task context.
GnrcVstTaskContextRelation.label: Generic Visit Task Context Relation

Goal.description: The Goal object represents the components of a goal such as its name, description, and status.

GoalAssignment.description: Represents the assignment of a goal.
GoalAssignment.label: Goal Assignment

GoalAssignmentDetail.description: Represents additional information associated with a GoalAssignment record.
GoalAssignmentDetail.label: Goal Assignment Detail

GoalDefinition.description: Represents a goal or a business objective that’s used as a reference. When instantiated, GoalDefinition records create GoalAssignment records that serve as goals in care plans.
GoalDefinition.label: Goal Definition

GoalLink.description: Represents the relationship between two goals. This is a many-to-many relationship, meaning that each goal can link to many other goals.

GoogleDoc.description: Represents a link to a Google Document.

GovtFinancialAsstSum.description: Represents information about the financial assistance received from governments.
GovtFinancialAsstSum.label: Government Financial Assistance Summary

GroundTravelEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 ground travel.
GroundTravelEmssnFctr.label: Ground Travel Emissions Factor

GroundTravelEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to ground travel.
GroundTravelEnrgyUse.label: Ground Travel Energy Use

GroupCensus.description: Represents a snapshot of statistics about eligible members (employees or members) of a group (employer or association) and their legal dependents. Use this entity in quoting, rating, and the subsequent enrollment process. Child object of employer or group Account.
GroupCensus.label: Group Census

GroupCensusMember.description: Represents personal information about a member, for example employee or association member, or their dependents. GroupCensusMember is used to estimate the insurance plan cost for the group. This object is also used in the enrollment process to retrieve the member and dependent details. Child object of GroupCensus.
GroupCensusMember.label: Group Census Member

GroupCensusMemberPlan.description: Represents the association of GroupCensusMember and ContractGroupPlan. Use this entity when census data includes previous member enrollment plan details and new member plan details. You can populate GroupCensusMemberPlan by reading the enrollment census in the enrollment services before creating insurance policies.
GroupCensusMemberPlan.label: Group Census Member Plan

GroupClass.description: Represents the classification of group members that receive similar benefits. Example classes include executives, union, and office workers. Child object of employer or group Account.
GroupClass.label: Group Class

GroupClassContribution.description: Represents employer or group contributions for GroupClass members and their dependents on a per product category such as medical, dental, or vision. Child object of GroupClass.
GroupClassContribution.label: Group Class Contribution

GroupMember.description: Represents a User or Group that is a member of a public group.
GroupMember.label: Group Member

GroupMembershipEventLog.description: Group Membership events capture details about changes to public group and queue membership, such as when members are added to or removed from the public group or queue.

GtwyProvPaymentMethodType.description: Represents a type that allows integrators and payment providers to choose an active payment to receive an order's payment data rather than allowing the Salesforce Order Management platform to select a default payment method.
GtwyProvPaymentMethodType.label: Gateway Provider Payment Method Type

GuestBuyerProfile.description: Represents a store's guest buyer profile, which allows unauthenticated buyers to browse the store.
GuestBuyerProfile.label: Guest Buyer Profile

HealthCareDiagnosis.description: Represents information related to industry-standard healthcare diagnosis codes. Before the Spring ’21 release, the Healthcare Procedure and Healthcare Diagnosis objects stored codes specifically related to procedures and diagnoses. These codes were used for prior-authorization requests and approval processes. Since the Spring’21 release, Health Cloud uses the Code Set and Code Set Bundle objects for this purpose instead.
HealthCareDiagnosis.label: Healthcare Diagnosis

HealthCareProcedure.description: Represents information related to industry-standard healthcare procedure codes. Before the Spring ’21 release, the Healthcare Procedure and Healthcare Diagnosis objects stored codes specifically related to procedures and diagnoses. These codes were used for prior-authorization requests and approval processes. Since the Spring’21 release, Health Cloud uses the Code Set and Code Set Bundle objects for this purpose instead.
HealthCareProcedure.label: Healthcare Procedure

HealthScore.description: Represents a subject’s score for a specific score category.

HealthScoreActionLog.description: Represents the log of actions triggered from the Dynamic Actions for Unified Health Scoring component in the Unified Health Scoring feature.

HealthcareFacilityNetwork.description: Represents a junction object identifying the insurance network that a location or business entity is a part of. Network participation records are also stored in this object.
HealthcareFacilityNetwork.label: Healthcare Facility Network

HealthcarePayerNetwork.description: Represents an insurance network group. For example, an insurance company’s exclusive provider organization (EPO) plans.
HealthcarePayerNetwork.label: Healthcare Payer Network

HealthcarePractitionerFacility.description: Represents the different locations in which a practitioner provides services.
HealthcarePractitionerFacility.label: Healthcare Practitioner Facility

HealthcareProvider.description: Represents business-level details about the healthcare organization or the practitioner.
HealthcareProvider.label: Healthcare Provider

HealthcareProviderNpi.description: Represents identifiers from the National Provider Identifier that are assigned to every facility and licensed practitioner in the United States. Also includes NPI assigned date, primary mailing address on file, and so on.
HealthcareProviderNpi.label: Healthcare Provider NPI

HealthcareProviderService.description: Represents a junction object between a HealthcareService and a HealthcareProvider or HealthcareFacility or HealthcarePractitionerFacility.
HealthcareProviderService.label: Healthcare Provider Service

HealthcareProviderSpecialty.description: Represents specialties for a practitioner or a service provider organization. A provider can have multiple specialties such as anesthesiology and cardiovascular.
HealthcareProviderSpecialty.label: Healthcare Provider Specialty

HealthcareProviderTaxonomy.description: Represents taxonomy or subspecialty codes for a practitioner or facility. A provider or facility can have multiple taxonomies.
HealthcareProviderTaxonomy.label: Healthcare Provider Taxonomy

HealthcareServiceDetail.description: Represents a junction object between a CareService and a CodeSetBundle.
HealthcareServiceDetail.label: Healthcare Service Detail

HeapDump.description: A complex type that represents a heap dump in an ApexExecutionOverlayResult object.

HierCondHlthCodeMapping.description: Represents how Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) codes map to condition codes for a specific year.
HierCondHlthCodeMapping.label: Hierarchical Condition Health Code Mapping

HierCondHlthRskAdjFctr.description: Stores the risk adjustment factor for patients and members based on the set of Hierarchical Condition Category (HCC) codes that apply to them and the status of their benefits eligibility.
HierCondHlthRskAdjFctr.label: Hierarchical Condition Health Risk Adjustment Factor

HlthCareProvTreatedCondition.description: Represents a junction object between a healthcare provider, facility, or practitioner and a problem definition that's related to a health condition, such as disease or illness.
HlthCareProvTreatedCondition.label: Healthcare Provider Treated Condition

Holiday.description: Represents a period during which a service resource is unavailable for appointment scheduling. Recurring holidays are not supported in Automotive Cloud.
Holiday.label: Holiday

HotelStayEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 hotel stay.
HotelStayEmssnFctr.label: Hotel Stay Emissions Factor

HotelStayEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to hotel stay.
HotelStayEnrgyUse.label: Hotel Stay Energy Use

IPAddressRange.description: Represents a range of IP addresses to include in or exclude from the specified feature.
IPAddressRange.label: IP Address Range

IconDefinition.description: Represents an icon, such as used for a tab.
IconDefinition.label: Icon Definition

Idea.description: Represents an idea on which users are allowed to comment and vote, for example, a suggestion for an enhancement to an existing product or process.
Idea.label: Idea

IdeaComment.description: Represents a comment that a user has submitted in response to an idea.
IdeaComment.label: Idea Comment

IdeaReputation.description: Represents a collection of statistics and scores derived from a user’s activity within an Ideas zone or internal organization.

IdeaReputationLevel.description: Represents a reputation level within an Ideas zone or internal organization and is used by the system to calculate reputation. You can create up to 25 levels per zone or internal organization.

IdeaTheme.description: Represents an invitation to zone members to submit ideas that are focused on a specific topic.

IdentityDocument.description: Represents information about documents used to identify Financial Services Cloud clients.
IdentityDocument.label: Identity Document

IdentityVerificationProcDef.description: Represents the definition of the identity verification process.
IdentityVerificationProcDef.label: Identity Verification Process Definition

IdentityVerificationProcDtl.description: Used to configure the search function as well as the minimum number of verifiers for the identity verification process.
IdentityVerificationProcDtl.label: Identity Verification Process Detail

IdentityVerificationProcFld.description: Used to configure the questions or criteria for verifying the identity of a caller.
IdentityVerificationProcFld.label: Identity Verification Process Field

IdpEventLog.description: Represents the Identity Provider Event Log. This log records both problems and successes with inbound SAML or OpenID Connect authentication requests from another app provider. It also records outbound SAML responses when Salesforce is acting as an identity provider.
IdpEventLog.label: Identity Provider Event Log

IframeWhiteListUrl.description: Represents a list of trusted external domains that you allow to frame your Embedded Service, Surveys, and Visualforce pages.
IframeWhiteListUrl.label: Trusted Domain for Inline Frames

Image.description: Represents the details of an image.
Image.label: Image

ImpactRiskOpportunity.description: Represents an impact, risk, or opportunity that can be evaluated and scored as a part of an organization's double-materiality assessment. Also known as an IRO.

ImpactRiskOpportunityScore.description: Represents the score of an impact, risk, or opportunity for an assessment.
