ProviderSearchSyncLog.label: Provider Search Sync Log

PublicComplaint.description: Represents the complaints submitted by public users. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.
PublicComplaint.label: Public Complaint

PulseCheck.description: Represents the wellbeing of a learner based on a primary metric or criteria at a specific date and time.

PulseCheckTemplate.description: Represents a common template used to create Pulse Check records.

PurchaseQuantityRule.description: Represents a rule that restricts the quantity of a product that can be purchased. The rule can be an increment, minimum, or maximum rule.
PurchaseQuantityRule.label: Quantity Rule

PurchaserPlan.description: Represents the payer plan that a purchaser makes available to its members and members’ dependents.
PurchaserPlan.label: Purchaser Plan

PurchaserPlanAssn.description: Represents a junction object that associates the purchaser to the plans they offer to members.
PurchaserPlanAssn.label: Purchaser Plan Association

PushTopic.description: Represents a query that is the basis for notifying Streaming API clients of changes to records in an org.
PushTopic.label: Push Topic

PymtSchdDistributionMethod.description: Represents information about the partial payments that the total payment is divided into.

Question.description: Represents a question in a zone that users can view and reply to.

QuestionDataCategorySelection.description: A data category selection represents a data category that classifies a question.

QuestionReportAbuse.description: Represents a user-reported abuse on a Question in a Chatter Answers zone.

QuestionSubscription.description: Represents a subscription for a user following a Question.

QueueRoutingConfig.description: Represents configuration settings that determine how work items are routed to agents. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.
QueueRoutingConfig.label: Routing Configuration

QueueSobject.description: Represents the mapping between a queue Group and the types associated with the queue, including custom objects.
QueueSobject.label: Queue sObject

Queued Execution Event Type.description: Queued Execution events contain details about queued executions—for example, batch Apex.

QueuedExecutionEventLog.description: Queued Execution events contain details about queued executions—for example, batch Apex.

QuickActionDefinition.description: Represents the definition of a quick action.
QuickActionDefinition.label: Action

QuickActionList.description: Represents a list of quick actions.
QuickActionList.label: Action List

QuickActionListItem.description: Represents an item in a quick action list.
QuickActionListItem.label: Action List Item

QuickText.description: This object stores a snippet of text that allows users to send a quick response to a customer. Use quick text to create greetings, answers to common questions, short notes, and more.
QuickText.label: Quick Text

QuickTextUsage.description: Represents the usage of quick text on a record, including which quick text was used, who used it, and how they used it.
QuickTextUsage.label: Quick Text Usage

QuotLineItmUsageRsrcPlcy.description: Represents the policies that are used for the usage resource that's associated with the usage product added in the quote line item.

QuotLineItmUseRsrcGrant.description: Represents the negotiated grants for the usage resource that's associated with the usage product added in the quote line item.

Quote.description: Represents a quote, which is a record showing proposed prices for products and services.
Quote.label: Quote

QuoteAction.description: Indicates the type of sales transaction that’s being quoted; for example, a renewal sale.

QuoteAdjustmentGroup.description: Group containing a set of adjustments applied to a quote.

QuoteDocument.description: Represents a quote in document format.
QuoteDocument.label: Quote PDF

QuoteItemTaxItem.description: The tax that is applied to a quote line item.
QuoteItemTaxItem.label: Quote Item Tax Item

QuoteLineDetail.description: Represents the breakdown details of a quote line item. Revenue Cloud generates these records to capture pricing and quantity changes, such as negative quantity reductions, early renewals, derived pricing or repricing during an amendment, and bundle or product attribute reconfigurations.

QuoteLineGroup.description: Stores the group information for line items in a quote. It also stores the aggregated line field information (subtotal). It contains a parent-child relationship to quote.

QuoteLineItem.description: Represents a quote line item, which is a member of the list of Product2 products associated with a Quote, along with other information about those line items on that quote.
QuoteLineItem.label: Quote Line Item

QuoteLineItemAttribute.description: Represents a virtual object that stores an attribute specified for a quote line item.

QuoteLineItemGroupClass.description: Represents the association of a Quote Line Item to GroupClass. Use this entity for large group quoting process when multiple group classes are attributed on a single quote line item. Child object of Quote.
QuoteLineItemGroupClass.label: Quote Line Item Group Class

QuoteLineItemRecipient.description: Represents a site, employee, or other entity for which services are being quoted. This could include details such as the recipient's name, contact information, associated site or location, and any specific requirements or preferences for the quoted services.
QuoteLineItemRecipient.label: Quote Line Item Recipient

QuoteLineItemRelatedObject.description: Represents the junction between a Quote Line Item and a related object. The values of the attributes from the related object are referenced by the relevant product attributes on the Quote LIne Item
QuoteLineItemRelatedObject.label: Quote Line Item Related Object

QuoteLinePriceAdjustment.description: Indicates the calculated price adjustment that is applied to the quote line, for example, a calculated volume discount or the prorated value of a manual discount. Use the quote line price adjustment to inform potential customers about the type, value, and total amount of their discounts.
QuoteLinePriceAdjustment.label: Quote Line Price Adjustment

QuoteLineRateAdjustment.description: Represents the negotiated rate adjustment for a quote line item.

QuoteLineRateCardEntry.description: Represents the catalog and negotiated rates of a usage resource associated with a quote line item that's used to charge overage consumption.

QuoteLineRelationship.description: Describes the relationship between quote line items, such as items in a bundle.
QuoteLineRelationship.label: Quote Line Relationship

QuoteLineWorkSource.description: Represents an association between a quote and work sources, such as assets, quote line items, order products, or work type groups.
QuoteLineWorkSource.label: Quote Line Work Source

QuoteRecipientGroup.description: Represents a recipient group for which offers or products with the same configuration are being added. This also includes reusing these groups to add or remove recipients.
QuoteRecipientGroup.label: Quote Recipient Group

QuoteRecipientGroupMember.description: Represents a junction between a quote line item recipient and a quote recipient group.
QuoteRecipientGroupMember.label: Quote Recipient Group Member

QuoteSaveEvent.description: Notifies subscribers that the process started by the Place Quote or Place Sales Transaction API request is complete. If the process is successful, use this event to learn about the updated quote. If the request isn't successful, use this event to learn about the errors and how to fix them.

QuoteToOrderCompletedEvent.description: Notifies subscribers when the /actions/standard/createOrderFromQuote REST request is complete. If the request is successful, use this event to learn about the Order record. If the request isn’t successful, use this event to learn about the errors associated with the request.

REST API Event Type.description: REST API events contain details about REST-specific requests.

RateAdjustmentByAttribute.description: Represents the adjustments that determine the rate of a resource based on its rate-impacting attributes. These attributes are linked to the usage product record. Rates are then influenced by conditions specified in the Attribute Based Adjustment Condition object. Finally, the charge rate is determined by using the Attribute Based Adjustment Rule object.

RateAdjustmentByTier.description: Represents the adjustments for the rate of a resource that’s determined based on the specified tiers. This object stores information about the type of adjustment used, the value of the adjustment type, and any applicable boundaries.

RateCard.description: Represents the rules used to rate the consumption of a group of resources within a product. Usage of a resource is billed at a specified rate if the user consumes more than their allowance for a time period.

RateCardEntry.description: Represents a rule that determines the charge rate for using a product's resource. Each entry is linked to one rate card exclusively, and its activation or deactivation can be controlled by assigning effective dates.

RatingFrequencyPolicy.description: Represents the policy that defines the frequency at which rating is triggered for the ratable summary records.

RatingRequest.description: Represents the common run-time parameters, such as context definition and rating procedure for a set of records in the rateable summary table.

RatingRequestBatchJob.description: Represents a junction between the rating request and batch job objects.

RebateClaim.description: Represents proof of sale of a vehicle submitted by a dealer in the form of a retail delivery report. This report can also be used for rebate payout calculations.

RecAlrtDataSrcExpSetDef.description: Represents information about the data source for a record alert and the association with an expression set definition.
RecAlrtDataSrcExpSetDef.label: Record Alert Data Source Expression Set Definition

ReceivedDocument.description: Contains a request for an operation to be performed on a document, such as rotating, splitting, or text extraction.
ReceivedDocument.label: Received Document

ReceivedDocumentType.description: Represents a junction object between Received Document and Document Type.
ReceivedDocumentType.label: Received Document Type

RecentFieldChange.description: Use this virtual object to see how an opportunity has changed in the past seven days. Learn the previous value of a field, who made the change, and when the change was made.
RecentFieldChange.label: Recent Field Change

RecentlyViewed.description: Represents metadata entities typically found in Setup such as page layout definitions, workflow rule definitions, and email templates that the current user has recently viewed.
RecentlyViewed.label: Recently Viewed

Recommendation.description: Represents the recommendations surfaced as offers and actions for Einstein Next Best Action.
Recommendation.label: Recommendation

RecommendationResponse.description: Represents the user responses to a presented offer or recommendation for Einstein Next Best Action. This object is available in API version 51.0 and later.
RecommendationResponse.label: Recommendation Response

RecordAction.description: Represents a relationship between a record and an action, such as a flow. Create a RecordAction for every action that you want to associate with a particular record.
RecordAction.label: RecordAction

RecordActionHistory.description: Represents the lifecycle of a RecordAction as it goes through different states.
RecordActionHistory.label: RecordActionHistory

RecordAggregationDefinition.description: Represents a data aggregation from one object to another object to which it is connected by other objects in the data model.
RecordAggregationDefinition.label: Record Aggregation Definition

RecordAggregationJoinCondition.description: Represents a condition in a join between two record aggregation objects.
RecordAggregationJoinCondition.label: Record Aggregation Join Condition

RecordAggregationObject.description: Represents an object in the record aggegation join sequence.
RecordAggregationObject.label: Record Aggregation Object

RecordAggregationObjectFilter.description: Represents a filter that is applied to the records of an object in the record aggregation join sequence.
RecordAggregationObjectFilter.label: Record Aggregation Object Filter

RecordAggregationResult.description: Represents a data aggregation from one record to another record based on the record aggregation definition for the corresponding objects.
RecordAggregationResult.label: Record Aggregation Result

RecordAlert.description: Represents an alert message about a specific record and tracks the status and active period of the alert.
RecordAlert.label: Record Alert

RecordAlertActionableTarget.description: Represents the action associated with the parent record alert.
RecordAlertActionableTarget.label: Record Alert Actionable Target

RecordAlertCategory.description: Represents a category to group and present record alerts.
RecordAlertCategory.label: Record Alert Category

RecordAlertCategoryLocalization.description: Represents the translated label of a RecordAlertCategory metadata type.
RecordAlertCategoryLocalization.label: Translation

RecordAlertDataSource.description: Represents an internal or external source for record alert data.
RecordAlertDataSource.label: Record Alert Data Source

RecordAlertDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a RecordAlert record’s fields.
RecordAlertDataTranslation.label: Record Alert Translation

RecordAlertTemplate.description: A template that is shown in the Alerts FlexCard when the expression set requirements are met.
RecordAlertTemplate.label: Record Alert Template

RecordTypeLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a label for a record type when the Translation Workbench is enabled for your organization.
RecordTypeLocalization.label: Translation

RecordVisibility (Pilot).description: Represents the visibility attributes that determine a record’s read access.

RecordsetFilterCriteria.description: Represents a set of filters that can be used to match service appointments or assets based on your criteria fields.
RecordsetFilterCriteria.label: Recordset Filter Criteria

RecordsetFilterCriteriaRule.description: Represents a rule using fields from the designated source object to create filters on the filtered, or target, object.
RecordsetFilterCriteriaRule.label: Recordset Filter Criteria Rule

RecordsetFltrCritMonitor.description: Monitors whether the value of an asset attribute is within the threshold of a recordset filter criteria (RFC).
RecordsetFltrCritMonitor.label: Recordset Filter Criteria Monitor

RecruitmentContentSection.description: Represents the content that you want to include in a section of a recruitment posting.

RecruitmentPostingCntntSect.description: Represents a junction between a recruitment posting and a recruitment content section.

RecruitmentRequisition.description: Represents a formal request to recruit for a position or a provider vacancy.

RecruitmentRequisitionLoc.description: Represents a junction between recruitment requisition and location

RecruitmentRequisitionPtcp.description: Represents information about a user or group of participants who have access to a recruitment requisition.

RecurrenceSchedule.description: Represents the recurrence schedule for a benefit schedule.
RecurrenceSchedule.label: Recurrence Schedule

RedirectWhitelistUrl.description: Represents a trusted URL for external user redirections.
RedirectWhitelistUrl.label: Allow URL for Redirects

ReferenceDataLoadLog.description: Represents information about the history of loading reference data for emissions factors.
ReferenceDataLoadLog.label: Reference Data Load Log

Referral.description: Represents the information on client referrals in an organization.

RefrigerantEmssnFctr.description: Represents the global warming potential values for individual refrigerants. Global warming potential compares the atmospheric radiative forcing of one molecule of refrigerant to that of carbon dioxide.
RefrigerantEmssnFctr.label: Refrigerant Emissions Factor

Refund.description: Represents a refund made against a payment.
Refund.label: Refund

RefundLinePayment.description: A refund line that has been applied to a payment.
RefundLinePayment.label: Refund Line Payment

RegAuthorizationTypeProduct.description: Represents the association of authorization type and product.

RegisteredExternalService.description: Represents a registered external service used to provide an extension or integration.
RegisteredExternalService.label: Registered External Service

RegulatoryAuthority.description: Represents an organization or government agency that provides authorization. This object is available in API version 49.0 and later.

RegulatoryAuthorizationType.description: Represents the authorization issued by the regulatory body.

RegulatoryCode.description: Represents the regulation code enforced by the regulatory body.

RegulatoryCodeUse.description: Represents a junction between a set of assessment questions and the regulatory code associated with them.

RegulatoryCodeViolation.description: Represents the transactional violation data that has been identified during an inspection.

RegulatoryTrxnFee.description: Represents the association of regulatory transaction fees with your applications, inspections, or violations.

RegulatoryTrxnFeeItem.description: Represents the storage of specific fee items associated with your regulatory transaction fees.

RelatedListColumnDefinition.description: Represents information about a column in a related list. A related list specifies a set of records for a related object, based on specific criteria.
RelatedListColumnDefinition.label: Related List Column Definition

RelatedListDefinition.description: Represents information about a related list. A related list specifies a set of records for a related object, based on specific criteria.
RelatedListDefinition.label: Related List Definition

RelatedRecordAssocCriteria.description: Defines criteria for automatically linking records like accounts, leads, opportunities, and cases with the branches that work with them.
RelatedRecordAssocCriteria.label: Related Record Association Criteria

RelationshipGraphDefinition.description: Represents a definition of a graph that you can configure in your organization to traverse object hierarchies and record details, giving you a glimpse of how your business works.
RelationshipGraphDefinition.label: Relationship Graph Definition

RemoteKeyCalloutEvent.description: The documentation has moved to RemoteKeyCalloutEvent in the Platform Events Developer Guide.

RentalCarEmssnFctr.description: Represents the emissions factors for scope 3 rental car usage.
RentalCarEmssnFctr.label: Rental Car Emissions Factor

RentalCarEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to rental cars.
RentalCarEnrgyUse.label: Rental Car Energy Use

Reply.description: Represents a reply that a user has submitted to a question in an answers zone.

ReplyEmailSettings.description: Represents a reply mail management configuration, which is used to configure emails that are received by an email sending domain.
ReplyEmailSettings.label: Generic Reply Email Setting Result

ReplyReportAbuse.description: Represents a user-reported abuse on a Reply in a Chatter Answers zone.

ReplyText.description: A text reply generated by Einstein Reply Recommendations that is based on closed chat transcripts. Admins review replies and publish them to quick text, editing them as needed. Einstein recommends relevant published replies to support agents in the Lightning Service Console, and agents can insert replies into chats or messaging sessions.

Report.description: Represents a report, a set of data that meets certain criteria, displayed in an organized way. Access is read-only.
Report.label: Report

Report Event Type.description: Report events contain information about what happened when a user ran a report. This event type includes all activity that's in the Report Export event type, plus more. For example, it has user activity for reports exported as both Formatted Report and Details Only output.

Report Export Event Type.description: Report Export events contain details about reports that a user exported. For example, this event type captures when a user exports a report as Details Only output. But it doesn’t capture reports that users export as Formatted Report or XLSX Detail output. For that data, see the Report event type.

ReportEventLog.description: Report event logs contain information about what happened when a user ran a report. This event type includes all activity that's in the Report Export event type, and additional information. For example, it has user activity for reports exported as both Formatted Report and Details Only output.

ReportExportEventLog.description: Report Export events contain details about reports that a user exported. For example, this event type captures when a user exports a report as Details Only output. But it doesn’t capture reports that users export as Formatted Report or XLSX Detail output. For that data, see the Report event type.

ReportTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Report.

ReputationLevel.description: Represents a reputation level defined for an Experience Cloud site.
ReputationLevel.label: Reputation Level

ReputationLevelLocalization.description: Represents the translated value of a reputation level. Reputation level localization only applies for reputation levels in Experience Cloud sites.
ReputationLevelLocalization.label: Translation

ReputationPointsRule.description: Represents the reputation point rules for an Experience Cloud site. Each rule specifies an action that members can earn points from and the points associated with those actions in a particular site.
ReputationPointsRule.label: Reputation Points Rule

ResidentialLoanApplication.description: Represents details about a loan application from the lender.
ResidentialLoanApplication.label: Residential Loan Application

ResourceAbsence.description: Fields associated with a time period in which a service resource is unavailable to work in Field Service.
ResourceAbsence.label: Resource Absence

ResourcePreference.description: Represents an account’s preference for a specified service resource on field service work.
ResourcePreference.label: Resource Preference

RestApiEventLog.description: REST API event logs contain details about REST-specific requests.

RestrictionRule.description: Represents a restriction rule or a scoping rule. A restriction rule has EnforcementType set to Restrict and controls the access that specified users have to designated records. A scoping rule has EnforcementType set to Scoping and controls the default records that your users see without restricting access.
RestrictionRule.label: Restriction Rule

RetailLocationGroup.description: Group retail stores based on shared features, such as size, location, part of a retail chain.

RetailStore.description: Create records for physical retail stores associated to business accounts.

RetailStoreGroupAssignment.description: Represents a junction between a retail store and a retail store group.

RetailStoreKpi.description: Map store groups to assessment indicator definition, products, and in-store location categories and define targets. Targets are the expected compliance values for each assessment indicator definition, which is a parameter based on which markers of compliance are decided for a task.

RetailVisitKpi.description: Capture the actual information during a visit against the defined assessment indicator definition and target values.

RetrievalSummaryDefField.description: Represents a table that stores the fields to retrieve from the target object of a rollup definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefField.label: Retrieval Summary Definition Field

RetrievalSummaryDefObject.description: Represents a table that stores the rollup definitions of a retrieval definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefObject.label: Retrieval Summary Definition Object

RetrievalSummaryDefinition.description: Represents a table that stores the header information of a retrieval definition.
RetrievalSummaryDefinition.label: Retrieval Summary Definition

ReturnOrder.description: Represents the repair, return, or recall of product items.
ReturnOrder.label: Return Order

ReturnOrderItemAdjustment.description: Represents a price adjustment on a return order line item.
ReturnOrderItemAdjustment.label: Return Order Item Adjustment

ReturnOrderItemTax.description: Represents the tax on a return order line item or return order item adjustment.
ReturnOrderItemTax.label: Return Order Item Tax

ReturnOrderLineItem.description: Represents a product that is returned, recalled, or repaired as part of a return order.
ReturnOrderLineItem.label: Return Order Line Item

ReturnOrderOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a return order with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
ReturnOrderOwnerSharingRule.label: Return Order Owner Rule

RevenueAsyncOperation.description: Represents the status of an asynchronous process initiated by a REST request in Subscription Management.
RevenueAsyncOperation.label: Revenue Async Operation

RevenueSourceCategoryConfig.description: Represents the Revenue Data Source-related stage information and the revenue metric that you want to measure and track.

RevenueSourceObjectConfig.description: Represents data from the underlying Salesforce standard or custom object that stores opportunity and product-related information.

RevenueTransactionErrorLog.description: Represents the details of errors that occurred during the processing of a request. The error record persists until a new error with the same category, primary record, and, if necessary, related record occurs.

RgltyCodeRegClauseVer.description: Represents a junction between Regulatory Code and Regulation Clause Version objects.

RgltyCodeViolRegClVer.description: Represents a junction between Regulatory Code Violation and Regulation Clause Version objects.

RuleTerritory2Association.description: Represents a record-assignment rule and its association to an object, such as Account. Available if Sales Territories has been enabled.
RuleTerritory2Association.label: Rule Territory Association

SOAP API Event Type.description: SOAP API events contain details about your org's SOAP API request activity.

SOQLResult.description: A complex type that represents the result of a SOQL query in an ApexExecutionOverlayResult object.

SOSDeployment.description: Represents the general settings for deploying SOS video call capability in a native mobile application.
SOSDeployment.label: SOS Deployment

SOSSession.description: This object is automatically created for each SOS session and stores information about the session.
SOSSession.label: SOS Session

SOSSessionActivity.description: Captures information about specific events that occur during an SOS video call, such as when an SOS call begins or ends.
SOSSessionActivity.label: SOS Session Activity

SalesAIScoreCycle.description: Represents the cycle type and ID used to score records.
SalesAIScoreCycle.label: Sales AI Score Cycle

SalesAIScoreModelFactor.description: Represents the factors that Sales Cloud Einstein uses to build a scoring model. Scoring models are used by features, such as Opportunity Scoring, to score individual records.
SalesAIScoreModelFactor.label: Sales AI Score Model Factor

SalesAgreeProductAttribute.description: Represents a virtual object that stores the key-value pairs for attributes of sales agreement products.

SalesAgreement.description: Represents a long-term agreement between a buyer and a seller to negotiate price and volume of products.

SalesAgreementProdSchdAdj.description: Represents the manual adjustments made to metric values for a sales agreement product schedule.

SalesAgreementProduct.description: Represents the total quantity or amount and the default pricing information of a product or category across the total time period of the sales agreement.

SalesAgreementProductSchedule.description: Represents the quantity or amount and the pricing information of a product or category for a particular schedule of the sales agreement.

SalesChannel.description: Represents the origin of an order. For example, a web storefront, physical store, marketplace, or mobile app. If you integrate Salesforce Order Management with Salesforce B2C Commerce, set up a SalesChannel corresponding to each Site in your B2C Commerce implementation.
SalesChannel.label: Sales Channel

SalesContractLine.description: Stores a contract's product information, including price, quantity, and components covered.
SalesContractLine.label: Sales Contract Line

SalesStoreCatalog.description: Represents the catalog associated with a store.
SalesStoreCatalog.label: Sales Store Catalog

SalesTransactionFulfillReq.description: Represents the statuses of all the sub-orders that belong to the selected commercial or technical product.

SalesTransactionItemShape.description: Defines the business logic for a sales transaction shape item, for example, an item in an order.

SalesTransactionShape.description: Defines the business logic for a sales transaction; for example, an order, a quote, or a cart.

SalesTransactionType.description: Represents the type of the sales transaction.

SalesTrxnDeleteEvent.description: Represents the platform event that triggers the deletion of sales transaction fulfillment request records when the corresponding reference records are deleted.

SalesTrxnItemRelationShape.description: Describes the relationship between sales transaction shape items; for example, a bundle or set.

SalesTrxnItemRelationship.description: Describes the relationship between sales transaction items; for example, a bundle or set.

SalesWorkQueueSettings.description: Represents settings used to customize work queue options for third-party scoring. Third-party scoring enables custom number fields on person accounts, contacts, and leads. You must be a Sales Engagement customer to update this object. Previously, you could only use the Einstein Intelligence Score for third-party scoring.

Salesforce Surveys Object Model.description: Learn about how Salesforce Surveys objects relate to one another in Salesforce.

SalesforceContract.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App.

SalesforceInvoice.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about your organization’s invoices with Salesforce.

SalesforceLoginAsEventLog.description: Salesforce LoginAs Event provides details about the Salesforce User's login into Customer Org as Customer's authorized user.

SalesforcePayment.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about payments related to your organization’s Salesforce invoice.

SalesforceQuote.description: Read-only virtual object used in the Your Account App. Represents information about your organization’s quotes with Salesforce.

Sandbox Event Type.description: Sandbox events contain details about sandbox copies.

SandboxProcess.description: Represents the sandbox copy process for a SandboxInfo record.
SandboxProcess.label: Sandbox Process

SandboxStatusEventLog.description: SandboxStatusEventLog stores details about Sandbox copies.

SavedPaymentMethod.description: Represents a payment method saved by an authenticated customer.

SavedPaymentMethodEvent.description: Represents a saved payment method platform event. Subscribe to these events so you can listen and respond to them when they’re published. For example, create a Salesforce Flow that is triggered when one of these events is published.

ScheduleBrdcstApptResource.description: Represents a junction between a Schedule Broadcast Appointment and a Service Resource. This object represents the resources to whom a schedule broadcast is sent.
ScheduleBrdcstApptResource.label: Schedule Broadcast Appointment Resource

ScheduleBroadcast.description: Represents a broadcast of appointments that's sent to resources of specific service territories.
ScheduleBroadcast.label: Schedule Broadcast

ScheduleBroadcastAppointment.description: Represents appointments that schedulers broadcast to resources using a schedule broadcast.
ScheduleBroadcastAppointment.label: Schedule Broadcast Appointment

ScheduleBroadcastTerritory.description: Represent service territories to which a schedule broadcast is sent.
ScheduleBroadcastTerritory.label: Schedule Broadcast Territory

SchedulingAdherenceDetail.description: Represents the breakdown of daily shift adherence data by agent status.

SchedulingAdherenceSummary.description: Represents daily shift adherence data for a service resource in a service territory and job profile on a specific date.

SchedulingConstraint.description: Represents scheduling constraints on each service resource.
SchedulingConstraint.label: Scheduling Constraint

SchedulingObjective.description: Represents scheduling objective settings for Workforce Engagement.
SchedulingObjective.label: Scheduling Objective

SchedulingRule.description: Represents scheduling rule settings for Workforce Engagement.
SchedulingRule.label: Scheduling Rule

SchedulingRuleParameter.description: Represents scheduling rule parameters associated with a scheduling rule.
SchedulingRuleParameter.label: Scheduling Rule Parameter

ScontrolLocalization.description: The translated value of the field label for an s-control.
ScontrolLocalization.label: Scontrol Localization

Scope3CrbnFtprnt.description: Represents the total carbon emissions from scope 3 activities. Carbon footprint quantifies the effect of atmospheric warming, which is represented in metric tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e).
Scope3CrbnFtprnt.label: Scope 3 Carbon Footprint

Scope3EmssnSrc.description: Represents scope 3 activities that are the source of greenhouse gas emissions.
Scope3EmssnSrc.label: Scope 3 Emissions Source

Scope3PcmtItem.description: Represents the procurement (corporate spending) entry records. Procurement is considered as the amount that the organization spends on goods and services.
Scope3PcmtItem.label: Scope 3 Procurement Item

Scope3PcmtSummary.description: Represents the amount that the organization spends for an individual procurement category. Scope 3 procurement summary quantifies the effect on atmospheric warming, represented in tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e) by using a matched emission factor from an associated Procurement Emission Factor Item record.
Scope3PcmtSummary.label: Scope 3 Procurement Summary

ScoreCategory.description: Represents the categories that are scored in a unified health profile.
ScoreCategory.label: Score Category

ScoreCategoryCalcInsight.description: Represents how a score category in Unified Health Scoring is mapped to a calculated insight in Salesforce CDP. Use this object only if you use CDP to calculate scores for Unified Health Scoring.
ScoreCategoryCalcInsight.label: Score Category Calculated Insight

ScoreRangeClassification.description: Represents the different score ranges of a score category and how scores in those ranges are classified or interpreted.
ScoreRangeClassification.label: Score Range Classification

Scorecard.description: Use scorecards to measure partner performance and establish benchmarks for channel programs within Experience Cloud. Display any report summary results that your channel account manager or executive team wants to see.
Scorecard.label: Scorecard

ScorecardAssociation.description: Represents a connection between a specific scorecard and the associated account, channel program, or channel program level.
ScorecardAssociation.label: Scorecard Association

ScorecardMetric.description: Stores information about a Salesforce report that is run and summarized to get a single value. The stored value is added as a metric to the related Scorecard object.
ScorecardMetric.label: Scorecard Metric

ScratchOrgInfo.description: Represents a scratch org and its audit log. Use this object to create a scratch org and keep a log of its creation and deletion.

Search Click Event Type.description: Search Click events contain details about the user’s interaction with the search results in the search results page. Interactions with search results in the instant result dialog are not recorded by this event. All searches within the app, including Experience Cloud sites, are included. However, unauthenticated users won’t have a unique Salesforce user ID.

Search Event Type.description: Search events contain details about the user’s search query. All searches within the app, including Experience Cloud sites, are included. However, unauthenticated users won’t have a unique Salesforce user ID.

SearchActivity.description: Represents search activity on a Knowledge article. Also known as KnowledgeSearchActivity.
SearchActivity.label: SearchActivity

SearchClickEventLog.description: Search Click Event Log contains details about the user’s interaction with the search results.

SearchCriteriaConfiguration.description: Represents the configuration details of searchable field sets such as the group of fields used as the basis for search, aggregation, sort, and result display.

SearchEventLog.description: Search Event Log provides details about the user’s search query.

SearchPromotionRule.description: Represents a promoted search term, which is one or more keywords that you associate with a Salesforce Knowledge article. When a user’s search query includes these keywords, the associated article is returned first in search results.
SearchPromotionRule.label: Promoted Search Term

SearchResultActionConfig.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up the actions that a user can perform on results returned by criteria-based search.

SearchableObjDataSyncInfo.description: Represents information about the data synchronization for a search object, such as frequency of synchronization, status, and the date and time of the last synchronization.

SearchableReferenceDocument.description: Represents documents that are referenced to search for answers during documentation authoring, such as ESG disclosures.
SearchableReferenceDocument.label: Searchable Reference Document

SecuritiesHolding.description: Represents the securities associated with an insurance policy.
SecuritiesHolding.label: Securities Holding

SecurityCustomBaseline.description: Provides the ability to read, create, and delete user-defined custom security baselines, which define an org’s security standards.
SecurityCustomBaseline.label: Security Custom Baseline

SelfServiceUser.description: Represents a Contact who has been enabled to use your organization’s Self-Service portal, where he or she can obtain online support.

Seller.description: Represents the seller role of an individual with respect to a particular company or organization.
Seller.label: Seller

SenderEmailAddress.description: Represents a From address in a marketing email.
SenderEmailAddress.label: Sender Email Address

SeqPolicySelectionCondition.description: Represents the condition used to determine which sequence policy is applied to a record.

SequenceAssignedEvent.description: Represents the notification to customers about the assignment of a sequence to a target record. This process is initiated by the /sequences/actions/assign request.

SequenceGapReconciliation.description: Represents a missing sequence value identified during reconciliation, which can be used later to ensure there are no gaps in the sequence policy numbers.

SequencePolicy.description: Represents the configuration of rules and parameters for generating unique, sequential numbers for records. Stores settings such as numbering patterns, prefixes, suffixes, sequence start numbers, increment values, and filter criteria to ensure accurate and compliant numbering.

SerializedProduct.description: Records serial numbers for each product in an inventory.
SerializedProduct.label: Serialized Product

SerializedProductTransaction.description: Represents a change in the state of a serialized product.
SerializedProductTransaction.label: Serialized Product Transaction

ServiceAppointment.description: Represents a service appointment booked through Automotive Scheduler, for test drives or vehicle services.
ServiceAppointment.label: Service Appointment

ServiceAppointmentAsset.description: Represents a junction between Service Appointment and Asset. This junction object enables admins to associate a patient appointment to an asset such as a piece of medical equipment.

ServiceAppointmentAttendee.description: Represents a Lead, Contact, or Person Account who is associated with the Service Appointment of type Group.
ServiceAppointmentAttendee.label: Service Appointment Attendee

ServiceAppointmentEvent.description: Notifies subscribers of the service appointment details that are generated from the event platform.
ServiceAppointmentEvent.label: Service Appointment Event

ServiceAppointmentGroup.description: Stores information about a group of related service appointments.

ServiceAppointmentStatus.description: Represents a possible status of a service appointment in field service.
ServiceAppointmentStatus.label: Service Appointment Status Value

ServiceChannel.description: Represents a channel for work items that are received from your customers. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.
ServiceChannel.label: Service Channel

ServiceChannelFieldPriority.description: Represents a secondary routing priority field-value mapping.
ServiceChannelFieldPriority.label: Service Channel Field Priority

ServiceChannelStatus.description: Represents the status that’s associated with a specific service channel.
ServiceChannelStatus.label: Service Channel Status

ServiceChannelStatusField.description: Represents the values that you use to indicate completed and in-progress work item status for the status field in the Status-Based Capacity routing model.

ServiceContract.description: Represents a customer support contract (business agreement).
ServiceContract.label: Service Contract

ServiceContractOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a ServiceContract (customer service agreement) with users other than the owner.
ServiceContractOwnerSharingRule.label: Service Contract Owner Rule

ServiceCrew.description: Represents a group of service resources who can be assigned to service appointments as a unit.
ServiceCrew.label: Service Crew

ServiceCrewMember.description: Represents a technician service resource that belongs to a service crew.
ServiceCrewMember.label: Service Crew Member

ServiceCrewOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a service crew with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
ServiceCrewOwnerSharingRule.label: Service Crew Owner Rule

ServiceInfoRequestDetail.description: Represents additional details about a service information request, such as the detail type and detail code.

ServiceInfoRequestOperation.description: Represents the system operation performed for a service information request such as a session launch or a questionnaire package operation.

ServiceInfoRespOvrideOpt.description: Represents the possible reasons for overriding a service information response.

ServiceInfoRespResourceUrl.description: Represents the URLs of resources relevant to a service information response.

ServiceInfoRespSuggestion.description: Represents suggestions in a service information response. For example, suggesting a change in medication dosage.

ServiceInfoResponseAction.description: Represents actions to be performed as suggested by a service information response.

ServiceInfoResponseCoverage.description: Represents coverage details about a service information response. For example, if additional information or documentation is required for the coverage to be provided.

ServiceInfoRqstOpOutcome.description: Represents the outcome of a service information request operation.

ServiceInformationRequest.description: Represents information about a service information request, such as the date and time when the request was submitted and the type of service requested.

ServiceInformationResponse.description: Represents a response to a service information request.

ServicePoint.description: Represents an entry point for services to a premises. The service provided to each service point is separately metered (or measured). Useful for energy services including electricity, water and gas services.

ServicePresenceStatus.description: Represents a presence status that can be assigned to a service channel. This object is available in API version 65.0 and later.
ServicePresenceStatus.label: Service Presence Status

ServiceReport.description: Represents a report that summarizes a work order, work order line item, or service appointment.
ServiceReport.label: Service Report

ServiceReportLayout.description: Represents a service report template in field service.
ServiceReportLayout.label: Service Report Layout

ServiceResource.description: Represents a service technician or service crew in Field Service and Salesforce Scheduler, or an agent in Workforce Engagement.
ServiceResource.label: Service Resource

ServiceResourceCapacity.description: Represents the maximum number of scheduled hours or number of service appointments that a capacity-based service resource can complete within a specific time period.
ServiceResourceCapacity.label: Resource Capacity

ServiceResourceCapacityHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a service resource capacity record.
ServiceResourceCapacityHistory.label: Resource Capacity History

ServiceResourceCostRule.description: Represents the rules that calculate the value of a meal or equivalent gifts awarded to the field service worker.

ServiceResourceDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a ServiceResource record’s fields.
ServiceResourceDataTranslation.label: Service Resource Translation

ServiceResourceLeaveBalance.description: Stores the leave balances for service resources.

ServiceResourceOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a service resource with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
ServiceResourceOwnerSharingRule.label: Service Resource Owner Rule

ServiceResourcePreference.description: Represents the service resource scheduling preferences that are considered as a business objective in the scheduling logic engine.
ServiceResourcePreference.label: Service Resource Preference

ServiceResourceSkill.description: Represents the association between a skill and a service resource.
ServiceResourceSkill.label: Service Resource Skill

ServiceSetupProvisioning.description: Represents a task completed by the Service Setup Assistant.
ServiceSetupProvisioning.label: Service Setup Provisioning

ServiceTerritory.description: Represents a dealer location where service resources are located and service appointments are performed.
ServiceTerritory.label: Service Territory

ServiceTerritoryDataTranslation.description: Represents the translated values of the data stored within a ServiceTerritory record’s fields.
ServiceTerritoryDataTranslation.label: Service Territory Translation

ServiceTerritoryLocation.description: Represents a location associated with a particular service territory in field service.
ServiceTerritoryLocation.label: Service Territory Location

ServiceTerritoryMember.description: Represents a service resource who can be assigned to an appointment in a service territory.
ServiceTerritoryMember.label: Service Territory Member

ServiceTerritoryRelationship.description: Represents the relationship between service territories based on work types performed.

ServiceTerritoryWorkType.description: Represents the relationship between a ServiceTerritory object and a WorkType object for Salesforce Scheduler appointments.
ServiceTerritoryWorkType.label: Service Territory Work Type

SessionPermSetActivation.description: The SessionPermSetActivation object represents a permission set assignment activated during an individual user session. When a SessionPermSetActivation object is inserted into a permission set, an activation event fires, allowing the permission settings to apply to the user’s specific session.
SessionPermSetActivation.label: Session Permission Set Activation

SetupAuditTrail.description: Represents changes you or other admins made in your org’s Setup area for at least the last 180 days.
SetupAuditTrail.label: Setup Audit Trail Entry

SetupEntityAccess.description: Represents the enabled setup entity access settings (such as for Apex classes) for the parent PermissionSet.
SetupEntityAccess.label: Setup Entity Access

ShapeRepresentation.description: Contains information about the shape of an org. The shape of an org includes licenses and limits information. You can easily create scratch orgs based on a source org’s shape.

SharedSavingPaymentAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Shared Saving Payment Agreement type.
SharedSavingPaymentAgreement.label: Shared Saving Payment Agreement

SharingRecordCollectionItem.description: Represents a single record in a collection of records.
SharingRecordCollectionItem.label: Record Collection Item

SharingRecordCollectionMember.description: Represents a user with access to a collection of records.
SharingRecordCollectionMember.label: Record Collection Member

Shift.description: Represents a shift for service resource scheduling.
Shift.label: Shift

ShiftEngagementChannel.description: Represents the relationship between a Shift object and an Engagement Channel Type object for Salesforce Scheduler.
ShiftEngagementChannel.label: Shift Engagement Channel

ShiftHistory.description: Represents the history of changes made to tracked fields on a time sheet.
ShiftHistory.label: Shift History

ShiftOwnerSharingRule.description: Represents the rules for sharing a shift with user records other than the owner or anyone above the owner in the role hierarchy.
ShiftOwnerSharingRule.label: Shift Owner Rule

ShiftPattern.description: Represents a pattern of templates for creating shifts.
ShiftPattern.label: Shift Pattern

ShiftPatternEntry.description: ShiftPatternEntry links a shift template to a shift pattern.
ShiftPatternEntry.label: Shift Pattern Entry

ShiftSegment.description: Represents a scheduled activity within a shift.

ShiftSegmentType.description: Represents shift segment type settings for Shift Scheduling and Workforce Engagement.

ShiftShare.description: Represents a sharing entry on a field service shift.
ShiftShare.label: Shift Share

ShiftStatus.description: Represents a shift, such as Tentative, Published, or Confirmed.
ShiftStatus.label: Shift Status Value

ShiftTemplate.description: Represents a template for creating shifts.
ShiftTemplate.label: Shift Template

ShiftWorkTopic.description: Represents the relationship between a Shift object and a Work Type or Work Type Group object for Salesforce Scheduler.
ShiftWorkTopic.label: Shift Work Topic

Shipment.description: Represents a product item that’s in transit between two inventory locations.
Shipment.label: Shipment

ShipmentItem.description: Represents a product that’s included in a shipment.
ShipmentItem.label: Shipment Item

ShippingCarrier.description: Shipping company or carrier responsible for transporting goods or packages. Examples include UPS, FedEx, and USPS.
ShippingCarrier.label: Shipping Carrier

ShippingCarrierMethod.description: Shipping service provided by a shipping carrier. Examples include Ground, 2Day, and NextDay. Service depends on the range of transit times available for each carrier.
ShippingCarrierMethod.label: Shipping Carrier Method

ShippingConfigSetProduct.description: Represents a product associated with a shipping configuration.
ShippingConfigSetProduct.label: Shipping Config Set Product

ShippingConfigurationSet.description: Shipping configuration for a set of products in a store.
ShippingConfigurationSet.label: Shipping Configuration Set

ShippingRateArea.description: A designated geographical area that’s available for shipping.
ShippingRateArea.label: Shipping Rate Area

ShippingRateGroup.description: Available shipping rates based on shipping destination.
ShippingRateGroup.label: Shipping Rate Group

SignatureTask.description: Represents the signature-related information that a visitor captures as part of a visit.
SignatureTask.label: Signature Task

SignatureTaskLineItem.description: Represents a junction between a signature task and a digital signature captured in a visit.
SignatureTaskLineItem.label: Signature Task Line Item

SignupRequest.description: Represents a request for a new sign-up.
SignupRequest.label: Signup Request

Site.description: Represents a public website that is integrated with an org.
Site.label: Site

SiteDetail.description: Represents the details of a Salesforce site or Experience Cloud site. Available in API version 38.0 and later.
SiteDetail.label: Site Detail

SiteEventLog.description: SiteEventLog stores details of Site.com requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

SiteHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields of a site.
SiteHistory.label: Site History

SiteIframeWhitelistUrl.description: Represents a list of external domains that you allow to frame your Salesforce site or Experience Cloud site pages.

SiteRedirectMapping.description: Represents a site redirect from an external site to an Experience Cloud site.
SiteRedirectMapping.label: Site Redirect Mapping

Sites Event Type.description: Sites events contain details of Site.com requests. Requests can originate from the browser (UI).

Skill.description: Represents a skill that service resources have. For technician type service resources, the skill represents their area of expertise. For asset type service resources, the skill must be specified as Test Drive.
Skill.label: Skill

SkillLevelDefinition.description: Represents a skill which can be acquired by completing enablement site (myTrailhead) modules.

SkillLevelProgress.description: Represents training progress for a given user.

SkillProfile.description: Represents a join between Skill and Profile.
SkillProfile.label: Skill Profile

SkillRequirement.description: Represents a skill that is required to complete a particular work type.
SkillRequirement.label: Skill Requirement

SkillType.description: Represents the broader type or category that a skill belongs to.
SkillType.label: Skill Type

SkillUser.description: Represents a join between Skill and User.
SkillUser.label: Skill User

SlaProcess.description: Represents an entitlement process associated with an Entitlement.
SlaProcess.label: Entitlement Process

Snippet.description: Represents a snippet, which is a container for rich text that can be reused across Account Engagement emails and email templates.
Snippet.label: Snippet

SnippetAssignment.description: Represents a relationship between a snippet and a campaign. Assignments are required to use snippet content in Account Engagement emails and email templates. A snippet can be assigned to more than one campaign.
SnippetAssignment.label: Snippet Assignment

SoapApiEventLog.description: SOAP API events contain details about your org's SOAP API request activity.

SocialContributionSum.description: Represents information about social contributions made to political and non-political organizations belonging to financial and non-financial categories.
SocialContributionSum.label: Social Contribution Summary

SocialPersona.description: Represents a snapshot of a contact's profile on a social network such as Facebook or Twitter.
SocialPersona.label: Social Persona

SocialPost.description: Represents a snapshot of a post on a social network such as a Facebook or Twitter.
SocialPost.label: Social Post

Solution.description: Represents a detailed description of a customer issue and the resolution of that issue.
Solution.label: Solution

SolutionStatus.description: Represents the status of a Solution, such as Draft, Reviewed, and so on.
SolutionStatus.label: Solution Status Value

SolutionTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a Solution.

SrvcMgmtObjCollabAppCnfg.label: Service Management Object Collaboration App Configuration

StageCondition.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up the rules in transition criteria and stage change, including the object state, logic, and values. This object is available in API version 62.0 and later.
StageCondition.label: Stage Condition

StageTransitionEntry.description: Represents the information about the runtime instance of the object stage transition.
StageTransitionEntry.label: Stage Transition Entry

StampAssignment.description: Represents assignment of a User Specialty to a user.
StampAssignment.label: Stamp Assignment

StandardAction.description: Represents the buttons, links, and actions (standard actions) for a standard or custom object. This object is available in API version 34.0 and later.
StandardAction.label: Standard Action

StandardCareFeeAgreement.description: Specifies the payment terms for contracts of Standard Care Fee Agreement type.
StandardCareFeeAgreement.label: Standard Care Fee Agreement

StandardInvocableActionType.description: Represents a collection of fields to set up granular user permissions for access to a standard invocable action in Flow Builder.
StandardInvocableActionType.label: Standard Invocable Action Type

StandardShippingRate.description: Standard shipping rate for a store.
StandardShippingRate.label: Standard Shipping Rate

StaticResource.description: Represents the working copy of a static resource file for editing or saving. Static resources allow you to upload content that you can reference in a Visualforce page, including images, stylesheets, JavaScript, and other files.
StaticResource.label: Static Resource

StgTrnsUndwrEvaluation.description: Represents the underwriting rule evaluation result.
StgTrnsUndwrEvaluation.label: Stage Transition Underwriting Evaluation

StnryAssetAnnualFact.description: Represents the information about stationary assets and their types, which is used to quantify the related intensity.
StnryAssetAnnualFact.label: Stationary Asset Annual Fact

StnryAssetCrbnFtprnt.description: Represents the total carbon emissions and other environmental attributes from stationary assets. Carbon footprint quantifies the effect of atmospheric warming, which is represented in metric tonnes of carbon dioxide equivalent (tCO₂e). Additionally, it also quantifies various aspects of the energy performance of the asset.
StnryAssetCrbnFtprnt.label: Stationary Asset Carbon Footprint

StnryAssetCrbnFtprntItm.description: Represents the total tCO₂e emissions of individual fuel types, which are the child records of the stationary asset carbon footprint record.
StnryAssetCrbnFtprntItm.label: Stationary Asset Carbon Footprint Item

StnryAssetEnrgyUse.description: Represents the energy consumption related to stationary assets across multiple fuel types.
StnryAssetEnrgyUse.label: Stationary Asset Energy Use

StnryAssetEnvSrcCnfg.description: Represents the setup object that contains the mapping between the Stationary Asset Environmental Source record type and internal enums. You can primarily use this object for calculations across different record types.
StnryAssetEnvSrcCnfg.label: Stationary Asset Environmental Source Record Type Config

StnryAssetEnvrSrc.description: Represents assets that are stationary in nature, use energy that can be recorded, and are the source of greenhouse gas emissions.
StnryAssetEnvrSrc.label: Stationary Asset Environmental Source

StnryAssetWaterActvty.description: Represents information about the water activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge that are related to the stationary assets.
StnryAssetWaterActvty.label: Stationary Asset Water Activity

StnryAssetWaterFtprnt.description: Represents information about the total volume of water from the water activities, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge that are related to the stationary assets.
StnryAssetWaterFtprnt.label: Stationary Asset Water Footprint

StnryAssetWtrFtprntItm.description: Represents information about the total volume of water from each water activity, such as withdrawal, consumption, or discharge related to the stationary assets. Each water activity is a child record of the stationary asset water footprint object.
StnryAssetWtrFtprntItm.label: Stationary Asset Water Footprint Item

StoreActionPlanTemplate.description: Associate an action plan template with a store.

StoreAssortment.description: Associate an assortment to either a store, a store group, or an account.

StoreIntegratedService.description: Represents an association between an integration and a store.
StoreIntegratedService.label: Store Integrated Service

StoreProduct.description: Associate a product to a retail store or to a specific in-store location.

StreamingChannel.description: Represents a channel that is the basis for notifying listeners of generic Streaming API events.
StreamingChannel.label: Streaming Channel

SubscriberPackageVersionInstallRequest.label: Second Generation Package Version Install Request

SubscriberPackageVersionUninstallRequest.label: Second Generation Package Version Uninstall Request

SuccessTeam.description: Records details about a success team in Salesforce Scheduler.

SuggestedAssessmentReason.description: Stores the reasons for a suggested assessment.
SuggestedAssessmentReason.label: Suggested Assessment Reason

SupplementalCompensation.description: Represents the meals or equivalent gifts awarded to the field service worker according to the labor laws and company policies.

Supplier.description: Represents information about a supplier that a manufacturer procures product parts and components from.
Supplier.label: Supplier

SupplierProduct.description: Represents information about a product that’s procured from a supplier.
SupplierProduct.label: Supplier Product

Surcharge.description: Represents the details about a surcharge calculation.
Surcharge.label: Surcharge

SurveyEmailBranding.description: Represents the configuration settings for invitation emails sent to survey participants for a particular survey.
SurveyEmailBranding.label: Survey Email Branding

SurveyEngagementContext.description: Represents the context based on which a survey invitation was sent or a survey response was received.
SurveyEngagementContext.label: Survey Engagement Context

SurveyInvitation.description: Represents the invitation sent to a participant to complete the survey.
SurveyInvitation.label: Survey Invitation

SurveyPage.description: Represents a page, such as the title page or a question page, in a survey.
SurveyPage.label: Survey Page

SurveyQuestion.description: Represents a question in a survey.
SurveyQuestion.label: Survey Question

SurveyQuestionChoice.description: Represents an answer choice that a participant can select for a survey question.
SurveyQuestionChoice.label: Survey Question Choice

SurveyQuestionResponse.description: Represents a participant’s answer to a specific question.
SurveyQuestionResponse.label: Survey Question Response

SurveyQuestionScore.description: Represents the aggregate of responses for the following question types: date, multiple choice, picklist, radio, ranking, rating, scoring, slider, and Net Promoter Score® (NPS®).
SurveyQuestionScore.label: Survey Question Score

SurveyResponse.description: Represents information about a participant’s response to a survey, such as the status of the response, the participant’s location, and when the survey was completed.
SurveyResponse.label: Survey Response

SurveySubject.description: Represents a relationship between a survey and another object, such as an account or a case.
SurveySubject.label: Survey Subject

SurveyVersion.description: Represents a version of a survey.
SurveyVersion.label: Survey Version

SurveyVersionAddlInfo.description: Represents additional information about a survey version. This information defines the default settings of a survey version.
SurveyVersionAddlInfo.label: Survey Version Additional Info

SustainabilityCredit.description: Represents information about the sustainability credits that are a part of a sustainability purchase.
SustainabilityCredit.label: Sustainability Credit

SustainabilityPurchase.description: Represents information related to the sustainability credits purchases such as carbon credits.
SustainabilityPurchase.label: Sustainability Purchase

SustainabilityScorecard.description: Represents information about the annual sustainability scorecard of third-party organizations whose data is used to calculate scope 3 emissions.
SustainabilityScorecard.label: Sustainability Scorecard

SustainabilityStakeholder.description: Represents the stakeholder for sustainability data, such as stakeholder for environmental, social, and governance data.
SustainabilityStakeholder.label: Sustainability Stakeholder

SustainabilityTask.description: Represents the tasks that the sustainability stakeholder does for a sustainability task group.
SustainabilityTask.label: Sustainability Task

SustainabilityTaskGroup.description: Represents the group of sustainability tasks.
SustainabilityTaskGroup.label: Sustainability Task Group

SustainabilityUom.description: Represents information about the additional unit of measure values defined by a customer.
SustainabilityUom.label: Sustainability Unit of Measure

SustnMaterialUseSummary.description: Represents the circular economy information that a company discloses as part of ESRS E5 - Resource use and circular economy.
SustnMaterialUseSummary.label: Sustainability Material Use Summary

SustnUomConversion.description: Represents information about the unit of measure conversion for the additional fuel types defined by a customer.
SustnUomConversion.label: Sustainability Unit of Measure Conversion

SvcApptSchdEvent.description: Represents the service appointment event. This object is included in a streamed notification received on the channels for the parent platform events. You can’t subscribe to the SvcApptSchdEvent channel directly.
SvcApptSchdEvent.label: Service Appointment Scheduling Event

SvcCatalogCategory.description: Represents the grouping of individual catalog items in Service Catalog.
SvcCatalogCategory.label: Service Catalog Category

SvcCatalogCategoryItem.description: Represents the assignment of this service to a category within the Service Catalog.
SvcCatalogCategoryItem.label: Service Catalog Category Item

SvcCatalogFilterCriteria.description: Represents an eligibility rule that determines if a Service Catalog user has access to a catalog item.
SvcCatalogFilterCriteria.label: Service Catalog Filter Criteria

SvcCatalogFulfillFlowItem.description: Represents a variable in a fulfillment flow for Service Catalog that can accept input.
SvcCatalogFulfillFlowItem.label: Service Catalog Fulfillment Flow Item

SvcCatalogFulfillmentFlow.description: Represents the flow associated with a specific catalog item in the Service Catalog.
SvcCatalogFulfillmentFlow.label: Service Catalog Fulfillment Flow

SvcCatalogItemAttribute.description: Represents pre-filled fulfillment flow inputs and user questions to ask to users in the context of a service catalog item version.
SvcCatalogItemAttribute.label: Service Catalog Item Attribute

SvcCatalogItemDef.description: Represents the grouping of individual catalog items in Service Catalog.
SvcCatalogItemDef.label: Service Catalog Item Definition

SvcCatalogItemDependency.description: Represents a collection of records that indicate the dependencies of a service process.
SvcCatalogItemDependency.label: Service Catalog Item Dependency

SvcCatalogReqRelatedItem.description: Represents an item related to a Service Catalog Request.
SvcCatalogReqRelatedItem.label: Service Catalog Request Related Item

SvcCatalogRequest.description: Represents a request made by a user using the Service Catalog. Catalog builders use this object to report on Service Catalog activity.
SvcCatalogRequest.label: Service Catalog Request

SvcInfoRelatedQuestionnaire.description: Represents the questionnaire associated with a service information request or service information response coverage.

SvcInfoRespCoverageDetail.description: Represents additional coverage details about a service information response.

Swarm.description: Represents a team of agents, Salesforce users, or Slack users in a Slack channel or thread dedicated to solving a problem. This problem can be related to a support case, incident, sales opportunity, or change request.
Swarm.label: Swarm

SwarmMember.description: Represents a Salesforce member, such as an agent, of a swarm.
SwarmMember.label: Swarm Member

SymbolTable.description: A complex type that represents all user-defined tokens in the Body of an ApexClass, ApexClassMember, or ApexTriggerMember and their associated line and column locations within the Body.

TabDefinition.description: Represents a tab, and returns all tabs available in the org.
TabDefinition.label: Tab Definition

TagCategory.description: Group similar interest tags together into tag categories.
TagCategory.label: Tag Category

TagDefinition.description: Defines the attributes of child Tag objects.

Task.description: Represents a business activity such as making a phone call or other to-do items. In the user interface, Task and Event records are collectively referred to as activities.

TaskPriority.description: Represents the importance or urgency of a task, such as High, Normal, or Low.
TaskPriority.label: Task Priority Value

TaskRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a task and a lead, contacts, and other objects related to the task. If Shared Activities is enabled, this object doesn’t support triggers, workflow, or data validation rules.

TaskStatus.description: Represents the status of a task, such as Not Started, Completed, or Closed.
TaskStatus.label: Task Status Value

TaskTag.description: Associates a word or short phrase with a task .

TaskWhoRelation.description: Represents the relationship between a task and a lead or contacts.

TaxDisclosureSummary.description: Represents statistics about the disclosure of business entity information to all tax jurisdictions.
TaxDisclosureSummary.label: Tax Disclosure Summary

TaxEngine.description: Represents information about an instance of a tax engine provider as well as the merchant credentials for that specific instance.

TaxEngineInteractionLog.description: Represents a record of a communication with an external tax engine following a tax calculation request.

TaxEngineProvider.description: Represents general information about a service that manages a tax engine. Tax engine providers have a one-to-many relationship with tax engines, where the tax engine record represents a specific configuration of a tax engine that can be assigned to multiple order items.

TaxGeoConfig.description: Represents a tax configuration associated with a GeoCountry.
TaxGeoConfig.label: Tax Geo Configuration

TaxPolicy.description: Represents information about a group of tax treatments, where each treatment represents parameters to determine how a particular product is taxed for a transaction line item. Tax policies are related to products, which pass the policy on to the resulting order items and in turn the billing schedules.

TaxRate.description: Represents a tax rate for a tax code and country.
TaxRate.label: Tax Rate

TaxTreatment.description: Represents information about tax calculation by external engines. Each product requires a tax policy to determine whether to apply tax. Each tax policy requires at least one tax treatment. The tax treatments determine how taxable products are taxed.

Team.description: Represents the team of members associated with an organization.

TeamMember.description: Represents the member associated with a team.

TelemetryActionDefStep.description: Represents a step in the action for a telemetry signal definition.

TelemetryActionDefinition.description: Represents the action taken on a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle, such as getting the current status of a vehicle or its component, or sending a request to perform a remote action on the vehicle or its component.

TelemetryActionRelatedProcess.description: Represents the relationship between a telemetry action and a process triggered by the action such as a service catalog item definition or a product.

TelemetryActnDefStepAttr.description: Represents the attributes of a telemetry action definition step.

TelemetryDefinition.description: Represents the definition of the structure of a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle.

TelemetryDefinitionVersion.description: Represents a version of the structure of a telemetry signal sent from a connected asset or vehicle.

TenantScrAIPrmptInjection.description: Stores generative AI prompt injection data.

TenantSecret.description: This object stores an encrypted organization-specific key fragment that’s used with the primary secret (KDF seed) to produce org-specific data encryption keys.

TenantSecurityAIGtwyUsage.description: Stores Einstein generative AI gateway usage data.

TenantSecurityAlertRuleSelectedTenant.description: Stores information about a Security Center alert rule for tenants.

TenantSecurityApiAnomaly.description: Stores detected anomalies in how users typically make API calls. Fore more information, see Threat Detection. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityCertificate.description: Stores metric details related to public key certificate information. The certificate binds the public key to the identity of an entity.

TenantSecurityConfigAgent.description: Stores metric details related to implemented Agentforce Agents

TenantSecurityCustomMetricSetup.description: Represents the configuration for a custom metric within Security Center.

TenantSecurityCustomMetricStat.description: Represents custom metric data within Security Center.

TenantSecurityEncryptedField.description: Represents fields encrypted under your Shield Platform Encryption policy.

TenantSecurityFeature.description: Stores org features across all tenants in Security Center.

TenantSecurityGuestUserAnomaly.description: Represents metric details for guest user anomaly events detected by Threat Detection.

TenantSecurityHealthCheckDetail.description: Stores the details of Health Check scores for a connected tenant. The Health Check detail page in Security Center displays scores and settings for all your tenants in one place. Use this object to get settings and risks per tenant on a selected date.

TenantSecurityHealthCheckTrend.description: Stores the history of Security Health Check scores for a connected tenant within Security Center. Health Check in Security Center displays Health Check scores and the average risk settings for all your tenants in one place. This object belongs to the parent tenant and stores Health Check data pushed from child tenants. This object is available for Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityLicense.description: Stores license usage information within Security Center.

TenantSecurityLogin.description: Stores the login details of a single user to a tenant, grouped by date and type. You can query this object to find out how many times the user logged in to a specific tenant using a specific login type (for example, username/password or SSO). This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityLoginIpRangeTrend.description: Stores details of changes related to login IP ranges in Security Center.

TenantSecurityMetricDetailLink.description: Represents the link between the metric count and metric drill down.

TenantSecurityMobilePolicyTrend.description: Stores metrics related to changes in mobile security policies across all tenants in Security Center.

TenantSecurityMonitorMetric.description: Stores the daily count and daily count change for a metric within Security Center. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityNotification.description: Stores information about notifications that were triggered in Security Center as a function of the Alerts feature. For more information, see Create Alerts for Security Changes.

TenantSecurityNotificationRule.description: Stores an alert configured in the Security Center Alerts feature to notify recipients of changes made to security settings. For more information, see Create Alerts for Security Changes. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityPolicy.description: Stores security policies created and deployed in Security Center. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies.

TenantSecurityPolicyDeployment.description: Stores the status of deployments of a Security Center policy on a tenant. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 54.0 and later.

TenantSecurityPolicySelectedTenant.description: Stores the list of tenants selected for a Security Center policy. For more information, see Define and Deploy Security Policies. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 54.0 and later.

TenantSecurityReportAnomaly.description: Stores anomalies in how users run or export reports, including unsaved reports, as detected by Threat Detection. For more information, see Threat Detection. This object is available to Security Center subscribers in API version 53.0 and later.

TenantSecurityTenantInfo.description: Stores information on changes related to the tenant history.

TenantSecurityTransactionPolicyTrend.description: Stores changes to the count of Transaction Security Policies for a connected tenant within Security Center.

TenantSecurityTrigTransactionSecurityPol.description: Stores metric details related to Transaction Security Policy triggering events.

TenantSecurityTrustedIpRangeTrend.description: Stores details of changes related to trusted IP ranges in Security Center.

TenantUsageEntitlement.description: Represents a data structure that contains information about the features or functionalities that a Salesforce org has access to.
TenantUsageEntitlement.label: Tenant Usage Entitlement

Term.description: Represents a term or condition applied for a loan application or a collateral.

TermRelatedObject.description: Represents the relationship between a term and the object for which the term is defined.

Territory.description: Represents a flexible collection of accounts and users where the users have at least read access to the accounts, regardless of who owns the accounts.

Territory2AlignmentLog.description: Represents the start and end status of a territory assignment rule run job.
Territory2AlignmentLog.label: Territory2 Alignment Log

Territory2ModelHistory.description: Represents the history of changes to the values in the fields on a territory model.
Territory2ModelHistory.label: Territory Model History
